<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="Supervisory Authorities">
  <data key="d0">Supervisory Authorities</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Supervisory authorities are entities responsible for monitoring compliance with data protection laws and ensure that controllers and processors meet their obligations under the Regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;Supervisory authorities are bodies established in Member States responsible for overseeing data protection rights and enforcement.&lt;SEP&gt;Supervisory authorities are responsible for monitoring the application of data protection regulations, cooperating with each other, and handling complaints related to personal data processing.&lt;SEP&gt;Supervisory Authorities are entities that oversee compliance with data protection laws and support the enforcement of these regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Supervisory authorities are independent public authorities established in each Member State to monitor the application of personal data protection regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Supervisory authorities are entities responsible for compliance oversight and mutual assistance in regulatory matters.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f7c44f8c5cb297980b57ded26d28b04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-841ca8a926a3aaa8cdcb3960c2c0d626&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d89a0536404e78829969b0f7fe895176&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0789b58f298ba801f3b269230a509b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66ded376bcd1c12c425bce88cfd552a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8907f0fe9fc1b981b8c734b5cbf9008</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018959</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fundamental Rights and Freedoms">
  <data key="d0">Fundamental Rights and Freedoms</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Fundamental rights and freedoms include essential human rights that must be protected during the processing of personal data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f7c44f8c5cb297980b57ded26d28b04</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018959</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Personal Data Protection">
  <data key="d0">Personal Data Protection</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Personal data protection refers to the legal measures and practices in place to safeguard individuals' personal information from unauthorized use or disclosure.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f7c44f8c5cb297980b57ded26d28b04</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018959</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Independent Supervisory Authorities">
  <data key="d0">Independent Supervisory Authorities</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Independent supervisory authorities are public authorities responsible for monitoring the enforcement of personal data protection regulations throughout the Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f7c44f8c5cb297980b57ded26d28b04</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018959</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Legislation">
  <data key="d0">Legislation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Legislation refers to the specific laws and regulations governing the protection of personal data and the responsibilities of authorities in its enforcement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f7c44f8c5cb297980b57ded26d28b04</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018959</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises">
  <data key="d0">Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Micro, small and medium enterprises refer to businesses that are characterized by their small size and limited number of employees, and have specific needs for regulations regarding data processing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cd85d6e795b0f281182f4994bd0d3d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018959</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Controllers">
  <data key="d0">Controllers</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Controllers are entities that determine the purposes and means of processing personal data and have responsibilities under the Regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;Controllers are entities that determine the purposes and means of processing personal data and have significant obligations under data protection regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Controllers are entities that determine the purposes and means of processing personal data and can be held liable for damages.&lt;SEP&gt;Controllers are entities responsible for determining the purposes and means of processing personal data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cd85d6e795b0f281182f4994bd0d3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d89a0536404e78829969b0f7fe895176&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5bb48441e5e8722f7d89d485c663d88&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65949aed6696e22716296aea9c7eb380</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018959</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Processors">
  <data key="d0">Processors</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Processors are entities that process personal data on behalf of controllers and are also bound by the Regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;Processors are entities that process personal data on behalf of the controller and are tasked with adhering to specific regulations regarding data protection.&lt;SEP&gt;Processors are entities that process personal data on behalf of the controller and may also share liability for damages.&lt;SEP&gt;Processors are entities that process personal data on behalf of the controllers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cd85d6e795b0f281182f4994bd0d3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d89a0536404e78829969b0f7fe895176&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5bb48441e5e8722f7d89d485c663d88&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65949aed6696e22716296aea9c7eb380</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018959</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Certification Mechanisms">
  <data key="d0">Certification Mechanisms</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Certification mechanisms are systems established to enhance transparency and compliance regarding data protection, allowing quick assessment by data subjects.&lt;SEP&gt;Certification mechanisms are approved systems that validate compliance with data protection measures and can be referenced in Article 42.&lt;SEP&gt;Certification mechanisms refer to the procedures and standards used for granting certifications in data protection.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cd85d6e795b0f281182f4994bd0d3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4fb6b788c6bc23206d8cd996c5a6a6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ad40e7a844b107cf5d24e2adca46bdb</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018959</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Third Countries">
  <data key="d0">Third Countries</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Third countries are nations outside the jurisdiction of the Union where personal data may be transferred, necessitating specific data protection considerations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cd85d6e795b0f281182f4994bd0d3d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018959</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="International Organisations">
  <data key="d0">International Organisations</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">International organisations are entities formed by multiple countries that may receive personal data and have specific obligations under data protection regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;International organisations may also be exempt from the Regulation when acting under international agreements with the Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cd85d6e795b0f281182f4994bd0d3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3725d0d03194d1c923cc1275d5433c2a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019220</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European Union">
  <data key="d0">European Union</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Union (EU) is a political and economic union comprising member states primarily located in Europe. It plays a significant role in shaping laws and policies that affect its member countries, particularly in areas such as data protection and artificial intelligence regulation. 

The EU establishes common regulations, directives, and frameworks that govern various sectors, ensuring cooperation among member states. This includes specific regulations concerning data protection, which reflect the EU's commitment to safeguarding personal information, as well as its involvement in the governance of high-risk artificial intelligence systems.

As a collective entity, the European Union not only focuses on economic integration but also addresses broader issues of justice, democracy, and social policies. Through legislative processes, the EU develops and enforces standards that impact its member states, promoting a unified approach to various challenges. Its regulatory frameworks aim to balance innovation with safety, particularly in the rapidly evolving landscape of technology and digital services. 

Overall, the European Union stands as a pivotal institution in Europe, fostering collaboration among nations while navigating complex regulatory environments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cd85d6e795b0f281182f4994bd0d3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76c97638c70c32faaac95c378d456ab2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-224ac909847d6dc3f9484ef626d8ecd2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b39c0bb45bd2a8849aa7e9bcb8c9d4a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f763b444522d2da4e393e2f999f53812&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e99d990c855f3b544868eeee8a6b049b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f5283f6c8ea50d5bcac79684f773610&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfb1222254442ec5ae96316c08a386f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b64b4983aba9917221464e74b0d86865&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ab4686c3d64e748fcf2e50ddb488920&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3725d0d03194d1c923cc1275d5433c2a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24db102847abeef12e1042f8de042ea9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019183</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Adequacy Decision">
  <data key="d0">Adequacy Decision</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An adequacy decision is a determination made by the European Commission that a third country or international organisation offers an adequate level of data protection.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cd85d6e795b0f281182f4994bd0d3d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018960</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Third Country">
  <data key="d0">Third Country</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">A third country refers to any country that is not a member of the Union and is evaluated for data protection adequacy.&lt;SEP&gt;A third country is any nation that is not a member of the European Union or the European Economic Area in the context of data transfers.&lt;SEP&gt;A Third Country is a country outside of the relevant jurisdiction that may receive the transfer of personal data from the controller.&lt;SEP&gt;A Third Country refers to a nation that is not a member of the European Union but is considered for compliance with data protection rules.&lt;SEP&gt;A Third Country is a nation that is not a member of the European Union and may receive personal data transfers subject to specific safeguards.&lt;SEP&gt;A third country refers to any nation that is not a member of the Union but may be involved in agreements regarding mutual recognition of conformity assessments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2cbf3f86a25d11cd5d991d79db9a221a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7071cdf0dedffd1eaf46713ebddb9b1e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e144d059e01c4df4d2fdb9406d31751d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66f1f525b011c8f0bfb14ba0891419e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ab41d6ec0d1446be5ba58c1ab5b423c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b14c58587932db3a6dafb07fe1b8b673</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019214</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Council">
  <data key="d0">Council</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Council, formally known as the Council of the European Union, is a principal decision-making institution within the European Union (EU). It collaborates closely with the European Parliament on legislative matters, including significant issues such as data protection and the regulation of public sector information. Acting as a key body, the Council plays a crucial role in the legislative process, where it engages in decision-making alongside the Parliament and the European Commission.

Composed of representatives from the member countries of the EU, the Council serves to represent the governments of these member states in discussions related to EU laws and policies. This institution is responsible for enacting legislation, including establishing regulations pertinent to various areas, such as artificial intelligence systems. The Council holds the authority to revoke delegated powers and is integral to the regulatory framework of the EU, receiving necessary documentation from the Commission throughout the regulatory process.

Overall, the Council functions not only as a legislative body but also as a governing entity involved in the broader context of policy formulation and legislative action within the Union, cementing its position as a vital component in the structure of EU governance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2cbf3f86a25d11cd5d991d79db9a221a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f087b1b4f7f6e16afe33b8014a5f30c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58a23170492ef728683ec4aa9e03ccb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e302930e155db8d2b9e787df655d5751&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b39c0bb45bd2a8849aa7e9bcb8c9d4a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0ea41c30759ecd048ab40483ec1605b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c1a7de4ca41da4fd41e3254a6460114&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f5283f6c8ea50d5bcac79684f773610&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7078a625612fc9b62bb1e1986ffe1b7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b084b4b20e358aaf88a17e35cc6da65d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f35759698835ddd7beb04c8f00f74f9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22dcb6c71a1828d1166aad9d5a7cac19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b1941526d498e207caabd2fb04f938f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6a7c04a6e62adc17c47006b55b3e8bce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d055d5f99b33b0d67edb91e844c4185</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019205</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Protection Authorities">
  <data key="d0">Data Protection Authorities</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Data Protection Authorities are independent bodies in member states that oversee data protection policies and practices.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2cbf3f86a25d11cd5d991d79db9a221a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018961</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Protection of Personal Data">
  <data key="d0">Protection of Personal Data</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Protection of Personal Data refers to the legal framework ensuring the privacy and rights of individuals regarding their personal information.&lt;SEP&gt;The Protection of Personal Data involves safeguarding individuals' personal information in accordance with laws and regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Protection of Personal Data refers to the rights and safeguards for individuals concerning their personal information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2cbf3f86a25d11cd5d991d79db9a221a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87f4c2229943d3f8e84a9941f117b8b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae28521738df7feadad1be4821afc294</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018961</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 25(6)">
  <data key="d0">Article 25(6)</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 25(6) pertains to the transfer of personal data to third countries under certain conditions within Directive 95/46/EC.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 25(6) refers to a specific provision in Directive 95/46/EC regarding the transfer of personal data to third countries.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2cbf3f86a25d11cd5d991d79db9a221a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66f1f525b011c8f0bfb14ba0891419e3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018961</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 26(4)">
  <data key="d0">Article 26(4)</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 26(4) addresses the conditions imposed on data transfers within the provisions of Directive 95/46/EC.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2cbf3f86a25d11cd5d991d79db9a221a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018962</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Binding Corporate Rules">
  <data key="d0">Binding Corporate Rules</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Binding Corporate Rules are internal policies companies adopt to facilitate international data transfers while ensuring compliance with data protection laws.&lt;SEP&gt;Binding Corporate Rules are data protection policies that govern personal data transfers within a group of undertakings between controllers or processors across Member States and third countries.&lt;SEP&gt;Binding corporate rules are internal policies adopted by companies to ensure that personal data is processed in compliance with applicable data protection laws.&lt;SEP&gt;Binding Corporate Rules are internal policies adopted by multinational companies to ensure that personal data is protected during international transfers.&lt;SEP&gt;Binding Corporate Rules are internal policies within corporations that govern international data transfers and are designed to ensure the protection of personal data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2cbf3f86a25d11cd5d991d79db9a221a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d95ad85f86f6e4a4771e8f92b0cbf27&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1184185c4bc8012fe969516fa45f07b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ab41d6ec0d1446be5ba58c1ab5b423c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c22927198decad5ee173ab2f05d62983</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018962</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Standard Data Protection Clauses">
  <data key="d0">Standard Data Protection Clauses</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Standard Data Protection Clauses are pre-approved contractual terms that can be used to ensure data protection in international agreements.&lt;SEP&gt;Standard Data Protection Clauses are legal provisions established to facilitate the transfer of personal data while ensuring protection measures are upheld.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2cbf3f86a25d11cd5d991d79db9a221a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ab41d6ec0d1446be5ba58c1ab5b423c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018962</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Commission">
  <data key="d0">Commission</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Commission refers to the European Commission, which is the executive body of the European Union (EU). It plays a pivotal role in proposing legislation, overseeing adherence to EU laws, and implementing decisions across various sectors, including data protection and artificial intelligence (AI) systems. Specifically, the Commission is responsible for establishing data protection standards, including actively evaluating and approving adequacy decisions for third countries regarding data protection measures. It promotes compliance with these regulations within the EU framework, facilitating international cooperation in the enforcement of data protection laws.

In the realm of AI, the Commission serves as the governing body that regulates compliance for both general-purpose and high-risk AI models. It oversees the development and implementation of codes of practice and regulations concerning AI systems, ensuring that processes are compliant with established standards. The Commission is empowered to designate certain AI models as presenting systemic risks based on thorough assessments and can adopt delegated acts aimed at improving regulatory measures. This includes overseeing the conformity assessment bodies responsible for evaluating AI systems and ensuring ongoing compliance with legal frameworks.

The Commission is also tasked with supporting the establishment of voluntary model contractual terms for collaboration between providers and third parties, alongside encouraging the creation of benchmarks and measurement methods related to AI. It liaises with Member States to oversee the notifications related to law enforcement practices and facilitates communication among them regarding the implementation of AI regulations and market surveillance. Furthermore, the Commission maintains oversight of regulatory compliance measures necessary to ensure effective data protection and high ethical standards in AI use.

Overall, the Commission embodies a key regulatory authority within the EU, responsible for setting guidelines, ensuring regulatory compliance, and enhancing the protection of data and AI practices, thereby addressing both legal and ethical considerations in these rapidly evolving fields.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f7c44f8c5cb297980b57ded26d28b04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2cbf3f86a25d11cd5d991d79db9a221a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-841ca8a926a3aaa8cdcb3960c2c0d626&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9552394e758f858742ece06fe166111&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da5e0cbe02b415c14c47d962922ae943&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe63429efbb90ae6ec22b62b5d79e7b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51e09a8c8db52827f80f9874a8d4e4de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d95ad85f86f6e4a4771e8f92b0cbf27&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0789b58f298ba801f3b269230a509b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f087b1b4f7f6e16afe33b8014a5f30c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af9d06fe383d38e16d29be00a265867e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-224ac909847d6dc3f9484ef626d8ecd2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d44a5f83cf273e81899482e995be2a98&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58a23170492ef728683ec4aa9e03ccb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e302930e155db8d2b9e787df655d5751&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b39c0bb45bd2a8849aa7e9bcb8c9d4a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8907f0fe9fc1b981b8c734b5cbf9008&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fb6a4af737980e04056c2522ea213fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87ae75b9888750c7d94cfda6be4f3dac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4fb6b788c6bc23206d8cd996c5a6a6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66f1f525b011c8f0bfb14ba0891419e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3642f938e14bfed60a5d5b5fdc383e38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80e46c2caec4056bbc2d3b305e3ed190&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d37ffab0584c5106298892733e2c26d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-088a4c3c3c775d33baa63868a127c869&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a54b012266e9b9c7302fce6d400f583&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38cdce9b64b40ba40d6acb529d375787&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6651a485fa4747217fdc9be856c3bf9d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f137cf6069f0720a443c5b5abd0fe3ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e20d35aae57ccfd5ec58ef7772f98c17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b75f7d42df244a78773a748afb4f421f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46bc64e87ac07d3576c10a8dd9d66d9e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f5283f6c8ea50d5bcac79684f773610&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-382f1c7a3c02bab4bf3bee2d03cc7e1f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20cc9868fcea5ce578101b36c79a42ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5f6ef3b354bb0dbf8af7b2c108fd236&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d997baeb2a2ac2118ac1e3e19dfcf16&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6507d56efb6357f20f57227d44b681ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d97d0e266280dff1c105fac7dc08fc5d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0714fdb65a0577bc4493dcb81d0a915&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed27aea701ddc7f366ea5adbe8a4b8e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24db102847abeef12e1042f8de042ea9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b14c58587932db3a6dafb07fe1b8b673&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73e4afb71ddc31ffc854d861300d4eb6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf7d18a6020405fb3429834a129e7cd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fe225f6b6c5b43aceb1fd1109bf8e4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc7122206f7a3097526258a05d85baef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-546a0f6bb154d36417ac57e86137b45d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15ddf6f50e7dd1750489a4999454bcdf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f743aee05d8e1afc03000436802a1ad2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4996cfa66f0668d565cd83bbe46dd21a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ad4d08daad55de411fe1304fd990b8e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6a7c04a6e62adc17c47006b55b3e8bce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e4463f7eaf425919a6a8182d693643c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-413f3509ccce7d84f0a2044eb12be69f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfd6bb7a9801a10b9d2b6a706f0d919d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfb1222254442ec5ae96316c08a386f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b1941526d498e207caabd2fb04f938f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78ea54ae6ffd2850256fb7ad037b8474&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b28096d582da2417ada6ecd24c88d994</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
