<node id="Council of Europe Convention of 28 January 1981">
  <data key="d0">Council of Europe Convention of 28 January 1981</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The Council of Europe Convention of 28 January 1981 is an international agreement aimed at protecting individuals regarding the automatic processing of personal data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2cbf3f86a25d11cd5d991d79db9a221a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018965</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Member State">
  <data key="d0">Member State</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">A Member State refers to a country that is part of the European Union (EU) and is governed by its regulations, laws, and directives. These states have the responsibility to implement EU regulations in various areas, particularly in data protection, personal data processing, and the regulation of artificial intelligence (AI) systems. Each Member State establishes its own supervisory authorities to ensure compliance with EU mandates, thereby contributing to the collective regulatory framework that guides public interest.

Member States are integral to the EU's governance structure, operating within their jurisdictions where they manage courts and supervisory bodies. They play a vital role in shaping data protection laws and maintaining legal cohesiveness within the Union. Each state must adhere to the broader agreements of the EU while managing its supervisory authorities and fulfilling responsibilities related to the protection and transfer of personal data. 

In addition to data protection, Member States hold powers to regulate the use of AI systems, including those for biometric identification, determining conditions around documentation, especially for high-risk AI systems, and assuming liability for conformity assessments conducted by notified bodies. They are also tasked with assessing compliance against common specifications and ensuring the safety and conformity of AI systems within their territories.

Member States, therefore, not only participate as collective entities within the EU but also act as individual national governing bodies responsible for their own legal regulations, including issues related to law enforcement, asylum, and migration. This dual role enhances both cooperation and regulatory compliance within the larger framework of the union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f7c44f8c5cb297980b57ded26d28b04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6cef9a553db9271d5edd9d76997b31b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca204399e5b95988e550678c5f4db7ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-18dac2bb6a1be4d5442954b82a769ffd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1552a23fe0792f0f86048881370b455d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9552394e758f858742ece06fe166111&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd97dcdb68144953a81ad8ba7d8f52b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0789b58f298ba801f3b269230a509b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66ded376bcd1c12c425bce88cfd552a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-36a1ea945634c046899535f1e8f39a77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e52d9f505adab3ccf36c6979ad3a7d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f087b1b4f7f6e16afe33b8014a5f30c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bbf8c83dfe1a6df2d3a3d01645abe8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db7bcd6a42a9c26ced1d71444d109dff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af9d06fe383d38e16d29be00a265867e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-224ac909847d6dc3f9484ef626d8ecd2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4816e09d93a70dec7bd3be2be787d180&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af27fd67de6b968672bf93dbf11392ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f500418ca711a20a360004da8c1f5ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3626adc7cf865bec83f6479c1e08cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40ecaa725d6d1bc748899703ed8b84dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e5e9be572ec001588771fa74ce45258&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b3266fc2be81fd61dcffc1afc41700b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ad40e7a844b107cf5d24e2adca46bdb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1184185c4bc8012fe969516fa45f07b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62c64f05f2da893351ea92b9eac1c889&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f40cde20fc8948de8e853c9a34187f56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80e46c2caec4056bbc2d3b305e3ed190&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38cdce9b64b40ba40d6acb529d375787&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ca50c2792c184b300a7d258f980e38c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46bc64e87ac07d3576c10a8dd9d66d9e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51749b7ff68c3ff9e52c0d29dfb02772&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78ea54ae6ffd2850256fb7ad037b8474&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0714fdb65a0577bc4493dcb81d0a915&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e64e0ad4efda4fc9f3a84823cb301955&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfb1222254442ec5ae96316c08a386f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ff761b32d779286afb789136edfc0b4c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab5bd61fedb2857e3db189c5f7bb8f94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eced97c6a138205573883808dbd74066&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b4a84f46448cc3a4a1755da273e920e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019189</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 54">
  <data key="d0">Article 54</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 54 outlines rules for the establishment of supervisory authorities within Member States.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 54 outlines the provisions related to reporting infringements of regulations by natural persons.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 54 specifies the requirements for authorized representatives of providers of general-purpose AI models in the Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6cef9a553db9271d5edd9d76997b31b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e09a4cc6243398f5e32d65a6312bd87&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-546a0f6bb154d36417ac57e86137b45d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019218</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 55">
  <data key="d0">Article 55</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 55 pertains to the powers of the supervisory authority in relation to data processing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 55 details the competence, tasks, and powers assigned to supervisory authorities within their respective Member States.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 55 outlines the procedures and provisions related to the actions of supervisory authorities in response to requests from other authorities.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 55 refers to a provision that allows supervisory authorities to adopt provisional measures in cases of non-compliance.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 55 describes the obligations specifically for providers of General-Purpose AI Models that pose systemic risks.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 55 sets additional requirements for compliance related to AI practices.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6cef9a553db9271d5edd9d76997b31b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-841ca8a926a3aaa8cdcb3960c2c0d626&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9552394e758f858742ece06fe166111&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65949aed6696e22716296aea9c7eb380&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13766dce116c63c31fc5d746b27279fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ba035757525dfa257fa2b97fdbd40b2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019219</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 56">
  <data key="d0">Article 56</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 56 discusses the competence of the lead supervisory authority for cross-border processing by controllers or processors.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 56 addresses relevant codes of practice and commitments that may influence the imposition of fines on AI model providers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6cef9a553db9271d5edd9d76997b31b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-382f1c7a3c02bab4bf3bee2d03cc7e1f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019204</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Professional Secrecy">
  <data key="d0">Professional Secrecy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Professional secrecy is a legal obligation to protect confidential information processed by individuals.&lt;SEP&gt;Professional secrecy is the obligation of professionals to keep specific information confidential, especially regarding personal data of data subjects.&lt;SEP&gt;Professional Secrecy is a duty imposed on members and staff of supervisory authorities to keep sensitive information confidential.&lt;SEP&gt;Professional Secrecy is an obligation that ensures confidentiality in the processing of personal data by controllers or processors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6cef9a553db9271d5edd9d76997b31b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8ea5b2826564cb4f4f5c8c193fab368&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc7a45c7f8eea9ab9297b5839c19c2a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40ecaa725d6d1bc748899703ed8b84dc</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018967</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Lead Supervisory Authority">
  <data key="d0">Lead Supervisory Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Lead Supervisory Authority is the main body overseeing a cross-border processing case involving data subjects from multiple Member States.&lt;SEP&gt;The Lead Supervisory Authority is the primary authority responsible for overseeing regulatory compliance and processing activities related to data protection within its jurisdiction.&lt;SEP&gt;The lead supervisory authority serves as the primary contact for controllers or processors regarding cross-border processing.&lt;SEP&gt;The Lead Supervisory Authority is responsible for making, adopting, and notifying decisions related to data processing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;The Lead Supervisory Authority is the primary entity responsible for adopting final decisions based on the Board's determinations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ca204399e5b95988e550678c5f4db7ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1552a23fe0792f0f86048881370b455d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da5e0cbe02b415c14c47d962922ae943&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e52d9f505adab3ccf36c6979ad3a7d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bbf8c83dfe1a6df2d3a3d01645abe8f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018967</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 60">
  <data key="d0">Article 60</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 60 outlines the procedures that the supervisory authority must follow when handling certain cases regarding data protection.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 60 refers to legal provisions under which supervisory authorities operate and adopt final decisions.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 60 refers to a section of regulation detailing testing in real-world conditions for high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 60 sets the regulations regarding the testing of high-risk AI systems in real-world conditions outside AI regulatory sandboxes.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 60 establishes protocols for conducting testing in real-world conditions, including informed consent and liabilities.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 60 details the compliance requirements for AI systems operating in real-world conditions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ca204399e5b95988e550678c5f4db7ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51e09a8c8db52827f80f9874a8d4e4de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5af0747da2a9f2783a1bde010a13814&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92f9c6220442ff06dfe6fe52499f18aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eced97c6a138205573883808dbd74066&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e4463f7eaf425919a6a8182d693643c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019187</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Articles 61 and 62">
  <data key="d0">Articles 61 and 62</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Articles 61 and 62 detail additional procedures and responsibilities for supervisory authorities that choose not to lead a case.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ca204399e5b95988e550678c5f4db7ee</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018968</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 57">
  <data key="d0">Article 57</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 57 outlines the tasks and powers of the supervisory authority.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 57 contains tasks and responsibilities defined for supervisory authorities in relation to personal data protection.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ca204399e5b95988e550678c5f4db7ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65949aed6696e22716296aea9c7eb380&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-413f3509ccce7d84f0a2044eb12be69f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018968</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Subjects">
  <data key="d0">Data Subjects</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Data subjects are individuals whose personal data is processed and who are granted specific rights and protections under various data protection regulations and laws. These rights commonly include rectification, erasure, and restriction of processing, which empower individuals to manage how their personal information is handled. The concept of data subjects underscores the importance of respecting and safeguarding the freedoms and rights of individuals in relation to their personal data.

Under data protection frameworks, data subjects have defined rights that must be acknowledged and respected. These rights ensure that data subjects can exercise control over their personal data, including the ability to access their information and seek assistance from a Data Protection Officer to understand and enforce these rights. 

Overall, the status of data subjects is crucial within the broader context of data governance, highlighting the need for accountability and transparency in the processing of personal data by organizations and institutions. This emphasis on individual rights aligns with international standards in data protection.&lt;SEP&gt;Data subjects are individuals whose personal data may be processed in the context of the AI regulatory sandbox.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cd85d6e795b0f281182f4994bd0d3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47177763646868a685685b7567bea40f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d89a0536404e78829969b0f7fe895176&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe63429efbb90ae6ec22b62b5d79e7b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fa083a0dd77efdae774f798a1d2f060&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-499a505625518b0e48c48965f5a70336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8907f0fe9fc1b981b8c734b5cbf9008&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ce0488d21ac5956f37974d7ae0799b4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c22927198decad5ee173ab2f05d62983&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ad40e7a844b107cf5d24e2adca46bdb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e0d95f75393cb87bb510dfcf3ba0ef5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 80">
  <data key="d0">Article 80</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 80 addresses procedures for lodging complaints regarding personal data processing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ca204399e5b95988e550678c5f4db7ee</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018968</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 28">
  <data key="d0">Article 28</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 28 outlines specific obligations and requirements for processors when handling personal data on behalf of controllers.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 28 refers to standard contractual clauses to be adopted for the processing of personal data.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 28 includes standard data protection clauses relevant to the processing of personal data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ca204399e5b95988e550678c5f4db7ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-18dac2bb6a1be4d5442954b82a769ffd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0ab083807b5f91410241f4f574d25b8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018968</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation">
  <data key="d0">Regulation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation represents a comprehensive and binding legislative framework established by the European Union that governs various aspects of data processing and the use of artificial intelligence (AI) systems. Primarily, the Regulation aims to ensure compliance with legal obligations, protect the rights of data subjects, and establish unified standards for data protection across Member States.

In regards to data protection, the Regulation sets forth a series of rules and guidelines detailing the responsibilities of data controllers and processors. These stipulations ensure that personal data is handled in an ethical manner, while also outlining individual rights related to personal data and specifying the penalties for non-compliance. The framework promotes transparency in how personal data is processed and enforces the conduct of supervisory authorities overseeing these processes, striving to protect individuals from abuses and breaches.

In addition to data protection, the Regulation governs the use and development of AI systems with a strong emphasis on public interests and rights protection. It establishes rules specific to the compliance of both Union entities and third-country providers of AI systems, particularly concerning high-risk applications and national security. The Regulation stresses the importance of governance measures, including compliance obligations for AI technologies, operational transparency, and risk management associated with general-purpose AI models.

The Regulation also addresses the operational standards for notified bodies responsible for assessing conformity and outlines the requirements for AI regulatory sandboxes. These sandboxes are intended to facilitate the safe experimentation and use of AI innovations within a governed framework. Overall, the Regulation serves as a vital legal structure ensuring the ethical deployment of technological advancements, safeguarding individual rights in the landscape of data processing and AI system integration across the European Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f7c44f8c5cb297980b57ded26d28b04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6cef9a553db9271d5edd9d76997b31b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2d13a59890e903c4e56162458f272ab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3dec771ee61059f33dea3999f6d5facd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bb97fdc90c81e778311b34e1a2883b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d89a0536404e78829969b0f7fe895176&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d95ad85f86f6e4a4771e8f92b0cbf27&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0085cb3cc5d5dc4d434424e6dab722f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66ded376bcd1c12c425bce88cfd552a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0ab083807b5f91410241f4f574d25b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f087b1b4f7f6e16afe33b8014a5f30c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bbf8c83dfe1a6df2d3a3d01645abe8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbc89674e06d04462cc498a8c1da1d44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af9d06fe383d38e16d29be00a265867e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-224ac909847d6dc3f9484ef626d8ecd2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4816e09d93a70dec7bd3be2be787d180&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af27fd67de6b968672bf93dbf11392ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f500418ca711a20a360004da8c1f5ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8ea5b2826564cb4f4f5c8c193fab368&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc7a45c7f8eea9ab9297b5839c19c2a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e302930e155db8d2b9e787df655d5751&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-499a505625518b0e48c48965f5a70336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb2f14226b252ba13becf59370a070e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0ea41c30759ecd048ab40483ec1605b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c1a7de4ca41da4fd41e3254a6460114&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ad40e7a844b107cf5d24e2adca46bdb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b39c0bb45bd2a8849aa7e9bcb8c9d4a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b45385ec456bd2744fcc58cd02368fc0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf9439294cd1ddefbd5a696360ace9e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5f6ef3b354bb0dbf8af7b2c108fd236&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f35759698835ddd7beb04c8f00f74f9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78ea54ae6ffd2850256fb7ad037b8474&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a8f57272764fbaa96a8c14389c0661d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6507d56efb6357f20f57227d44b681ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b5a506beb14df3337a120faddb2f0b6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15ddf6f50e7dd1750489a4999454bcdf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3725d0d03194d1c923cc1275d5433c2a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f40b01fb5e1dbaa442b55c31285ecb50&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f743aee05d8e1afc03000436802a1ad2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-061f3c307dd55152ffbb5bdfae17ea90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ccdea28ee93cb8cfdf2099776ddcb591&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00803764d58d840979922e38d1dc555c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55fa705f95ec5acec79f8b691041b65c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77f7e4da7918161a180fb26c5a1704ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-413f3509ccce7d84f0a2044eb12be69f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5a5973b039f9a9af3e3e9d93b392c66</data>
