<node id="Article 36">
  <data key="d0">Article 36</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 36 provides guidelines regarding the processing operations for which the supervisory authority must give advice.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 36 pertains to the processing of personal data and the necessary authorizations required by law in Member States.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 36 refers to a section of the regulatory text that outlines changes related to the notifications of notified bodies.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 36 addresses changes to notifications that must be communicated by the notifying authority.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ca204399e5b95988e550678c5f4db7ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-18dac2bb6a1be4d5442954b82a769ffd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78ea54ae6ffd2850256fb7ad037b8474&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6507d56efb6357f20f57227d44b681ea</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019211</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Public Authority">
  <data key="d0">Public Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Public authority refers to an organization or body that regulates specific processing operations in accordance with data protection regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Public authority refers to government or public bodies that have the responsibility for making decisions and providing public services regulated by law.&lt;SEP&gt;A public authority is defined as an entity that can deploy AI systems and operates under legal or governmental frameworks.&lt;SEP&gt;Public Authority refers to governmental organizations responsible for implementing regulations and ensuring compliance in their respective sectors.&lt;SEP&gt;A public authority is an entity responsible for safeguarding substantial public interest through the development of AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1fc0f10aaf2165d757efc7d75a7d7d18&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0ea41c30759ecd048ab40483ec1605b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-70bf47b2a9599482bedc275e3e2257a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22dcb6c71a1828d1166aad9d5a7cac19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e0d95f75393cb87bb510dfcf3ba0ef5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019203</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Personal Data">
  <data key="d0">Personal Data</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Personal data refers to any information related to an identified or identifiable natural person. This information is subject to various legal protections and regulations to ensure privacy and responsible processing. Personal data can encompass a wide range of information, including details about both children and adults, and may contain risks and rights considerations during its processing.

The concept of personal data requires that it be handled with care and specific restrictions in accordance with applicable laws. This includes compliance with processing regulations that safeguard the information from misuse and ensure individuals' rights are respected. Personal data is pertinent in multiple contexts, including research, archiving, and service provision, where the need for responsible use and protection is paramount.

Personal data consistently highlights the critical relationship between identifiable individuals and the information that relates to them. This information must be processed by controllers in a manner that adheres to established legal principles, ensuring both security and respect for individual privacy. As such, personal data is central to discussions about data protection and privacy across various jurisdictions and legal frameworks.&lt;SEP&gt;Personal Data refers to any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person, which is protected under Union law.&lt;SEP&gt;Personal data refers to any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person, which is protected under the EU regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Personal data refers to any information that relates to an identified or identifiable natural person.&lt;SEP&gt;Personal data includes any data that relates to an identified or identifiable individual, which may be processed under regulations concerning privacy and data protection.&lt;SEP&gt;Personal data refers to sensitive information that may be processed by innovative AI systems within the regulatory framework of AI sandboxes.&lt;SEP&gt;Personal data refers to information that relates to identified or identifiable individuals and may be processed within the AI regulatory sandbox.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cd85d6e795b0f281182f4994bd0d3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca204399e5b95988e550678c5f4db7ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2d13a59890e903c4e56162458f272ab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3dec771ee61059f33dea3999f6d5facd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bb97fdc90c81e778311b34e1a2883b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d89a0536404e78829969b0f7fe895176&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b303412f58783d3e4bc19dbad4e2a43c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd97dcdb68144953a81ad8ba7d8f52b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0085cb3cc5d5dc4d434424e6dab722f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66ded376bcd1c12c425bce88cfd552a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bfe3c72af8b2bd319fe191920f25097&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e52d9f505adab3ccf36c6979ad3a7d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b661d0b109eaf570a61ae0d0ca8020b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4816e09d93a70dec7bd3be2be787d180&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e302930e155db8d2b9e787df655d5751&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62b277bc6fa564a434a6c338a48eea46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-35884c5ef57faf321ff9fce99bd2d970&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-499a505625518b0e48c48965f5a70336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fa893844a2197c46302e74437f2bbef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2016931a6e14615018d3d7f8304b6a1e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb2f14226b252ba13becf59370a070e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e144d059e01c4df4d2fdb9406d31751d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9355b1cd3c48988b8332485ef99af2c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9403aaca1e6e92e51844c1b1175b373b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8252fb4b704db3adac7bfb7714d3b70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df28c0bb060b598df163cc06bf49d0e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0ea41c30759ecd048ab40483ec1605b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae28521738df7feadad1be4821afc294&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ce0488d21ac5956f37974d7ae0799b4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4fb6b788c6bc23206d8cd996c5a6a6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40ecaa725d6d1bc748899703ed8b84dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ab41d6ec0d1446be5ba58c1ab5b423c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e5e9be572ec001588771fa74ce45258&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4b86ca29202de00c1292db00c1efa4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd94ba8542b0c8ff4b050fc6027f5237&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e99d990c855f3b544868eeee8a6b049b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74667d89df5ee6111b7743e86ee4744f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ccdea28ee93cb8cfdf2099776ddcb591&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e0d95f75393cb87bb510dfcf3ba0ef5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019171</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Protection Impact Assessment">
  <data key="d0">Data Protection Impact Assessment</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Data Protection Impact Assessment (DPIA) is a crucial procedure implemented by the data Controller to thoroughly evaluate the risks associated with the processing of personal data. This assessment is particularly significant when the data processing operations involve high-risk activities, ensuring that the rights and freedoms of natural persons are protected.

A DPIA serves as a systematic evaluation process that identifies potential risks connected to data processing activities and ensures compliance with relevant regulations. It is not merely a one-time evaluation but a documented process that aims to both identify and mitigate any potential risks associated with personal data handling. This includes understanding the implications of processing operations and the effects they may have on individual privacy.

Furthermore, the Data Protection Impact Assessment is essential for assessing how personal data is handled, especially within advanced technologies such as artificial intelligence systems. By evaluating these risks, the DPIA plays a vital role in fostering trust and accountability in the management of personal data. Overall, the Data Protection Impact Assessment stands as a foundational element in the broader framework of data protection, emphasizing the importance of privacy in an increasingly data-driven world.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1fc0f10aaf2165d757efc7d75a7d7d18&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3dec771ee61059f33dea3999f6d5facd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ce3387b9f0e9256cf8b0a10e0726f37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9552394e758f858742ece06fe166111&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-274264435e41f5d230030900b38f8c35&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f71c70521bc1935b4a077373428f4b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df28c0bb060b598df163cc06bf49d0e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a13415ed2c222ba72d78fdab855a6ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81b13333cc1be55a8f31fdada74da057</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019211</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Protection Officers">
  <data key="d0">Data Protection Officers</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Data protection officers are individuals responsible for overseeing data protection compliance and ensuring that personal data processing adheres to regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1fc0f10aaf2165d757efc7d75a7d7d18</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018970</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Codes of Conduct">
  <data key="d0">Codes of Conduct</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Codes of conduct are guidelines drawn up by associations to facilitate the application of data protection regulations and tailor obligations for specific sectors.&lt;SEP&gt;Codes of Conduct are guidelines developed for fair processing of personal data, addressing specific processing contexts.&lt;SEP&gt;Codes of conduct are guidelines created by providers or organizations to govern the ethical deployment and operation of AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1fc0f10aaf2165d757efc7d75a7d7d18&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8907f0fe9fc1b981b8c734b5cbf9008&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b75f7d42df244a78773a748afb4f421f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019201</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Union">
  <data key="d0">Union</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Union refers to the European Union, which is a political and economic union of European countries. This collective of member states operates under a framework that emphasizes shared regulations and agreements concerning various sectors, including the protection of personal data and the governance of artificial intelligence (AI) systems.

As a structural entity, the Union is dedicated to maintaining an internal market and safeguarding individual rights, particularly in terms of data protection. It achieves this through a comprehensive governance framework that includes various institutions and bodies responsible for overseeing the development and enforcement of laws and standards. The member states collaborate closely to regulate personal data processing, ensuring compliance with common legislation while addressing the evolving challenges of a digital landscape.

In addition to its work in data protection, the Union extends its regulatory focus to AI practices. It has established harmonization legislation for high-risk AI systems and is involved in the governance of AI technologies and their associated risks. This includes creating regulatory sandboxes that facilitate testing and innovation in AI, while also ensuring safety and accountability across member states. The Union's regulatory mechanisms play a crucial role in shaping a secure and collaborative environment for data processing and AI development.

The collective nature of the Union, characterized by cooperation among its member states, not only enhances its ability to implement common standards but also promotes a unified approach to various legal and political matters. By adhering to treaties and agreements, the Union further influences the regulatory landscape across Europe, ensuring that collective interests—both economic and social—are addressed in a manner that reflects the interconnectedness of its member countries.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cd85d6e795b0f281182f4994bd0d3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2cbf3f86a25d11cd5d991d79db9a221a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2d13a59890e903c4e56162458f272ab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe63429efbb90ae6ec22b62b5d79e7b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd97dcdb68144953a81ad8ba7d8f52b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0789b58f298ba801f3b269230a509b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66ded376bcd1c12c425bce88cfd552a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e52d9f505adab3ccf36c6979ad3a7d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db7bcd6a42a9c26ced1d71444d109dff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4816e09d93a70dec7bd3be2be787d180&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-499a505625518b0e48c48965f5a70336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b63383abdca30a6a477ed963f4766dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9403aaca1e6e92e51844c1b1175b373b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40ecaa725d6d1bc748899703ed8b84dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e5e9be572ec001588771fa74ce45258&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ad40e7a844b107cf5d24e2adca46bdb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6651a485fa4747217fdc9be856c3bf9d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e47ed52d4514f1818e6c0687c1aa57e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f137cf6069f0720a443c5b5abd0fe3ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-70bf47b2a9599482bedc275e3e2257a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-474ee56c196aef9638f343ef09589bca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7aba082da5b9f8ab2defc1a7a725bef0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bb17f83caa294ef6efb4f278d7d59fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13766dce116c63c31fc5d746b27279fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ba035757525dfa257fa2b97fdbd40b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3725d0d03194d1c923cc1275d5433c2a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ccdea28ee93cb8cfdf2099776ddcb591&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00803764d58d840979922e38d1dc555c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b1941526d498e207caabd2fb04f938f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eced97c6a138205573883808dbd74066&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caf8819d467d1204dd768c10cacdbf06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e4463f7eaf425919a6a8182d693643c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55fa705f95ec5acec79f8b691041b65c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51c94d77f328c85a261162f4664235f6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
