</node>
<node id="Certification Body">
  <data key="d0">Certification Body</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">A Certification Body is responsible for issuing and renewing certification for data controllers or processors under specified criteria.&lt;SEP&gt;A certification body is responsible for granting or withdrawing certifications in accordance with regulatory requirements set out in relevant articles.&lt;SEP&gt;The Certification Body is responsible for issuing and withdrawing certifications related to compliance with data protection regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The certification body is responsible for ensuring compliance with specific obligations as stipulated in the regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8bb97fdc90c81e778311b34e1a2883b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-224ac909847d6dc3f9484ef626d8ecd2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-39551a1dbe3cdde38b22607932e0688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4fb6b788c6bc23206d8cd996c5a6a6b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018974</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 58">
  <data key="d0">Article 58</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 58 refers to specific powers granted to the Supervisory Authority in the context of data processing regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 58 specifies the powers of the supervisory authority in monitoring compliance with regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 58 outlines the powers, investigative, corrective, and advisory abilities of the Supervisory Authority concerning personal data protection.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 58 outlines the powers and obligations of the Supervisory Authority concerning the processing of personal data and its enforcement mechanisms.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8bb97fdc90c81e778311b34e1a2883b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-18dac2bb6a1be4d5442954b82a769ffd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f71c70521bc1935b4a077373428f4b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65949aed6696e22716296aea9c7eb380</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018975</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 83">
  <data key="d0">Article 83</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 83 pertains to the imposition of administrative fines for violations of data protection regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 83 discusses formal non-compliance findings by market surveillance authorities and required actions by relevant providers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8bb97fdc90c81e778311b34e1a2883b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38cdce9b64b40ba40d6acb529d375787</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
