<node id="Controller">
  <data key="d0">Controller</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Controller is an entity or individual responsible for determining the purposes and means of processing personal data. This role encompasses the obligation to ensure that data processing activities comply with applicable data protection regulations. The Controller is tasked with obtaining consent from data subjects, informing them of their rights, and demonstrating that such consent has been acquired. Additionally, the Controller holds the accountability for managing personal data, implementing measures to mitigate risks associated with data breaches, and responding to requests from data subjects.

In the context of legal compliance, the Controller must adhere to regulations governing data protection and may be subject to oversight by a Supervisory Authority. This includes taking necessary actions to maintain transparency and compliance in processing activities. The Controller's responsibilities also extend to ensuring that all data processing is conducted in line with the established laws and that any non-compliance can lead to legal consequences.

Overall, the Controller plays a critical role in shaping the framework under which personal data is processed, signifying their importance in safeguarding data subjects' privacy rights while navigating regulatory requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ca204399e5b95988e550678c5f4db7ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1fc0f10aaf2165d757efc7d75a7d7d18&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47177763646868a685685b7567bea40f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bb97fdc90c81e778311b34e1a2883b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89bcf919dc1ff2d224ffc9b6e042a2c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1552a23fe0792f0f86048881370b455d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ce3387b9f0e9256cf8b0a10e0726f37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b303412f58783d3e4bc19dbad4e2a43c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd97dcdb68144953a81ad8ba7d8f52b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7071cdf0dedffd1eaf46713ebddb9b1e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66ded376bcd1c12c425bce88cfd552a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0ab083807b5f91410241f4f574d25b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bfe3c72af8b2bd319fe191920f25097&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f087b1b4f7f6e16afe33b8014a5f30c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b661d0b109eaf570a61ae0d0ca8020b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bbf8c83dfe1a6df2d3a3d01645abe8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbc89674e06d04462cc498a8c1da1d44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db7bcd6a42a9c26ced1d71444d109dff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4816e09d93a70dec7bd3be2be787d180&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62b277bc6fa564a434a6c338a48eea46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-35884c5ef57faf321ff9fce99bd2d970&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-499a505625518b0e48c48965f5a70336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3626adc7cf865bec83f6479c1e08cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca37d7dbc74be645fc1de3e6e772a586&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2016931a6e14615018d3d7f8304b6a1e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e144d059e01c4df4d2fdb9406d31751d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9355b1cd3c48988b8332485ef99af2c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7aa4d903bc5ead1fdb896356fd92fbd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8252fb4b704db3adac7bfb7714d3b70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-274264435e41f5d230030900b38f8c35&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df28c0bb060b598df163cc06bf49d0e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f71c70521bc1935b4a077373428f4b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d92eec8ceb3813d55e2b578c5604f24&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae28521738df7feadad1be4821afc294&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8907f0fe9fc1b981b8c734b5cbf9008&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c09ea8bbba955df15eafbe1da5facb38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fb6a4af737980e04056c2522ea213fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1184185c4bc8012fe969516fa45f07b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c22927198decad5ee173ab2f05d62983&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e5e9be572ec001588771fa74ce45258&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b3266fc2be81fd61dcffc1afc41700b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ad40e7a844b107cf5d24e2adca46bdb</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018975</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High Risk">
  <data key="d0">High Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">High risk refers to situations where processing operations could lead to significant damage or adverse effects on the rights and freedoms of natural persons.&lt;SEP&gt;High risk refers to the likelihood of a personal data breach resulting in significant negative consequences for the rights and freedoms of natural persons.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-89bcf919dc1ff2d224ffc9b6e042a2c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df28c0bb060b598df163cc06bf49d0e9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018975</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Notification">
  <data key="d0">Notification</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Notification is the act of informing the supervisory authority or data subjects about a personal data breach, as required by regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Notification refers to the process by which authorities inform the Commission and Member States about changes to notified bodies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-89bcf919dc1ff2d224ffc9b6e042a2c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6507d56efb6357f20f57227d44b681ea</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019211</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 43">
  <data key="d0">Article 43</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 43 outlines the requirements and responsibilities of certification bodies in the context of data protection.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 43 relates to the accreditation of certification bodies by the Supervisory Authority.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 43 covers the accreditation and review of certification bodies related to data protection.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 43 outlines another aspect of powers and procedures regarding delegated acts in the regulatory framework.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 43 refers to the conformity assessment procedure that high-risk AI systems must undergo before being placed on the market.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 43 specifies requirements related to the identification number of the notified body responsible for conformity assessments.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 43 pertains to certain provisions regarding the operational authority and delegation of power within the EU.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-18dac2bb6a1be4d5442954b82a769ffd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e09a4cc6243398f5e32d65a6312bd87&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58a23170492ef728683ec4aa9e03ccb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-39551a1dbe3cdde38b22607932e0688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e20d35aae57ccfd5ec58ef7772f98c17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f5283f6c8ea50d5bcac79684f773610&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fe225f6b6c5b43aceb1fd1109bf8e4f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019200</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 46">
  <data key="d0">Article 46</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 46 outlines the conditions under which personal data may be transferred to third countries, including the necessity of appropriate safeguards.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 46 relates to appropriate safeguards for the transfer of personal data to third countries or international organizations.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 46 addresses contractual clauses and administrative arrangements concerning data processing.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 46 pertains to the conformity assessment procedures outlined in the Regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-18dac2bb6a1be4d5442954b82a769ffd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66f1f525b011c8f0bfb14ba0891419e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b3266fc2be81fd61dcffc1afc41700b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-413f3509ccce7d84f0a2044eb12be69f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019223</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 47">
  <data key="d0">Article 47</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 47 of the European data protection legislation outlines the requirements for Binding Corporate Rules.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 47 deals with the approval of binding corporate rules by the Supervisory Authority.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 47 focuses on the EU declaration of conformity that must be drafted by providers of high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 47 refers to a specific regulation within the legal framework governing high-risk AI systems and their compliance.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 47 involves procedural elements regarding the revocation and management of delegated acts within the EU structure.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-18dac2bb6a1be4d5442954b82a769ffd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ab41d6ec0d1446be5ba58c1ab5b423c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e20d35aae57ccfd5ec58ef7772f98c17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f5283f6c8ea50d5bcac79684f773610&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c3976a157910b9837b3b68c158c5b6b9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019200</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Charter">
  <data key="d0">Charter</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Charter sets out the fundamental rights and freedoms that must be adhered to within the Union.&lt;SEP&gt;The Charter refers to a legal document outlining the rights of individuals, including Article 47 concerning judicial remedies.&lt;SEP&gt;The Charter outlines rights and protections regarding personal data within the EU legal framework.&lt;SEP&gt;The Charter refers to the Charter of Fundamental Rights of the European Union, which sets out the rights and freedoms of individuals.&lt;SEP&gt;The Charter enshrines fundamental rights, including health, safety, democracy, and environmental protection within the European Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-18dac2bb6a1be4d5442954b82a769ffd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd97dcdb68144953a81ad8ba7d8f52b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af9d06fe383d38e16d29be00a265867e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b5a506beb14df3337a120faddb2f0b6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6a7c04a6e62adc17c47006b55b3e8bce</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019215</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Annual Report">
  <data key="d0">Annual Report</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The Annual Report documents the activities of the Supervisory Authority and is sent to national parliaments and other authorities.&lt;SEP&gt;The Annual Report is a document prepared by the Board regarding the protection of natural persons and the practical application of guidelines and best practices.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-18dac2bb6a1be4d5442954b82a769ffd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e09a4cc6243398f5e32d65a6312bd87</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cooperation Mechanism">
  <data key="d0">Cooperation Mechanism</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Cooperation Mechanism is a framework for collaboration between the lead supervisory authority and other supervisory authorities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-18dac2bb6a1be4d5442954b82a769ffd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 61">
  <data key="d0">Article 61</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 61 refers to the provisions regarding mutual assistance among supervisory authorities.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 61 pertains to the regulations governing informed consent for participation in testing of high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 61 outlines requirements for obtaining informed consent from subjects participating in AI testing under real-world conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 61 outlines additional conditions and responsibilities for market surveillance related to AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-18dac2bb6a1be4d5442954b82a769ffd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5af0747da2a9f2783a1bde010a13814&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caf8819d467d1204dd768c10cacdbf06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e4463f7eaf425919a6a8182d693643c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019187</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 62">
  <data key="d0">Article 62</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 62 deals with joint operations conducted by supervisory authorities for investigations related to data protection.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 62 refers to a specific segment of the regulatory framework outlining the operations of supervisory authorities and mutual assistance protocols.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 62 refers to a section of legislation concerning the coordination of AI regulatory sandboxes with national competent authorities.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 62 provides measures for supporting SMEs and startups in accessing AI regulatory sandboxes and complying with relevant regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-18dac2bb6a1be4d5442954b82a769ffd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-841ca8a926a3aaa8cdcb3960c2c0d626&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b28096d582da2417ada6ecd24c88d994&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e4463f7eaf425919a6a8182d693643c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019221</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Processor">
  <data key="d0">Processor</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Processor refers to an entity that processes personal data on behalf of the Controller, which can be either an individual or an organization. This entity is fundamental within data protection frameworks, as it operates under the authority of the Controller and must adhere to specific regulatory obligations regarding data management.

Processors handle personal data while ensuring compliance with relevant regulations, including maintaining data security and fulfilling breach notification requirements. They are also required to assist the Controller in meeting legal obligations related to data protection. This involves cooperating with supervisory authorities, and in some cases, may include consulting them on pertinent issues.

Furthermore, Processors have certain liabilities depending on how they manage and protect the data. They are bound by the decisions of supervisory authorities, which impose necessary compliance measures. In instances of non-compliance, Processors can be held accountable for any breaches of regulation, highlighting their pivotal role in safeguarding personal data. 

Ultimately, the Processor plays an essential role in the data processing ecosystem, tasked with the dual responsibility of processing data on behalf of the Controller and ensuring adherence to applicable legal standards and obligations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ca204399e5b95988e550678c5f4db7ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1fc0f10aaf2165d757efc7d75a7d7d18&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47177763646868a685685b7567bea40f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bb97fdc90c81e778311b34e1a2883b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1552a23fe0792f0f86048881370b455d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ce3387b9f0e9256cf8b0a10e0726f37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7071cdf0dedffd1eaf46713ebddb9b1e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66ded376bcd1c12c425bce88cfd552a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0ab083807b5f91410241f4f574d25b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f087b1b4f7f6e16afe33b8014a5f30c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bbf8c83dfe1a6df2d3a3d01645abe8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbc89674e06d04462cc498a8c1da1d44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db7bcd6a42a9c26ced1d71444d109dff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-499a505625518b0e48c48965f5a70336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3626adc7cf865bec83f6479c1e08cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-274264435e41f5d230030900b38f8c35&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f71c70521bc1935b4a077373428f4b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8907f0fe9fc1b981b8c734b5cbf9008&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fb6a4af737980e04056c2522ea213fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1184185c4bc8012fe969516fa45f07b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c22927198decad5ee173ab2f05d62983&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e5e9be572ec001588771fa74ce45258</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Supervisory Authorities Concerned">
  <data key="d0">Supervisory Authorities Concerned</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Supervisory Authorities Concerned are various regulatory bodies that collaborate on decisions and share relevant information regarding compliance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1552a23fe0792f0f86048881370b455d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Complainant">
  <data key="d0">Complainant</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Complainant is an individual or entity that lodges a complaint with a supervisory authority regarding data processing activities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1552a23fe0792f0f86048881370b455d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 66">
  <data key="d0">Article 66</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 66 refers to a procedural article that outlines urgent measures for protecting the interests of data subjects in exceptional circumstances.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 66 includes specifications regarding the urgent measures that may be adopted by supervisory authorities in specific circumstances.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 66 outlines the conditions under which urgent action is necessary for supervisory authorities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1552a23fe0792f0f86048881370b455d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-841ca8a926a3aaa8cdcb3960c2c0d626&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9552394e758f858742ece06fe166111</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Electronic Means">
  <data key="d0">Electronic Means</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Electronic means refer to methods used for the processing and handling of personal data through technology.&lt;SEP&gt;Electronic Means refers to the platform or method used for the exchange of information among supervisory authorities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1552a23fe0792f0f86048881370b455d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97d77d4c79204175483320a1c612b93b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mutual Assistance">
  <data key="d0">Mutual Assistance</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Mutual Assistance involves support provided between supervisory authorities to ensure compliance and effective regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;Mutual Assistance reflects the cooperation among supervisory authorities to provide assistance and relevant information to each other.&lt;SEP&gt;Mutual Assistance refers to the obligations of Member States to assist each other regarding compliance with data protection regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1552a23fe0792f0f86048881370b455d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9552394e758f858742ece06fe166111&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bbf8c83dfe1a6df2d3a3d01645abe8f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Subject">
  <data key="d0">Data Subject</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Data Subject is an individual whose personal data is being collected, processed, or stored, and they possess specific rights regarding their information as outlined in data protection regulations. This concept of the Data Subject underscores the importance of individual privacy rights, particularly in the context of data processing and management by organizations.

A Data Subject is entitled to be informed about the processing of their data and must give their consent for such processing under certain conditions. This includes rights related to accessing and rectifying their information, lodging complaints, and ensuring that their rights and freedoms are protected by supervisory authorities. The Data Subject status encompasses not only natural persons whose data is processed but also highlights the obligations of data controllers and processors to assure compliance with these rights.

Furthermore, the Data Subject's personal data must be handled in accordance with defined regulations, which require organizations to inform them about the nature of data collection and processing. These obligations aim to empower data subjects, ensuring transparency and fostering trust in data practices.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1fc0f10aaf2165d757efc7d75a7d7d18&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bb97fdc90c81e778311b34e1a2883b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b303412f58783d3e4bc19dbad4e2a43c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51e09a8c8db52827f80f9874a8d4e4de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd97dcdb68144953a81ad8ba7d8f52b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7071cdf0dedffd1eaf46713ebddb9b1e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0085cb3cc5d5dc4d434424e6dab722f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-36a1ea945634c046899535f1e8f39a77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0ab083807b5f91410241f4f574d25b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bfe3c72af8b2bd319fe191920f25097&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f087b1b4f7f6e16afe33b8014a5f30c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b661d0b109eaf570a61ae0d0ca8020b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbc89674e06d04462cc498a8c1da1d44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af9d06fe383d38e16d29be00a265867e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af27fd67de6b968672bf93dbf11392ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8ea5b2826564cb4f4f5c8c193fab368&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc7a45c7f8eea9ab9297b5839c19c2a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62b277bc6fa564a434a6c338a48eea46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97d77d4c79204175483320a1c612b93b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-35884c5ef57faf321ff9fce99bd2d970&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3626adc7cf865bec83f6479c1e08cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fa893844a2197c46302e74437f2bbef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4dfe3f1190ff8cf7dc9f62b85bed40a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca37d7dbc74be645fc1de3e6e772a586&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2016931a6e14615018d3d7f8304b6a1e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e144d059e01c4df4d2fdb9406d31751d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9355b1cd3c48988b8332485ef99af2c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7aa4d903bc5ead1fdb896356fd92fbd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8252fb4b704db3adac7bfb7714d3b70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d92eec8ceb3813d55e2b578c5604f24&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae28521738df7feadad1be4821afc294&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c09ea8bbba955df15eafbe1da5facb38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40ecaa725d6d1bc748899703ed8b84dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b3266fc2be81fd61dcffc1afc41700b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e5e9be572ec001588771fa74ce45258</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Urgent Need">
  <data key="d0">Urgent Need</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An Urgent Need refers to situations where a supervisory authority must act quickly to protect the interests of data subjects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1552a23fe0792f0f86048881370b455d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Union or Member State Law">
  <data key="d0">Union or Member State Law</data>
  <data key="d1">legalconcept</data>
  <data key="d2">Union or Member State Law refers to the legal frameworks governing the activities of Controllers and Processors in data handling.&lt;SEP&gt;Union or Member State law sets forth the legal framework and obligations that govern the processing of personal data for various purposes within a jurisdiction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ce3387b9f0e9256cf8b0a10e0726f37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ce0488d21ac5956f37974d7ae0799b4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Joint Operations">
  <data key="d0">Joint Operations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Joint Operations refer to collaborative efforts between supervisory authorities to tackle regulatory compliance issues effectively.&lt;SEP&gt;Joint operations involve collaborative activities between supervisory authorities, including joint investigations and enforcement measures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-841ca8a926a3aaa8cdcb3960c2c0d626&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bbf8c83dfe1a6df2d3a3d01645abe8f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018977</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Request for Mutual Assistance">
  <data key="d0">Request for Mutual Assistance</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A request for mutual assistance is a formal request made by one supervisory authority to another for information or support in oversight activities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-841ca8a926a3aaa8cdcb3960c2c0d626</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018977</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Code of Conduct">
  <data key="d0">Code of Conduct</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A code of conduct is a set of guidelines that organizations must adhere to for processing personal data.&lt;SEP&gt;The Code of Conduct provides guidelines for compliance and ethical data handling practices.&lt;SEP&gt;A Code of Conduct sets the standards for conduct and compliance that organizations must follow under data protection laws.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c9552394e758f858742ece06fe166111&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65949aed6696e22716296aea9c7eb380&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fb6a4af737980e04056c2522ea213fe</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018977</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 63">
  <data key="d0">Article 63</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 63 refers to the consistency mechanism for ensuring compliance across Member States.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 63 details the procedure to submit draft codes to the Board for approval.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 63 discusses the approval process and criteria relevant to the certification mechanisms in data protection.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 63 pertains to the mechanism for achieving consistency in the application of the Regulation throughout the Union.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 63 outlines aspects of the consistency mechanism for data protection regulations among supervisory authorities.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 63 discusses derogations available for microenterprises in the context of compliance with quality management systems related to AI.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c9552394e758f858742ece06fe166111&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51e09a8c8db52827f80f9874a8d4e4de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-274264435e41f5d230030900b38f8c35&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65949aed6696e22716296aea9c7eb380&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-39551a1dbe3cdde38b22607932e0688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e4463f7eaf425919a6a8182d693643c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019223</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 64">
  <data key="d0">Article 64</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 64 discusses the process for the Board to issue opinions regarding various measures adopted by supervisory authorities.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 64 discusses the procedural requirements for adopting decisions related to the consistency mechanism.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 64 covers the consistency mechanism for decisions made by supervisory authorities regarding data protection regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c9552394e758f858742ece06fe166111&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51e09a8c8db52827f80f9874a8d4e4de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e09a4cc6243398f5e32d65a6312bd87</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018977</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) 2016/679">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) 2016/679</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) 2016/679, commonly referred to as the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), is a pivotal legislative act established by the European Parliament and Council aimed at safeguarding personal data and ensuring the free movement of such data within the European Union (EU). This regulation lays down comprehensive rules for the processing of personal information, reflecting the importance of data protection and privacy in the digital age.

The GDPR governs the collection and processing of personal data, setting forth essential guidelines to protect individuals' privacy rights. It addresses various aspects of data handling, including specific provisions for biometric data, and influences how personal data is processed by technology systems, such as artificial intelligence. As a legal framework, the GDPR articulates the obligations of data controllers—those who determine the purposes and means of processing personal data—and delineates the rights granted to data subjects, whom the data pertains to.

In addition to outlining the fundamental principles for data protection, Regulation (EU) 2016/679 also references critical components such as the data protection impact assessment, which is necessary for evaluating risks associated with data processing activities. Its adoption marks a significant step in enhancing data protection standards within the EU, establishing a robust framework that harmonizes data privacy laws across member states. The GDPR has continually influenced data practices, ensuring that individuals' rights are prioritized in an increasingly data-driven society.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76c97638c70c32faaac95c378d456ab2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a242b3e1d633e7e955057a9b078f32d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9238afdc9781d2e524a5550b3c165bed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd94ba8542b0c8ff4b050fc6027f5237&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-234952a50b5a02b1afedbe8d8e1c076b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8b33cb346ddcf954cb3e193a006d6add&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d05ea92d6d58b07fd1569406080813a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a13415ed2c222ba72d78fdab855a6ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-358eb1d0b0f35e665a7b23702159cfd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-880ccb1f68ffcae0925e238408590ede&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe99ac2ad30ad5f2f6c6c5e2e23456e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc7122206f7a3097526258a05d85baef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7aba082da5b9f8ab2defc1a7a725bef0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81b13333cc1be55a8f31fdada74da057&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74667d89df5ee6111b7743e86ee4744f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5da5d9be8aadcb05915f4a8f8f5aa33</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019190</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European Commission">
  <data key="d0">European Commission</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Commission is the executive branch of the European Union, which proposes legislation and has a role in the development of regulations such as the General Data Protection Regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Commission is the executive branch of the European Union that proposes new laws and regulations, including those related to artificial intelligence.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Commission is the executive branch of the European Union, tasked with proposing legislation and implementing decisions.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Commission oversees compliance with regulations and may approve codes of practice for AI providers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76c97638c70c32faaac95c378d456ab2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b64b4983aba9917221464e74b0d86865&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d5a14698f71544a90fc06f98323f315&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ba035757525dfa257fa2b97fdbd40b2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019215</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Charter of Fundamental Rights of the European Union">
  <data key="d0">Charter of Fundamental Rights of the European Union</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The Charter of Fundamental Rights of the European Union outlines the rights and freedoms guaranteed to all individuals in the EU, including the protection of personal data.&lt;SEP&gt;The Charter of Fundamental Rights outlines the fundamental rights and freedoms protected within the European Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76c97638c70c32faaac95c378d456ab2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b64b4983aba9917221464e74b0d86865</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019215</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European Economic and Social Committee">
  <data key="d0">European Economic and Social Committee</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Economic and Social Committee is an advisory body of the European Union that provides opinions on issues related to the internal market and the integration of European Union policies.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Economic and Social Committee provides advice to the European Parliament and Council on economic and social matters.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76c97638c70c32faaac95c378d456ab2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f35759698835ddd7beb04c8f00f74f9a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019210</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Committee of the Regions">
  <data key="d0">Committee of the Regions</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Committee of the Regions is an advisory body of the European Union that represents regional and local authorities and contributes to legislation impacting local governance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76c97638c70c32faaac95c378d456ab2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018977</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Administrative Fines">
  <data key="d0">Administrative Fines</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Administrative fines are penalties imposed for non-compliance with regulations, intended to deter infringements.&lt;SEP&gt;Administrative fines are penalties imposed on undertakings or individuals for infringement, considering the economic situation and general income levels in the Member State.&lt;SEP&gt;Administrative Fines are penalties imposed by the Supervisory Authority for infringements of the Regulation, aimed at ensuring compliance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-87f4c2229943d3f8e84a9941f117b8b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbc89674e06d04462cc498a8c1da1d44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5bb48441e5e8722f7d89d485c663d88</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018977</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Denmark">
  <data key="d0">Denmark</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Denmark is a Member State where administrative fines are treated as criminal penalties imposed by national courts.&lt;SEP&gt;Denmark is a Member State of the EU with certain exceptions related to biometric categorization systems and processing personal data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-87f4c2229943d3f8e84a9941f117b8b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6243f0a255a83e57f7b7de8b0b878719</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019191</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Estonia">
  <data key="d0">Estonia</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Estonia is a Member State where administrative fines are imposed by the supervisory authority within a misdemeanour procedure.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-87f4c2229943d3f8e84a9941f117b8b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018978</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Member States">
  <data key="d0">Member States</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Member States refer to the individual countries that comprise the European Union (EU) and hold the responsibility of implementing and adhering to its various laws and regulations, particularly concerning data protection, AI systems, and governance. These nations are obliged to follow established EU directives related to personal data processing and AI regulation, demonstrating a collective commitment to safeguarding data privacy and managing the deployment of artificial intelligence technologies.

As members of the EU, the Member States have the authority to adapt their specific legal frameworks while remaining bound by overarching EU regulations. Each Member State must consult with relevant Supervisory Authorities to ensure alignment with EU directives, actively participate in collaborative assessments of data protection measures, and engage in the promotion of data protection initiatives. They are also tasked with implementing regulations pertaining to high-risk AI systems, establishing AI Regulatory Sandboxes for testing and innovation, and designating representatives to the European Artificial Intelligence Board.

In addition to their obligations around data protection, Member States are involved in governance related to AI systems, contributing to discussions regarding compliance standards, guidelines, and oversight mechanisms. They are expected to report to the European Commission on their resources allocated to national competent authorities every two years, ensuring transparency and accountability in their governance practices. This collaborative framework allows Member States to uphold a high standard of governance and security while addressing the diverse interests and impacts associated with AI deployment.

Overall, the concept of Member States encapsulates their role as sovereign entities that not only function within the European Union's legislative framework but also play an integral part in shaping the future of data protection and AI regulation within their jurisdictions. Their efforts significantly influence both individual data subjects and organizational practices across the region, as they work collectively to navigate the complexities of modern technology regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1fc0f10aaf2165d757efc7d75a7d7d18&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2d13a59890e903c4e56162458f272ab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-841ca8a926a3aaa8cdcb3960c2c0d626&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87f4c2229943d3f8e84a9941f117b8b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe63429efbb90ae6ec22b62b5d79e7b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7071cdf0dedffd1eaf46713ebddb9b1e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d44a5f83cf273e81899482e995be2a98&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e302930e155db8d2b9e787df655d5751&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-499a505625518b0e48c48965f5a70336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b63383abdca30a6a477ed963f4766dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb2f14226b252ba13becf59370a070e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9403aaca1e6e92e51844c1b1175b373b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-274264435e41f5d230030900b38f8c35&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f71c70521bc1935b4a077373428f4b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8907f0fe9fc1b981b8c734b5cbf9008&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c09ea8bbba955df15eafbe1da5facb38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fb6a4af737980e04056c2522ea213fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87ae75b9888750c7d94cfda6be4f3dac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66f1f525b011c8f0bfb14ba0891419e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c22927198decad5ee173ab2f05d62983&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-663826fe1821a9ef057cd84da3b741a8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f379f07f844b3112cd145a56e02874b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80a99ad850f0546ea9da41c8d764b154&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5af0747da2a9f2783a1bde010a13814&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3642f938e14bfed60a5d5b5fdc383e38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-088a4c3c3c775d33baa63868a127c869&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a54b012266e9b9c7302fce6d400f583&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e47ed52d4514f1818e6c0687c1aa57e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b75f7d42df244a78773a748afb4f421f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f5283f6c8ea50d5bcac79684f773610&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b45385ec456bd2744fcc58cd02368fc0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-880ccb1f68ffcae0925e238408590ede&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5f6ef3b354bb0dbf8af7b2c108fd236&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d997baeb2a2ac2118ac1e3e19dfcf16&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6507d56efb6357f20f57227d44b681ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b14c58587932db3a6dafb07fe1b8b673&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf7d18a6020405fb3429834a129e7cd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a169417b09f70fa2792a3c9ce82a678d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7aba082da5b9f8ab2defc1a7a725bef0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81b13333cc1be55a8f31fdada74da057&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d5a14698f71544a90fc06f98323f315&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15ddf6f50e7dd1750489a4999454bcdf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df0cf5bee4370453cb38606bad89b764&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3725d0d03194d1c923cc1275d5433c2a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f743aee05d8e1afc03000436802a1ad2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22207e9a20c55a3749a58440b8aab4fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00803764d58d840979922e38d1dc555c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55fa705f95ec5acec79f8b691041b65c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77f7e4da7918161a180fb26c5a1704ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51c94d77f328c85a261162f4664235f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-413f3509ccce7d84f0a2044eb12be69f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5a5973b039f9a9af3e3e9d93b392c66&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfd6bb7a9801a10b9d2b6a706f0d919d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019171</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Right to Freedom of Expression">
  <data key="d0">Right to Freedom of Expression</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Right to Freedom of Expression encompasses various forms of expression including journalistic, academic, artistic, and literary expressions, protected under this Regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;The Right to Freedom of Expression pertains to the fundamental right individuals have to express their opinions freely.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-87f4c2229943d3f8e84a9941f117b8b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2016931a6e14615018d3d7f8304b6a1e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018978</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 11 of the Charter">
  <data key="d0">Article 11 of the Charter</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 11 of the Charter outlines the rights related to the freedom of expression and information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-87f4c2229943d3f8e84a9941f117b8b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018978</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="This Regulation">
  <data key="d0">This Regulation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">This Regulation refers to the legal frameworks and rules governing the imposition of administrative fines and penalties within the EU context.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-87f4c2229943d3f8e84a9941f117b8b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018978</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Criminal Penalty">
  <data key="d0">Criminal Penalty</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Criminal penalties are legal consequences set by national courts, which may be imposed instead of administrative fines in certain jurisdictions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-87f4c2229943d3f8e84a9941f117b8b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018978</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chair of the Board">
  <data key="d0">Chair of the Board</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Chair of the Board is responsible for informing members and the Commission about relevant information and decisions made by the Board.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-da5e0cbe02b415c14c47d962922ae943</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018978</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 65">
  <data key="d0">Article 65</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 65 outlines the procedures for dispute resolution by the Board, specifying the conditions under which binding decisions are adopted.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 65 provides further guidelines on the processes and implications of decision-making in data protection.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 65 discusses circumstances under which the European Data Protection Supervisor holds voting rights.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 65 mandates the issuance of binding decisions by the Board.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-da5e0cbe02b415c14c47d962922ae943&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51e09a8c8db52827f80f9874a8d4e4de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d95ad85f86f6e4a4771e8f92b0cbf27&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e09a4cc6243398f5e32d65a6312bd87</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018978</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Final Decision">
  <data key="d0">Final Decision</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Final Decision is an outcome of the supervisory authority's process, determined based on prior decisions and must be communicated to relevant parties.&lt;SEP&gt;The Final Decision refers to the ultimate ruling made by the Lead Supervisory Authority following the guidance of the Board's decision.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-da5e0cbe02b415c14c47d962922ae943&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51e09a8c8db52827f80f9874a8d4e4de</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018978</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European Data Protection Board">
  <data key="d0">European Data Protection Board</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Data Protection Board is established by regulation and can issue guidance on the processing of personal data.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Data Protection Board is a body established to ensure consistent application of data protection regulations across EU member states.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Data Protection Board was established by the regulation to ensure consistent application of data protection rules across the EU.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Data Protection Board is an agency that ensures the protection of personal data rights within the European Union.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Data Protection Board is involved in providing opinions on data protection matters related to the regulation of AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b303412f58783d3e4bc19dbad4e2a43c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51e09a8c8db52827f80f9874a8d4e4de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58a23170492ef728683ec4aa9e03ccb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b5a506beb14df3337a120faddb2f0b6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d055d5f99b33b0d67edb91e844c4185</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019215</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Automated Processing">
  <data key="d0">Automated Processing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Automated processing refers to the use of technology to process personal data without human intervention, which can produce significant effects on data subjects.&lt;SEP&gt;Automated Processing involves the use of technology to evaluate personal data without human intervention, leading to legal effects concerning the individual.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b303412f58783d3e4bc19dbad4e2a43c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0085cb3cc5d5dc4d434424e6dab722f3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018978</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Natural Persons">
  <data key="d0">Natural Persons</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Natural Persons refers to individual human beings who are recognized as entities with specific rights and responsibilities under legal frameworks. This term encompasses individuals whose personal information is collected, processed, and protected under various data protection laws. Natural Persons are entitled to safeguards regarding their personal data, particularly in the context of data protection regulations, such as those established under Union law. Their rights and freedoms are prioritized, ensuring that individuals are protected against risks such as identity theft and financial loss during data processing activities.

Natural Persons may be impacted by advanced technologies, particularly artificial intelligence (AI) systems. Their characteristics and biometric data can be utilized for categorization and identification, which raises concerns about bias and discrimination. Legal obligations surrounding the processing of their personal data emphasize their vulnerability, especially when interacting with authorities or when their data is subject to AI and law enforcement practices.

Furthermore, Natural Persons possess the ability to oversee the functionality of AI systems, making informed decisions about their operation while ensuring that transparency obligations are met. They are regarded as distinct legal entities, which allows them to apply for or receive public assistance, thus highlighting their position within societal and regulatory contexts.

In summary, Natural Persons embody the intersection of individual rights, data protection, and the implications of AI technology. They are integral to discussions about privacy, rights management, and the responsibilities entailed in handling personal data, reflecting a contemporary understanding of individual protections in both legal and technological domains.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e2d13a59890e903c4e56162458f272ab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3dec771ee61059f33dea3999f6d5facd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89bcf919dc1ff2d224ffc9b6e042a2c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ce3387b9f0e9256cf8b0a10e0726f37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d89a0536404e78829969b0f7fe895176&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd97dcdb68144953a81ad8ba7d8f52b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7071cdf0dedffd1eaf46713ebddb9b1e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0789b58f298ba801f3b269230a509b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97d77d4c79204175483320a1c612b93b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-35884c5ef57faf321ff9fce99bd2d970&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-499a505625518b0e48c48965f5a70336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4dfe3f1190ff8cf7dc9f62b85bed40a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9403aaca1e6e92e51844c1b1175b373b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-274264435e41f5d230030900b38f8c35&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df28c0bb060b598df163cc06bf49d0e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87ae75b9888750c7d94cfda6be4f3dac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c1a7de4ca41da4fd41e3254a6460114&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ad40e7a844b107cf5d24e2adca46bdb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62c64f05f2da893351ea92b9eac1c889&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3642f938e14bfed60a5d5b5fdc383e38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e47ed52d4514f1818e6c0687c1aa57e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c2fbe724dee488ea4e437995307241f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e20d35aae57ccfd5ec58ef7772f98c17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46bc64e87ac07d3576c10a8dd9d66d9e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-358eb1d0b0f35e665a7b23702159cfd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d44ed9cdcce8d29cd4cf7a4556478e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e64e0ad4efda4fc9f3a84823cb301955&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73e4afb71ddc31ffc854d861300d4eb6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d043d4edae3c59146709349b2875a92&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22dcb6c71a1828d1166aad9d5a7cac19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df495629e0a16630b58b47ba83c27efa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97987bc5b95dc5a6f6ebc189b5a394a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00803764d58d840979922e38d1dc555c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2378b7a291e44d534884f6b6e7eeb2a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab5bd61fedb2857e3db189c5f7bb8f94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ad4d08daad55de411fe1304fd990b8e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5772ed895bc8308d060b1975c2dd69d0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019187</data>
