</node>
<node id="Legal Obligation">
  <data key="d0">Legal Obligation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A legal obligation refers to a requirement imposed by law on data controllers regarding the processing of personal data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0085cb3cc5d5dc4d434424e6dab722f3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018981</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Legal Grounds">
  <data key="d0">Legal Grounds</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Legal grounds refer to the basis on which processing personal data is justified, including consent and contractual necessity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0085cb3cc5d5dc4d434424e6dab722f3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018981</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="The Board">
  <data key="d0">The Board</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Board is an entity responsible for making decisions, issuing guidelines, and maintaining public registers concerning data protection and compliance with regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e09a4cc6243398f5e32d65a6312bd87</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018981</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="The Council">
  <data key="d0">The Council</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Council is a governing body of the European Union that receives annual reports from the Board regarding data protection.&lt;SEP&gt;The Council, often referred to as the Council of the European Union, collaborates with the European Parliament on legislative matters and evaluations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e09a4cc6243398f5e32d65a6312bd87&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5f6ef3b354bb0dbf8af7b2c108fd236</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019209</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="The Commission">
  <data key="d0">The Commission</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Commission is the executive branch of the European Union that interacts with the Board concerning opinions, guidelines, and recommendations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Commission is responsible for adopting implementing acts, approving codes of practice, and classifying AI models with systemic risks.&lt;SEP&gt;The Commission is responsible for appointing members to the Advisory Forum and overseeing the implementation of AI regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Commission facilitates the exchange of experience between national competent authorities and oversees the creation of the EU database for high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;The Commission is responsible for adopting decisions related to infringements and communicating findings in accordance with regulations on AI models.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e09a4cc6243398f5e32d65a6312bd87&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-663826fe1821a9ef057cd84da3b741a8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37fb1095f63f925386014701386e5a4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bb17f83caa294ef6efb4f278d7d59fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5a5973b039f9a9af3e3e9d93b392c66</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019166</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Protection">
  <data key="d0">Data Protection</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Data protection is the practice of safeguarding personal data and ensuring regulatory compliance in transfers of data to third countries or international organizations.&lt;SEP&gt;Data protection refers to the principles, processes, and standards applied to protect personal information and regulate its processing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e09a4cc6243398f5e32d65a6312bd87&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4fb6b788c6bc23206d8cd996c5a6a6b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018981</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 12">
  <data key="d0">Article 12</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 12 details requirements regarding certain icons in data protection regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 12 refers to a specific article within the regulatory document concerning powers delegated to the Commission.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 12 outlines requirements for high-risk AI systems regarding record-keeping and monitoring of events.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 12 outlines the requirements for logging and interpretation of the outputs of high-risk AI systems to enable deployments to effectively manage and understand system logs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e09a4cc6243398f5e32d65a6312bd87&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58a23170492ef728683ec4aa9e03ccb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb73a01a1d9b0ba7ee87eb6d896fbea4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c2fbe724dee488ea4e437995307241f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019197</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Best Practices">
  <data key="d0">Best Practices</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Best practices in data protection refer to effective methods and documented procedures to ensure compliance with regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e09a4cc6243398f5e32d65a6312bd87</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018981</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 76">
  <data key="d0">Article 76</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 76 details provisions pertinent to the public availability of consultation results from the Board.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e09a4cc6243398f5e32d65a6312bd87</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018981</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Protection Rights">
  <data key="d0">Data Protection Rights</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Data protection rights refer to the legal rights of natural persons regarding the processing and protection of their personal data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e0789b58f298ba801f3b269230a509b8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018981</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Compliance Mechanisms">
  <data key="d0">Compliance Mechanisms</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Compliance mechanisms are processes designed to ensure that supervisory authorities adhere to legal standards in protecting data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e0789b58f298ba801f3b269230a509b8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018981</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Judicial Review">
  <data key="d0">Judicial Review</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Judicial review refers to the legal process whereby the actions of supervisory authorities can be examined by a court.&lt;SEP&gt;Judicial review is the process by which a supervisory authority’s actions may be examined in court, ensuring compliance with legal standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e0789b58f298ba801f3b269230a509b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af27fd67de6b968672bf93dbf11392ac</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018981</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Humanitarian Purposes">
  <data key="d0">Humanitarian Purposes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Humanitarian purposes refer to actions taken to aid individuals during crises, such as monitoring epidemics or responding to emergencies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2fa083a0dd77efdae774f798a1d2f060</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018982</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Natural Disasters">
  <data key="d0">Natural Disasters</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Natural disasters are catastrophic events caused by natural forces that lead to significant damage and humanitarian needs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2fa083a0dd77efdae774f798a1d2f060</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018982</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Man-Made Disasters">
  <data key="d0">Man-Made Disasters</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Man-made disasters result from human action or negligence and require urgent humanitarian responses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2fa083a0dd77efdae774f798a1d2f060</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018982</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Member State Law">
  <data key="d0">Member State Law</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Member State Law refers to the national laws enacted by individual countries within the European Union (EU) that govern various aspects of personal data processing. These laws can impose additional conditions and specifics on how personal data is handled, supplementing the overarching regulations set forth by the Union. Member State Law is not limited to data protection but also encompasses legislation regarding judicial proceedings and public access to documents, highlighting the breadth of legal frameworks present in each member state.

Each EU member state is responsible for enacting its own laws and regulations, which must comply with Union law while allowing for specific local adjustments and derogations concerning data subject rights. This legal framework ensures that while there is consistency across the EU in terms of data protection, individual countries have the latitude to tailor certain provisions to better fit their national contexts. 

Member State Law thus plays a critical role in the interplay between EU-wide regulations and national sovereignty, balancing the need for harmonized data protection standards with local legal traditions and requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ce3387b9f0e9256cf8b0a10e0726f37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b303412f58783d3e4bc19dbad4e2a43c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0ab083807b5f91410241f4f574d25b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b661d0b109eaf570a61ae0d0ca8020b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8ea5b2826564cb4f4f5c8c193fab368&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc7a45c7f8eea9ab9297b5839c19c2a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5bb48441e5e8722f7d89d485c663d88&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62b277bc6fa564a434a6c338a48eea46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fa893844a2197c46302e74437f2bbef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2016931a6e14615018d3d7f8304b6a1e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0ea41c30759ecd048ab40483ec1605b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae28521738df7feadad1be4821afc294</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018982</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Processing">
  <data key="d0">Data Processing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Data processing involves handling personal data with respect to specific legal bases, including consent, legitimate interests, or public authority.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2fa083a0dd77efdae774f798a1d2f060</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018982</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Public Authorities">
  <data key="d0">Public Authorities</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Public authorities are governmental bodies that receive personal data for official missions, such as tax and customs authorities.&lt;SEP&gt;Public authorities are governmental entities responsible for the implementation and enforcement of laws and regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Public Authorities are government bodies that handle specific responsibilities and are involved in the processing of personal data in the public interest.&lt;SEP&gt;Public authorities of a third country are entities that may be excluded from the Regulation when engaging in international cooperation.&lt;SEP&gt;Public authorities are government entities that may deploy high-risk AI systems and must comply with registration obligations.&lt;SEP&gt;Public authorities are government bodies responsible for providing essential public services and benefits to natural persons.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2fa083a0dd77efdae774f798a1d2f060&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e52d9f505adab3ccf36c6979ad3a7d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4dfe3f1190ff8cf7dc9f62b85bed40a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a13415ed2c222ba72d78fdab855a6ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d44ed9cdcce8d29cd4cf7a4556478e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3725d0d03194d1c923cc1275d5433c2a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5af0747da2a9f2783a1bde010a13814</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019207</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Client">
  <data key="d0">Client</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Clients are individuals or entities receiving services from a controller and may have their personal data processed under legitimate interests.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2fa083a0dd77efdae774f798a1d2f060</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018982</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Union Law">
  <data key="d0">Union Law</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Union Law is the comprehensive legal framework established by the European Union (EU), regulating key areas such as personal data protection, individual privacy rights, and the governance of artificial intelligence (AI) systems across its member states. It comprises a set of legal regulations and directives that dictate how personal data can be processed lawfully, outlining the responsibilities of data controllers and processors along with the rights of individuals. This framework is crucial for maintaining a consistent level of data protection and privacy within the EU.

Specifically, Union Law mandates the conditions under which personal data may be processed, ensuring compliance with established regulations across all member states. It plays a pivotal role in outlining the standards for handling personal data, as well as dictating the terms for the transfer of such data outside the EU, thereby reinforcing the overall data protection and privacy measures within the region.

Beyond personal data protection, Union Law also governs the use of AI systems, establishing regulations that specifically address the deployment and management of high-risk AI technologies. These provisions include requirements and protocols intended to ensure safety and ethical considerations in AI development and implementation. Moreover, Union Law encompasses legal regulations concerning various rights and obligations of individuals and organizations, reflecting the EU's commitment to protecting fundamental rights while also regulating the operations of member states.

In summary, Union Law serves as a vital component of the EU's legal architecture, aiming to harmonize legal standards across its member countries in matters of privacy, data protection, and the ethical deployment of AI, thus influencing both private and public sectors extensively.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ce3387b9f0e9256cf8b0a10e0726f37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b303412f58783d3e4bc19dbad4e2a43c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0ab083807b5f91410241f4f574d25b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b661d0b109eaf570a61ae0d0ca8020b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8ea5b2826564cb4f4f5c8c193fab368&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc7a45c7f8eea9ab9297b5839c19c2a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62b277bc6fa564a434a6c338a48eea46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fa893844a2197c46302e74437f2bbef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca37d7dbc74be645fc1de3e6e772a586&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2016931a6e14615018d3d7f8304b6a1e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae28521738df7feadad1be4821afc294&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b3266fc2be81fd61dcffc1afc41700b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4b86ca29202de00c1292db00c1efa4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3642f938e14bfed60a5d5b5fdc383e38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80e46c2caec4056bbc2d3b305e3ed190&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e87d6d03ced0c44c2805ed7127eb0258&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92f9c6220442ff06dfe6fe52499f18aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e99d990c855f3b544868eeee8a6b049b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e20d35aae57ccfd5ec58ef7772f98c17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b5a506beb14df3337a120faddb2f0b6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74667d89df5ee6111b7743e86ee4744f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-061f3c307dd55152ffbb5bdfae17ea90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ad4d08daad55de411fe1304fd990b8e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f40b01fb5e1dbaa442b55c31285ecb50</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019178</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Network Security">
  <data key="d0">Network Security</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Network security encompasses measures and protocols used to protect data and networks from unauthorized access or attacks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2fa083a0dd77efdae774f798a1d2f060</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018982</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Electronic Communications Networks">
  <data key="d0">Electronic Communications Networks</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Electronic communications networks provide the infrastructure necessary for transmitting data and facilitating communications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2fa083a0dd77efdae774f798a1d2f060</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018982</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Legal Basis">
  <data key="d0">Legal Basis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Legal basis refers to the justification for processing personal data, ensuring compliance with data protection regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2fa083a0dd77efdae774f798a1d2f060</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018982</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Controller">
  <data key="d0">Data Controller</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The data controller is the entity that determines the purposes and means of processing personal data and has legal responsibilities regarding it.&lt;SEP&gt;A data controller is an entity that determines the purposes and means of processing personal data.&lt;SEP&gt;A Data Controller is an individual or entity that determines the purposes and means of processing personal data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2fa083a0dd77efdae774f798a1d2f060&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97d77d4c79204175483320a1c612b93b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fa893844a2197c46302e74437f2bbef</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018982</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Third Party">
  <data key="d0">Third Party</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A third party is an individual or organization that is not the data subject or the data controller but may receive access to the personal data.&lt;SEP&gt;A third party is an entity other than the data subject, controller, processor, and authorized individuals under the authority of the controller.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2fa083a0dd77efdae774f798a1d2f060&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e5e9be572ec001588771fa74ce45258</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018982</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Complaints">
  <data key="d0">Complaints</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Complaints are grievances lodged by data subjects in relation to the processing of their personal data that supervisory authorities are responsible for handling.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-66ded376bcd1c12c425bce88cfd552a0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018982</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chair">
  <data key="d0">Chair</data>
  <data key="d1">position</data>
  <data key="d2">The Chair is responsible for convening meetings, preparing agendas, and notifying decisions to supervisory authorities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-36a1ea945634c046899535f1e8f39a77</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018982</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deputy Chairs">
  <data key="d0">Deputy Chairs</data>
  <data key="d1">position</data>
  <data key="d2">The Deputy Chairs assist the Chair in their duties and have a term of office that is renewable.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-36a1ea945634c046899535f1e8f39a77</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018982</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Memorandum of Understanding">
  <data key="d0">Memorandum of Understanding</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The Memorandum of Understanding governs collaboration and operational tasks between the Board and the European Data Protection Supervisor.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-36a1ea945634c046899535f1e8f39a77</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Tasks of the Chair">
  <data key="d0">Tasks of the Chair</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Tasks of the Chair refer to the responsibilities assigned to the Chair of the Board, including convening meetings and preparing agendas.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-36a1ea945634c046899535f1e8f39a77</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Confidentiality">
  <data key="d0">Confidentiality</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Confidentiality refers to the requirement for Board discussions to remain confidential as deemed necessary.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-36a1ea945634c046899535f1e8f39a77</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EC) No 1049/2001">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EC) No 1049/2001</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EC) No 1049/2001 governs access to documents submitted to Board members and other authorities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-36a1ea945634c046899535f1e8f39a77</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Technical Measures">
  <data key="d0">Technical Measures</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Technical measures are safeguards implemented by processors to ensure appropriate handling and processing of personal data as required by regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;Technical measures are actions taken to ensure the accuracy, robustness, and cybersecurity of high-risk AI systems throughout their lifecycle.&lt;SEP&gt;Technical Measures are actions taken to facilitate the interpretation of AI outputs by deployers, as outlined in Article 13(3).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0ab083807b5f91410241f4f574d25b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e20d35aae57ccfd5ec58ef7772f98c17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-561d345a761ead6d6e1bfabd0f89e09c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019200</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Organisational Measures">
  <data key="d0">Organisational Measures</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Organisational measures refer to policies and procedures that processors must adopt to manage and protect personal data appropriately.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0ab083807b5f91410241f4f574d25b8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EC) No 1338/2008">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EC) No 1338/2008</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EC) No 1338/2008 defines legal frameworks concerning community statistics on public health and health and safety at work.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EC) No 1338/2008 addresses Community statistics on public health and health and safety at work, issued by the European Parliament and Council.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9bfe3c72af8b2bd319fe191920f25097&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97d77d4c79204175483320a1c612b93b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Health Data">
  <data key="d0">Health Data</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Health data encompasses information about an individual's physical or mental health status collected during healthcare services.&lt;SEP&gt;Health data include information relevant to individual health and social care services, necessitating careful handling.&lt;SEP&gt;Health data pertains to personal data that includes information about an individual's health status or medical history, which must be managed according to data protection principles.&lt;SEP&gt;Health data consists of information relevant to the health of individuals, which is used for training AI systems in healthcare.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9bfe3c72af8b2bd319fe191920f25097&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc7a45c7f8eea9ab9297b5839c19c2a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4dfe3f1190ff8cf7dc9f62b85bed40a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-234952a50b5a02b1afedbe8d8e1c076b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019199</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="OJ L 354, 31.12.2008, p. 70">
  <data key="d0">OJ L 354, 31.12.2008, p. 70</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">OJ L 354, 31.12.2008, p. 70 refers to the official journal entry relevant to Regulation (EC) No 1338/2008 detailing public health statistics.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9bfe3c72af8b2bd319fe191920f25097</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="One-Stop-Shop Mechanism">
  <data key="d0">One-Stop-Shop Mechanism</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The One-Stop-Shop Mechanism allows for a single Supervisory Authority to handle data processing cases that involve multiple Member States, streamlining compliance processes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1e52d9f505adab3ccf36c6979ad3a7d0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Private Bodies">
  <data key="d0">Private Bodies</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Private Bodies are non-governmental organizations or businesses that process personal data and may serve the public interest.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1e52d9f505adab3ccf36c6979ad3a7d0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Corrective Powers">
  <data key="d0">Corrective Powers</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Corrective Powers refer to the authorities granted to Supervisory Authorities to take action against violations of data protection regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1e52d9f505adab3ccf36c6979ad3a7d0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sanctions">
  <data key="d0">Sanctions</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Sanctions are penalties that can be imposed by Supervisory Authorities on organizations that fail to comply with data protection regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1e52d9f505adab3ccf36c6979ad3a7d0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Legal Proceedings">
  <data key="d0">Legal Proceedings</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Legal Proceedings involve the actions taken by supervisory authorities to address violations of data protection regulations through judicial systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1e52d9f505adab3ccf36c6979ad3a7d0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Investigatory Powers">
  <data key="d0">Investigatory Powers</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Investigatory Powers are the powers granted to Supervisory Authorities to investigate potential violations of data protection laws.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1e52d9f505adab3ccf36c6979ad3a7d0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Not-for-Profit Body">
  <data key="d0">Not-for-Profit Body</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Not-for-Profit Body is an organization that may represent Data Subjects' interests in compliance with data protection laws.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5f087b1b4f7f6e16afe33b8014a5f30c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Right to Erasure">
  <data key="d0">Right to Erasure</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The right to erasure allows a data subject to request the deletion of their personal data under certain conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;The Right to Erasure, also known as the right to be forgotten, allows the data subject to request the deletion of their personal data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5b661d0b109eaf570a61ae0d0ca8020b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca37d7dbc74be645fc1de3e6e772a586</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Right to be Forgotten">
  <data key="d0">Right to be Forgotten</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The right to be forgotten is an extension of privacy rights that allows individuals to have their personal data deleted in specific contexts.&lt;SEP&gt;The Right to be Forgotten allows the data subject to request the erasure of their personal data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5b661d0b109eaf570a61ae0d0ca8020b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca37d7dbc74be645fc1de3e6e772a586</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intellectual Property">
  <data key="d0">Intellectual Property</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Intellectual property refers to creations of the mind, like trade secrets and copyrights, which are protected by law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5b661d0b109eaf570a61ae0d0ca8020b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Online Environment">
  <data key="d0">Online Environment</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The online environment refers to digital spaces where personal data is shared and processed, often raising privacy concerns.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5b661d0b109eaf570a61ae0d0ca8020b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Consistent Application">
  <data key="d0">Consistent Application</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Consistent Application pertains to the uniform enforcement and interpretation of regulations across different Member States.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3bbf8c83dfe1a6df2d3a3d01645abe8f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Awareness-Raising Activities">
  <data key="d0">Awareness-Raising Activities</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Awareness-Raising Activities encompass initiatives by supervisory authorities to inform and educate the public and businesses about regulatory obligations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3bbf8c83dfe1a6df2d3a3d01645abe8f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Complaint">
  <data key="d0">Complaint</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Complaint is an assertion made by a data subject or other parties regarding possible infringements of data protection regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3bbf8c83dfe1a6df2d3a3d01645abe8f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 79">
  <data key="d0">Article 79</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 79 allows for the lodging of complaints by data subjects to supervisory authorities as a means to seek redress.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 79 refers to a specific provision in the Regulation that outlines the jurisdiction for bringing court proceedings related to data protection.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 79 defines the criteria for determining when a high-risk AI system may present a risk and outlines the related obligations for deployers.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 79 details the procedure for dealing with AI systems that present risks, including evaluations and compliance requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 79 discusses compliance measures and the procedures for addressing non-compliance of AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 79 addresses notifications regarding market measures and their compliance with regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbc89674e06d04462cc498a8c1da1d44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c22927198decad5ee173ab2f05d62983&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-088a4c3c3c775d33baa63868a127c869&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a54b012266e9b9c7302fce6d400f583&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38cdce9b64b40ba40d6acb529d375787&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a13415ed2c222ba72d78fdab855a6ca</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019192</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Paragraph 2">
  <data key="d0">Paragraph 2</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Paragraph 2 specifies conditions under which controllers and processors may be exempt from liability for damages caused by processing.&lt;SEP&gt;Paragraph 2 outlines provisions for Member States regarding exemptions and derogations related to specific processing situations for journalistic and academic purposes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbc89674e06d04462cc498a8c1da1d44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d44a5f83cf273e81899482e995be2a98</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Paragraph 4">
  <data key="d0">Paragraph 4</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Paragraph 4 discusses the conditions under which a controller or processor may recover compensation from other controllers or processors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbc89674e06d04462cc498a8c1da1d44</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Records of Processing Activities">
  <data key="d0">Records of Processing Activities</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Records of Processing Activities are documents that each controller must maintain to track and detail processing activities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-db7bcd6a42a9c26ced1d71444d109dff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Technical and Organisational Measures">
  <data key="d0">Technical and Organisational Measures</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Technical and organisational measures are strategies implemented to ensure the minimization of personal data processing in alignment with proportionality and necessity principles.&lt;SEP&gt;Technical and Organisational Measures refer to strategies implemented to ensure compliance with processing regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Technical and Organisational Measures refer to actions and controls implemented by processors to ensure data protection.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-db7bcd6a42a9c26ced1d71444d109dff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fa893844a2197c46302e74437f2bbef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ce0488d21ac5956f37974d7ae0799b4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Standard Contractual Clauses">
  <data key="d0">Standard Contractual Clauses</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Standard Contractual Clauses refer to predefined legal terms that help ensure consistency and protection when processing personal data across borders.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-db7bcd6a42a9c26ced1d71444d109dff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Certification Mechanism">
  <data key="d0">Certification Mechanism</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Certification Mechanism refers to a system that validates and verifies compliance with data protection standards.&lt;SEP&gt;The Certification Mechanism is a process aimed at establishing data protection certification and ensuring compliance with regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Certification Mechanism refers to the system through which data controllers or processors can achieve certification by meeting specific criteria.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-db7bcd6a42a9c26ced1d71444d109dff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fb6a4af737980e04056c2522ea213fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-39551a1dbe3cdde38b22607932e0688f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Administrative Fine">
  <data key="d0">Administrative Fine</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An administrative fine is a penalty that may be imposed for infringing provisions of regulation, with specified limits based on severity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-224ac909847d6dc3f9484ef626d8ecd2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Subjects' Rights">
  <data key="d0">Data Subjects' Rights</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Data subjects' rights are the legal rights afforded to individuals regarding their personal data as mentioned in the regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-224ac909847d6dc3f9484ef626d8ecd2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Monitoring Body">
  <data key="d0">Monitoring Body</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The monitoring body oversees compliance with the regulation and is mentioned in connection with obligations related to personal data processing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-224ac909847d6dc3f9484ef626d8ecd2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sensitive Personal Data">
  <data key="d0">Sensitive Personal Data</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Sensitive personal data includes particularly sensitive information that merits specific protection due to its relation to fundamental rights and freedoms.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4816e09d93a70dec7bd3be2be787d180</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Not-for-Profit Organization">
  <data key="d0">Not-for-Profit Organization</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">A not-for-profit organization can act on behalf of data subjects to lodge complaints regarding data protection rights.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-af27fd67de6b968672bf93dbf11392ac</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Court of Justice">
  <data key="d0">Court of Justice</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Court of Justice is an institution where appeals against decisions by supervisory authorities can be made based on specific legal criteria.&lt;SEP&gt;The Court of Justice is an institution that provides preliminary rulings on the interpretation of Union law, including judicial remedies related to regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-af27fd67de6b968672bf93dbf11392ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f500418ca711a20a360004da8c1f5ff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Annulment">
  <data key="d0">Annulment</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Annulment is a legal action that can be taken to revoke decisions made by a supervisory authority.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-af27fd67de6b968672bf93dbf11392ac</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Directive">
  <data key="d0">Directive</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A directive is a formal recommendation or instruction issued to guide the implementation of specific legal standards or policies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-af27fd67de6b968672bf93dbf11392ac</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Paragraph 1">
  <data key="d0">Paragraph 1</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Paragraph 1 refers to the initial provisions that Member States must notify to the Commission by a specified date.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d44a5f83cf273e81899482e995be2a98</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 85">
  <data key="d0">Article 85</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 85 addresses the reconciliation of the right to personal data protection with freedom of expression and information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d44a5f83cf273e81899482e995be2a98</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 86">
  <data key="d0">Article 86</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 86 outlines the processing of personal data in official documents held by public authorities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d44a5f83cf273e81899482e995be2a98</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018984</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 87">
  <data key="d0">Article 87</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 87 pertains to the conditions for processing national identification numbers and general application identifiers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d44a5f83cf273e81899482e995be2a98</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018985</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 88">
  <data key="d0">Article 88</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 88 discusses specific rules for protecting employees' personal data in the context of employment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d44a5f83cf273e81899482e995be2a98</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018985</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 89">
  <data key="d0">Article 89</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 89 relates to safeguards and derogations for processing personal data for archiving and research purposes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d44a5f83cf273e81899482e995be2a98</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018985</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Law">
  <data key="d0">Law</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Law refers to the legal framework that governs the protection of personal data and the rights of individuals regarding data processing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d44a5f83cf273e81899482e995be2a98</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018985</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Paragraph 3">
  <data key="d0">Paragraph 3</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Paragraph 3 requires Member States to notify the Commission about their adopted laws following the specifications outlined in the previous paragraphs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d44a5f83cf273e81899482e995be2a98</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018985</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="National Court">
  <data key="d0">National Court</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">A national court is a judicial body in a Member State that can request the Court of Justice for a preliminary ruling on the interpretation of Union law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5f500418ca711a20a360004da8c1f5ff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018985</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Supervisor Authority">
  <data key="d0">Supervisor Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">A supervisory authority is an independent public authority responsible for monitoring compliance with data protection laws.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5f500418ca711a20a360004da8c1f5ff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018985</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Plaintiff">
  <data key="d0">Plaintiff</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A plaintiff is a person who brings a legal action against another party in a court.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5f500418ca711a20a360004da8c1f5ff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018985</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 267 TFEU">
  <data key="d0">Article 267 TFEU</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 267 TFEU refers to a provision in the Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union that allows national courts to refer questions to the Court of Justice for preliminary rulings.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5f500418ca711a20a360004da8c1f5ff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018985</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 263 TFEU">
  <data key="d0">Article 263 TFEU</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 263 TFEU provides for the annulment of acts of the Union or its institutions by individuals who are directly and individually concerned.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5f500418ca711a20a360004da8c1f5ff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018985</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Churches and Religious Associations">
  <data key="d0">Churches and Religious Associations</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Churches and religious associations are recognized entities in Member States that have specific status under existing constitutional laws.&lt;SEP&gt;Churches and Religious Associations are groups that may have specific rules for data protection, relevant in the context of personal data processing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a8ea5b2826564cb4f4f5c8c193fab368&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87ae75b9888750c7d94cfda6be4f3dac</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018985</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Independent Supervisory Authority">
  <data key="d0">Independent Supervisory Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">An Independent Supervisory Authority oversees compliance with data protection regulations, ensuring adherence to established guidelines.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a8ea5b2826564cb4f4f5c8c193fab368</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018985</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 90">
  <data key="d0">Article 90</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 90 outlines the obligations related to secrecy and the powers of supervisory authorities under the Regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a8ea5b2826564cb4f4f5c8c193fab368</data>
