<node id="Public Interest">
  <data key="d0">Public Interest</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Public Interest refers to the concept that encompasses the welfare or well-being of the general public, particularly in contexts where it may necessitate the processing of personal data for the benefit of the community. This principle is particularly significant in areas such as public health, where the processing of personal data can be justified even without consent from the data subject when it serves the public good.

The notion of Public Interest emphasizes the necessity of utilizing personal data to achieve societal benefits, including but not limited to health initiatives, research, and archival purposes. Such justifications for data processing highlight the broader societal concerns that can validate certain data transfers, especially in legal or regulatory contexts. 

Public Interest serves as a rationale for processing personal data that aligns with significant societal interests, allowing for responsible management of data under specific conditions. This multifaceted concept plays a crucial role in balancing individual privacy rights against the collective needs of society, addressing situations where societal benefits may outweigh the need for individual consent or privacy.&lt;SEP&gt;Public interest refers to the welfare or well-being of the general public that influences regulations and practices concerning AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fe63429efbb90ae6ec22b62b5d79e7b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4816e09d93a70dec7bd3be2be787d180&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc7a45c7f8eea9ab9297b5839c19c2a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62b277bc6fa564a434a6c338a48eea46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97d77d4c79204175483320a1c612b93b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae28521738df7feadad1be4821afc294&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ce0488d21ac5956f37974d7ae0799b4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b3266fc2be81fd61dcffc1afc41700b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a169417b09f70fa2792a3c9ce82a678d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019216</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Legal Claims">
  <data key="d0">Legal Claims</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Legal claims refer to actions taken to assert a legal right, where processing personal data may be necessary.&lt;SEP&gt;Legal claims involve the establishment, exercise, or defense of rights recognized by law, often necessitating the processing of personal data in court settings.&lt;SEP&gt;Legal Claims indicate the necessity for data transfer to support the establishment, exercise, or defense of legal rights.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cc7a45c7f8eea9ab9297b5839c19c2a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40ecaa725d6d1bc748899703ed8b84dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b3266fc2be81fd61dcffc1afc41700b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018985</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Genetic Data">
  <data key="d0">Genetic Data</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Genetic data refers to personal data relating to hereditary characteristics derived from biological samples.&lt;SEP&gt;Genetic Data pertains to information regarding an individual's genetic characteristics and requires special protections during processing.&lt;SEP&gt;Genetic data refers to personal data related to the inherited or acquired genetic characteristics of a natural person.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cc7a45c7f8eea9ab9297b5839c19c2a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4dfe3f1190ff8cf7dc9f62b85bed40a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e5e9be572ec001588771fa74ce45258</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018985</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Full And Effective Compensation">
  <data key="d0">Full And Effective Compensation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Full and effective compensation refers to the obligation to provide complete restitution for damages suffered by data subjects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b5bb48441e5e8722f7d89d485c663d88</data>
