<node id="Natural Person">
  <data key="d0">Natural Person</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A natural person is an individual human being identified for various purposes, including health-related matters.&lt;SEP&gt;A natural person refers to an individual human being who can be held liable under data protection regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;A natural person is a human being whose identity can be recognized by certain attributes including physical, physiological, genetic, mental, economic, cultural, or social factors.&lt;SEP&gt;Natural Person refers to an individual human being whose biological and personal data are subject to processing under regulatory frameworks.&lt;SEP&gt;A natural person refers to an individual human being as opposed to a legal entity or organization in the context of legal obligations regarding AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b5bb48441e5e8722f7d89d485c663d88&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3626adc7cf865bec83f6479c1e08cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1184185c4bc8012fe969516fa45f07b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e5e9be572ec001588771fa74ce45258&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51c94d77f328c85a261162f4664235f6</data>
