</node>
<node id="Regulation (EC) No 765/2008">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EC) No 765/2008</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EC) No 765/2008 sets the requirements for accreditation and market surveillance related to the marketing of products.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EC) No 765/2008 establishes requirements for accreditation and repeals previous regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EC) No 765/2008 establishes the requirements for market surveillance and the compliance of products within the European Union.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EC) No 765/2008 outlines the general principles for CE marking conformity in the EU.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39551a1dbe3cdde38b22607932e0688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fe225f6b6c5b43aceb1fd1109bf8e4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc7122206f7a3097526258a05d85baef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74667d89df5ee6111b7743e86ee4744f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019216</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Protection Seals">
  <data key="d0">Data Protection Seals</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Data Protection Seals are indicators of compliance with data protection standards and are established under the authority of the Board.&lt;SEP&gt;Data protection seals are indicators that signify compliance with data protection regulations and are to be recognized and promoted as part of the certification mechanisms.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39551a1dbe3cdde38b22607932e0688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4fb6b788c6bc23206d8cd996c5a6a6b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773018990</data>
