</node>
<node id="Sandbox Plan">
  <data key="d0">Sandbox Plan</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A sandbox plan details the objectives and conditions established for testing innovative AI systems within a regulatory framework.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f4b86ca29202de00c1292db00c1efa4b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019172</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI Regulatory Sandbox">
  <data key="d0">AI Regulatory Sandbox</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">AI regulatory sandbox is a controlled environment established to enable the development and testing of innovative AI systems while ensuring regulatory compliance.&lt;SEP&gt;The AI Regulatory Sandbox is a controlled environment established by national competent authorities to facilitate the development and testing of AI systems under regulatory oversight.&lt;SEP&gt;The AI Regulatory Sandbox is a controlled environment for testing high-risk AI systems under regulated conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;An AI regulatory sandbox is a controlled framework that allows for the development and testing of AI systems under regulatory oversight.&lt;SEP&gt;AI regulatory sandboxes are controlled environments established to foster innovation and facilitate the testing and validation of AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;The AI Regulatory Sandbox is a framework designed for testing AI systems while ensuring compliance with legal and ethical standards.&lt;SEP&gt;The AI Regulatory Sandbox is a controlled environment where AI systems can be tested under supervision to ensure they meet regulatory standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f4b86ca29202de00c1292db00c1efa4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5af0747da2a9f2783a1bde010a13814&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a169417b09f70fa2792a3c9ce82a678d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7aba082da5b9f8ab2defc1a7a725bef0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5da5d9be8aadcb05915f4a8f8f5aa33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f743aee05d8e1afc03000436802a1ad2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e0d95f75393cb87bb510dfcf3ba0ef5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019172</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI Literacy">
  <data key="d0">AI Literacy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">AI Literacy encompasses the knowledge and skills necessary to understand and make informed decisions regarding the use and implications of AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;AI literacy represents the skills and knowledge needed to understand AI systems and their implications for deployment.&lt;SEP&gt;AI Literacy refers to the measures that providers and deployers of AI systems must take to ensure sufficient understanding and knowledge of AI among their staff and users.&lt;SEP&gt;AI literacy refers to knowledge and understanding of AI systems, particularly important for those involved in their development and operation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f4b86ca29202de00c1292db00c1efa4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f379f07f844b3112cd145a56e02874b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b75f7d42df244a78773a748afb4f421f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97987bc5b95dc5a6f6ebc189b5a394a1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019172</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Testing in Real-World Conditions">
  <data key="d0">Testing in Real-World Conditions</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Testing in real-world conditions refers to the practice of evaluating AI systems outside of laboratory settings to assess compliance with regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f4b86ca29202de00c1292db00c1efa4b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019172</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Subject">
  <data key="d0">Subject</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A subject is a natural person who participates in testing aimed at evaluating AI systems in real-world conditions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f4b86ca29202de00c1292db00c1efa4b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019172</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Informed Consent">
  <data key="d0">Informed Consent</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Informed consent denotes a subject's voluntary agreement to participate in testing, having been fully informed of its implications.&lt;SEP&gt;Informed consent is the agreement of subjects to participate in testing, based on understanding the risks and objectives involved.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f4b86ca29202de00c1292db00c1efa4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caf8819d467d1204dd768c10cacdbf06</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019172</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deep Fake">
  <data key="d0">Deep Fake</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A deep fake is AI-generated content that mimics real personas or objects, potentially misleading viewers about its authenticity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f4b86ca29202de00c1292db00c1efa4b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019172</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Widespread Infringement">
  <data key="d0">Widespread Infringement</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Widespread infringement refers to violations of Union laws that may harm collective interests of individuals across multiple Member States.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f4b86ca29202de00c1292db00c1efa4b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019172</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Post-Market Monitoring">
  <data key="d0">Post-Market Monitoring</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Post-Market Monitoring refers to the ongoing analysis of AI systems after they have been deployed, focusing on interactions with other AI systems and ensuring compliance with regulatory requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f763b444522d2da4e393e2f999f53812</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019173</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Annex IV">
  <data key="d0">Annex IV</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Annex IV contains specified elements required for the technical documentation of high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Annex IV is a part of regulatory documentation that discusses technical procedures related to post-market monitoring plans for high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Annex IV specifies the technical documentation requirements for certain High-Risk AI Systems that must be maintained by law enforcement and other authorities.&lt;SEP&gt;Annex IV contains specific requirements and details that must be included in the technical documentation for the AI System.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f763b444522d2da4e393e2f999f53812&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80e46c2caec4056bbc2d3b305e3ed190&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd94ba8542b0c8ff4b050fc6027f5237&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-741b1675a971d075b2d3571148530b89</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019173</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Union Harmonisation Legislation">
  <data key="d0">Union Harmonisation Legislation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Union harmonisation legislation includes regulations that establish common standards for the safety and compliance of products in the EU market.&lt;SEP&gt;Union harmonisation legislation refers to legal acts that govern product compliance and technical standards in the market.&lt;SEP&gt;A set of laws that standardize requirements for products within the Union, relevant to high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Union harmonisation legislation refers to the set of laws and guidelines within the European Union that regulate the compliance of products and systems, including high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Union Harmonisation Legislation outlines regulatory standards for high-risk AI systems within the European Union, including requirements for post-market monitoring.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f763b444522d2da4e393e2f999f53812&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb73a01a1d9b0ba7ee87eb6d896fbea4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea757da73e875c6fedacdd166bb91c2e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-474ee56c196aef9638f343ef09589bca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf7d18a6020405fb3429834a129e7cd0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019173</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Market">
  <data key="d0">Market</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Market refers to the environment where high-risk AI systems are deployed and monitored, governed by relevant legislation and regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f763b444522d2da4e393e2f999f53812</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019173</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High-Risk AI Systems">
  <data key="d0">High-Risk AI Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">High-Risk AI Systems represent a category of artificial intelligence technologies that are identified as posing significant risks to individuals' rights, safety, and fundamental freedoms. Due to their potential impact, these systems are subject to stricter regulatory oversight and compliance measures. The necessity for careful design, implementation, and monitoring stems from their involvement in critical applications such as healthcare, law enforcement, and biometrics, where their misuse or failure could lead to severe repercussions.

These systems are classified under regulations that demand rigorous adherence to legal and technical standards, including transparency and documentation requirements. High-Risk AI Systems must undergo thorough conformity assessments to ensure safety and regulatory compliance throughout their lifecycle. This includes registration within designated databases, adherence to cybersecurity requirements, and compliance with specific obligations outlined by regulatory frameworks.

Moreover, High-Risk AI Systems necessitate ongoing scrutiny, often requiring testing in real-world conditions to validate their safety and efficacy. The landscape of these systems is continually shaped by evolving legislation aimed at safeguarding health and safety, which directly influences their development and deployment in society. Overall, the classification and regulation of High-Risk AI Systems reflect a proactive approach to mitigating risks associated with advanced technologies in various sectors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-663826fe1821a9ef057cd84da3b741a8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f763b444522d2da4e393e2f999f53812&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80a99ad850f0546ea9da41c8d764b154&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a242b3e1d633e7e955057a9b078f32d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5af0747da2a9f2783a1bde010a13814&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3642f938e14bfed60a5d5b5fdc383e38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6089fa3fb8ca9e6804e31c89a758b4ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e87d6d03ced0c44c2805ed7127eb0258&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92f9c6220442ff06dfe6fe52499f18aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb73a01a1d9b0ba7ee87eb6d896fbea4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e20d35aae57ccfd5ec58ef7772f98c17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8b33cb346ddcf954cb3e193a006d6add&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46bc64e87ac07d3576c10a8dd9d66d9e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51749b7ff68c3ff9e52c0d29dfb02772&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfdd4a90d27a0fa7cfe5caacb375335c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-474ee56c196aef9638f343ef09589bca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-358eb1d0b0f35e665a7b23702159cfd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78ea54ae6ffd2850256fb7ad037b8474&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6507d56efb6357f20f57227d44b681ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-971ebc9330032c79166b56276164406c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0714fdb65a0577bc4493dcb81d0a915&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4086e5336bfe9061f6ae69821c67e4ab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfb1222254442ec5ae96316c08a386f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24db102847abeef12e1042f8de042ea9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73e4afb71ddc31ffc854d861300d4eb6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d2a58a86edb7bec623750da3d232aa2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fe225f6b6c5b43aceb1fd1109bf8e4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d043d4edae3c59146709349b2875a92&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df0cf5bee4370453cb38606bad89b764&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3725d0d03194d1c923cc1275d5433c2a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f40b01fb5e1dbaa442b55c31285ecb50&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4996cfa66f0668d565cd83bbe46dd21a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eced97c6a138205573883808dbd74066&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caf8819d467d1204dd768c10cacdbf06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d055d5f99b33b0d67edb91e844c4185&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55fa705f95ec5acec79f8b691041b65c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77f7e4da7918161a180fb26c5a1704ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5772ed895bc8308d060b1975c2dd69d0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019173</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Annex III">
  <data key="d0">Annex III</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Annex III is a crucial component of the regulatory framework governing artificial intelligence (AI) systems, specifically focusing on those considered high-risk. It delineates various AI systems that meet specific conditions and outlines the necessary oversight and assessment requirements mandated for these systems. 

Within Annex III, a comprehensive list of high-risk AI use cases is provided, necessitating thorough assessments and ongoing evaluations to ensure compliance with the established standards. This includes detailed information regarding the conformity assessment procedures that these AI systems must undergo prior to market placement or service entry. The annex specifies that certain high-risk AI systems require registration and outlines the specific criteria needed for their oversight and verification by natural persons.

Moreover, Annex III identifies distinct categories of high-risk AI systems that are subject to rigorous testing standards and emphasizes the importance of conformity assessments equipped with defined measures. It stipulates the need for particular points related to these assessment processes, ensuring that all high-risk AI systems are covered comprehensively under the relevant regulations. Additionally, Annex III indicates that all identified high-risk AI systems will be included in the EU database, reinforcing transparency and accountability in AI deployment.

Overall, Annex III articulates a structured approach to managing high-risk AI systems, providing essential guidelines and expectations necessary for ensuring their safe and ethical integration into the market.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-663826fe1821a9ef057cd84da3b741a8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80a99ad850f0546ea9da41c8d764b154&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3642f938e14bfed60a5d5b5fdc383e38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80e46c2caec4056bbc2d3b305e3ed190&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d37ffab0584c5106298892733e2c26d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c2fbe724dee488ea4e437995307241f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5f6ef3b354bb0dbf8af7b2c108fd236&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfb1222254442ec5ae96316c08a386f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60ded1802882124212402df3d80de903&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ff761b32d779286afb789136edfc0b4c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fe225f6b6c5b43aceb1fd1109bf8e4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eced97c6a138205573883808dbd74066</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019176</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="General-Purpose AI Models">
  <data key="d0">General-Purpose AI Models</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">General-Purpose AI Models are artificial intelligence systems designed to perform a wide range of tasks across various applications and domains. These models are characterized by their versatility, allowing them to generate text, images, and other content, which can present both opportunities for innovation and challenges for content creators. As such, they underscore the importance of risk management due to their capabilities and potential systemic risks associated with their widespread use.

In addition to their functional attributes, General-Purpose AI Models are subject to specific obligations and regulations aimed at ensuring compliance and monitoring their deployment in the market. These regulatory frameworks are essential for governing their usage and market placement, given the implications of their extensive capabilities and reach.

Overall, General-Purpose AI Models represent a significant advancement in artificial intelligence, with applications spanning multiple fields, necessitating careful oversight to manage the risks and ethical considerations that accompany their deployment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f4b86ca29202de00c1292db00c1efa4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93ef23a1d24ffc516addd681974bac32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e128fa4453175248aac2b8414bc17643&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a8f57272764fbaa96a8c14389c0661d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed27aea701ddc7f366ea5adbe8a4b8e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0bbf5cbd8a6844b23704b7143707807&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4996cfa66f0668d565cd83bbe46dd21a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d055d5f99b33b0d67edb91e844c4185&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf9439294cd1ddefbd5a696360ace9e7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019176</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 73">
  <data key="d0">Article 73</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 73 provides specific provisions for situations where deployers cannot contact providers regarding high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 73 details the reporting obligations for serious incidents occurring during the testing of high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 73 refers to a provision in the Regulation that discusses serious incident reports related to AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 73 outlines the obligations related to the reporting of serious incidents involving high-risk AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f763b444522d2da4e393e2f999f53812&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a13415ed2c222ba72d78fdab855a6ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caf8819d467d1204dd768c10cacdbf06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-413f3509ccce7d84f0a2044eb12be69f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019176</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Prohibited AI Practices">
  <data key="d0">Prohibited AI Practices</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Prohibited AI Practices refer to the specific AI system applications that are banned due to ethical concerns or potential harm to individuals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6f379f07f844b3112cd145a56e02874b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019176</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI Systems">
  <data key="d0">AI Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">AI Systems refer to a broad range of artificial intelligence technologies that utilize computational methods to perform tasks traditionally requiring human intelligence. These systems are characterized by their ability to process various types of data, including personal and biometric information, and are designed for a multitude of applications across different sectors such as law enforcement, finance, healthcare, and education. 

Governance and regulatory frameworks are critical for AI Systems, particularly within the European Union, where they are subject to specific regulations aimed at ensuring their safety, transparency, and trustworthiness. These regulations are intended to mitigate risks associated with AI Systems, especially those classified as high-risk, which demand rigorous compliance measures to protect the rights and welfare of individuals. AI Systems are also governed by ethical guidelines aimed at preventing discrimination and safeguarding fundamental rights during their operation.

Despite their beneficial applications, AI Systems also pose significant risks if misused. They have the potential to manipulate or exploit individuals, leading to harmful outcomes. Notably, oversight is required for AI Systems used in sensitive areas such as biometric identification, risk assessment in law enforcement, and social behavior classification. The need for robust measures to ensure responsible use and to counter undesirable behaviors stems from these risks. Consequently, the development and deployment of AI Systems are guided by ethical principles, design standards, and compliance demands to ensure their beneficial potential is realized while minimizing potential harms. 

Overall, AI Systems represent a complex and evolving landscape that continues to grow in importance and influence, necessitating careful regulation and ethical oversight to balance innovation with societal impact.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f4b86ca29202de00c1292db00c1efa4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80a99ad850f0546ea9da41c8d764b154&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62c64f05f2da893351ea92b9eac1c889&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6243f0a255a83e57f7b7de8b0b878719&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-088a4c3c3c775d33baa63868a127c869&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e99d990c855f3b544868eeee8a6b049b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e47ed52d4514f1818e6c0687c1aa57e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8b33cb346ddcf954cb3e193a006d6add&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b75f7d42df244a78773a748afb4f421f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfdd4a90d27a0fa7cfe5caacb375335c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d05ea92d6d58b07fd1569406080813a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5f6ef3b354bb0dbf8af7b2c108fd236&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d44ed9cdcce8d29cd4cf7a4556478e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-837ff2237a4d4f4c44aa67702b89ec06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e64e0ad4efda4fc9f3a84823cb301955&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ff761b32d779286afb789136edfc0b4c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b64b4983aba9917221464e74b0d86865&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73e4afb71ddc31ffc854d861300d4eb6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b5a506beb14df3337a120faddb2f0b6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a169417b09f70fa2792a3c9ce82a678d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74667d89df5ee6111b7743e86ee4744f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ab4686c3d64e748fcf2e50ddb488920&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df495629e0a16630b58b47ba83c27efa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13766dce116c63c31fc5d746b27279fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97987bc5b95dc5a6f6ebc189b5a394a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3725d0d03194d1c923cc1275d5433c2a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22207e9a20c55a3749a58440b8aab4fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f8eb19a191801e8405a7745849c61a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00803764d58d840979922e38d1dc555c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b1941526d498e207caabd2fb04f938f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2378b7a291e44d534884f6b6e7eeb2a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ad4d08daad55de411fe1304fd990b8e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d055d5f99b33b0d67edb91e844c4185&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55fa705f95ec5acec79f8b691041b65c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5772ed895bc8308d060b1975c2dd69d0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019177</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High-Impact Capabilities">
  <data key="d0">High-Impact Capabilities</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">High-impact capabilities are features or functions of AI models that can significantly affect users and systems, necessitating careful evaluation.&lt;SEP&gt;High-Impact Capabilities refer to capabilities of AI models that exceed the most advanced benchmarks in performance and utility.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6f379f07f844b3112cd145a56e02874b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d97d0e266280dff1c105fac7dc08fc5d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019179</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Systemic Risk">
  <data key="d0">Systemic Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Systemic risk refers to the potential for widespread consequences resulting from the impact of general-purpose AI models on society and the market.&lt;SEP&gt;Systemic Risk is a risk associated with the high-impact capabilities of AI models that can affect public health, safety, and rights.&lt;SEP&gt;Systemic risk is the potential for a general-purpose AI model to have widespread negative impacts, necessitating careful classification and oversight.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6f379f07f844b3112cd145a56e02874b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d97d0e266280dff1c105fac7dc08fc5d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bb17f83caa294ef6efb4f278d7d59fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f137cf6069f0720a443c5b5abd0fe3ea</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019179</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Market Surveillance Authorities">
  <data key="d0">Market Surveillance Authorities</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Market Surveillance Authorities are entities tasked with ensuring compliance with various regulations and facilitating coordination among different stakeholders in the market. They play a crucial role in overseeing both general market operations and specific sectors, such as high-risk artificial intelligence (AI) systems, at the national level. 

These authorities monitor compliance with relevant safety standards and regulations associated with AI systems, emphasizing consumer safety and the integrity of market activities. Their responsibilities include conducting investigations into market operations, particularly concerning high-risk AI systems, ensuring that these systems adhere to established regulatory frameworks.

In addition to these tasks, Market Surveillance Authorities operate within Member States, serving as governmental bodies responsible for monitoring compliance and reporting incidents related to high-risk AI systems available in the market. Their oversight includes checking that these systems meet safety standards and relevant regulations, thereby safeguarding consumer interests and ensuring effective market functioning.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f763b444522d2da4e393e2f999f53812&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5af0747da2a9f2783a1bde010a13814&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a54b012266e9b9c7302fce6d400f583&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51749b7ff68c3ff9e52c0d29dfb02772&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ff761b32d779286afb789136edfc0b4c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df0cf5bee4370453cb38606bad89b764&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22207e9a20c55a3749a58440b8aab4fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b1941526d498e207caabd2fb04f938f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfd6bb7a9801a10b9d2b6a706f0d919d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a242b3e1d633e7e955057a9b078f32d2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019179</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="General-Purpose AI System">
  <data key="d0">General-Purpose AI System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A general-purpose AI system is a versatile technology that can serve multiple purposes and may be integrated into other AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;A General-Purpose AI System is an AI system based on a general-purpose model capable of serving various purposes and integrating into other systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6f379f07f844b3112cd145a56e02874b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf9439294cd1ddefbd5a696360ace9e7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
