<node id="Downstream Provider">
  <data key="d0">Downstream Provider</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Downstream Provider is an entity providing an AI system that incorporates a model, regardless of its source.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6f379f07f844b3112cd145a56e02874b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019180</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Critical Infrastructure">
  <data key="d0">Critical Infrastructure</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Critical infrastructure refers to essential systems and assets that are vital for the functioning of society, which can be threatened by various disruptions.&lt;SEP&gt;Critical infrastructure encompasses essential systems and services, such as water and electricity supply, whose failure can have severe consequences for society.&lt;SEP&gt;Critical Infrastructure refers to essential systems and assets whose incapacitation would have a debilitating impact on security, economy, public health, or safety.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6f379f07f844b3112cd145a56e02874b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d05ea92d6d58b07fd1569406080813a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab5bd61fedb2857e3db189c5f7bb8f94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-971ebc9330032c79166b56276164406c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019180</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Union Legislative Instruments">
  <data key="d0">Union Legislative Instruments</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Union Legislative Instruments are laws established by the European Union that encompass reporting obligations for certain products, including AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-80a99ad850f0546ea9da41c8d764b154</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019180</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Market Surveillance Authority">
  <data key="d0">Market Surveillance Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Market Surveillance Authority is a regulatory body tasked with monitoring and ensuring compliance with the established regulations pertaining to products and services in the market, including high-risk AI systems. It is specifically responsible for overseeing compliance with the provisions outlined in Regulation (EU) 2019/1020, which relates to market surveillance measures for various products.

The Market Surveillance Authority plays a crucial role in monitoring the deployment and use of real-time biometric identification systems, ensuring that these technologies meet the necessary regulatory standards. After conducting a risk assessment on high-risk AI systems, the deployers of these systems are required to notify the authority, enabling it to assess compliance prior to authorization for use.

In carrying out its responsibilities, the Market Surveillance Authority acts as a notified body for high-risk AI systems, collaborating with law enforcement agencies and Union institutions to reinforce regulatory adherence. The authority is not only charged with ensuring that AI systems comply with testing regulations but also has the authority to raise objections against measures taken by other entities when necessary.

Additionally, the Market Surveillance Authority addresses any infringements of compliance regulations and takes appropriate actions as required to uphold market integrity. It serves as a key mechanism for informing public authorities about compliance requests related to AI systems, thereby contributing to overall safety and regulatory adherence within its jurisdiction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f4b86ca29202de00c1292db00c1efa4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80a99ad850f0546ea9da41c8d764b154&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a242b3e1d633e7e955057a9b078f32d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5af0747da2a9f2783a1bde010a13814&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80e46c2caec4056bbc2d3b305e3ed190&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-088a4c3c3c775d33baa63868a127c869&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38cdce9b64b40ba40d6acb529d375787&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e318b5cf27cebec499fc2e251461775a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d17f49a76bb2cf6b427b715f614df19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a13415ed2c222ba72d78fdab855a6ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-880ccb1f68ffcae0925e238408590ede&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93ef23a1d24ffc516addd681974bac32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60ded1802882124212402df3d80de903&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf7d18a6020405fb3429834a129e7cd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b4a84f46448cc3a4a1755da273e920e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caf8819d467d1204dd768c10cacdbf06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e14a05a776d89b0f172b0c5789b0936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b14c58587932db3a6dafb07fe1b8b673</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019181</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) 2017/745">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) 2017/745</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) 2017/745 is a legal framework governing medical devices in the European Union, amending earlier directives.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2017/745 outlines the conditions related to the compliance of certain medical devices, which apply to high-risk AI systems that are medical devices.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2017/745 pertains to medical devices and is referenced as a legal frame for notifications of high-risk AI systems that are safety components.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2017/745 pertains to medical devices and amends several previous directives.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-80a99ad850f0546ea9da41c8d764b154&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea757da73e875c6fedacdd166bb91c2e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0cbd1a5d65f0da33dfc2d2c52c0fa26f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4086e5336bfe9061f6ae69821c67e4ab</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019181</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) 2017/746">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) 2017/746</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) 2017/746 governs in vitro diagnostic medical devices within the European Union, amending existing legislation.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2017/746 is associated with in-vitro diagnostic medical devices and is relevant for notifications regarding AI systems functioning as such devices.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-80a99ad850f0546ea9da41c8d764b154&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4086e5336bfe9061f6ae69821c67e4ab</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019181</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Provider">
  <data key="d0">Provider</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The entity known as the Provider plays a crucial role in the development and regulation of high-risk AI systems. A Provider is defined as a natural or legal person or body that develops or markets an AI system under its own name or trademark. This entity is not only responsible for supplying the AI systems but must also ensure compliance with various regulatory frameworks.

One of the primary responsibilities of a Provider includes incorporating essential components and processes into high-risk AI systems, ensuring they meet predetermined standards of safety and efficacy. In addition to the design and development of these systems, Providers are tasked with conducting rigorous testing in accordance with relevant regulatory guidelines to guarantee transparency and safety.

The Provider is obligated to fulfill specific responsibilities related to conformity with regulations, which includes submitting applications for the assessment of technical documentation associated with the AI system. Providers must also ensure that their quality management systems comply with applicable requirements, notably those outlined in Article 17. This includes maintaining accurate compliance records and reporting any incidents related to the high-risk AI systems they supply or develop.

Furthermore, Providers may include entities that design, develop, or supply General-Purpose AI Models, emphasizing their comprehensive role across various aspects of AI system deployment. Overall, the Provider is integral to the lifecycle of high-risk AI systems, from inception and market placement to compliance and incident reporting.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f763b444522d2da4e393e2f999f53812&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d17f49a76bb2cf6b427b715f614df19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c3976a157910b9837b3b68c158c5b6b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-474ee56c196aef9638f343ef09589bca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20cc9868fcea5ce578101b36c79a42ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-561d345a761ead6d6e1bfabd0f89e09c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d08b2a930ede07e77c7cc4f29016fc57&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-741b1675a971d075b2d3571148530b89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a169417b09f70fa2792a3c9ce82a678d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d2a58a86edb7bec623750da3d232aa2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13766dce116c63c31fc5d746b27279fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caf8819d467d1204dd768c10cacdbf06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51c94d77f328c85a261162f4664235f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-663826fe1821a9ef057cd84da3b741a8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a54b012266e9b9c7302fce6d400f583&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51749b7ff68c3ff9e52c0d29dfb02772&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60ded1802882124212402df3d80de903</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019181</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Social Score">
  <data key="d0">Social Score</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Social score refers to a numerical value derived from evaluating an individual's social behavior or characteristics, which can lead to favorable or unfavorable treatment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-62c64f05f2da893351ea92b9eac1c889</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019181</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Biometric Categorisation Systems">
  <data key="d0">Biometric Categorisation Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Biometric categorisation systems use individuals' biometric data to infer various personal characteristics and opinions, which should be prohibited if misused.&lt;SEP&gt;Biometric categorisation systems are technologies that classify individuals based on their biometric data to determine various personal characteristics.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-62c64f05f2da893351ea92b9eac1c889&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2378b7a291e44d534884f6b6e7eeb2a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019181</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Remote Biometric Identification Systems">
  <data key="d0">Remote Biometric Identification Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Remote biometric identification systems utilize technology to identify individuals from a distance, often raising concerns about risks and biases.&lt;SEP&gt;Remote biometric identification systems utilize technology to identify individuals in real-time based on their biometric traits in public spaces.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-62c64f05f2da893351ea92b9eac1c889&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9238afdc9781d2e524a5550b3c165bed</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019181</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Annex I">
  <data key="d0">Annex I</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Annex I is a crucial section of regulatory documentation that details the Union harmonization legislation specifically relevant to high-risk AI systems. It encompasses various aspects of AI regulation, including the safety components associated with these systems. The legislation outlined in Annex I is applicable to products that incorporate AI systems and delineates the requirements for technical documentation necessary for compliance when these products are placed on the market.

The annex lists existing Union harmonization legislation that governs high-risk AI systems, detailing the applicable legal framework which includes products subjected to rigorous testing procedures. Furthermore, Annex I refers to specific elements of Directive (EU) 2020/1828, providing additional points and amendments that enhance the regulatory measures for AI systems. Overall, Annex I serves as an essential reference for understanding the legislative landscape affecting high-risk AI systems and their operational safety standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f763b444522d2da4e393e2f999f53812&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3642f938e14bfed60a5d5b5fdc383e38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e87d6d03ced0c44c2805ed7127eb0258&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb73a01a1d9b0ba7ee87eb6d896fbea4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b084b4b20e358aaf88a17e35cc6da65d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-926dc457d536779e13715d0b813c320d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eced97c6a138205573883808dbd74066&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55fa705f95ec5acec79f8b691041b65c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019182</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
