</node>
<node id="European Central Bank">
  <data key="d0">European Central Bank</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Central Bank is the central bank for the euro and plays a crucial role in monetary policy and supervision of financial institutions.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Central Bank is the central bank for the euro and is responsible for monetary policy in the Eurozone, including certain regulatory tasks.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Central Bank is the central bank for the euro and oversees monetary policy in the Eurozone, including the supervision of regulated credit institutions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a242b3e1d633e7e955057a9b078f32d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22207e9a20c55a3749a58440b8aab4fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b1941526d498e207caabd2fb04f938f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019182</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Directive 2013/36/EU">
  <data key="d0">Directive 2013/36/EU</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Directive 2013/36/EU outlines regulations for the prudential supervision of credit institutions and investment firms within the EU.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive 2013/36/EU is a legal framework set by the European Parliament and Council regarding credit institutions and prudential supervision.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive 2013/36/EU establishes rules on access to the activity of credit institutions and the prudential supervision of credit institutions and investment firms.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a242b3e1d633e7e955057a9b078f32d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22207e9a20c55a3749a58440b8aab4fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b1941526d498e207caabd2fb04f938f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019182</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Single Supervisory Mechanism">
  <data key="d0">Single Supervisory Mechanism</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Single Supervisory Mechanism is the system that oversees banking institutions in the Eurozone, ensuring compliance with EU laws.&lt;SEP&gt;The Single Supervisory Mechanism is a system of banking supervision in the Eurozone, aimed at ensuring the stability of the banking system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a242b3e1d633e7e955057a9b078f32d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22207e9a20c55a3749a58440b8aab4fd</data>
