  <data key="d5">1773019182</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Market Surveillance Activities">
  <data key="d0">Market Surveillance Activities</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Market surveillance activities refer to the systematic actions taken by authorities to monitor compliance and ensure safety and standards in markets, especially regarding AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a242b3e1d633e7e955057a9b078f32d2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019183</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fundamental Rights Impact Assessment">
  <data key="d0">Fundamental Rights Impact Assessment</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A fundamental rights impact assessment is an evaluation required prior to authorizing the use of biometric identification systems to ensure compliance with fundamental rights.&lt;SEP&gt;Fundamental rights impact assessment is a process that deployers of high-risk AI systems must conduct to identify risks to individual rights and inform necessary measures.&lt;SEP&gt;A Fundamental Rights Impact Assessment evaluates the implications of using certain technologies on individuals' rights and freedoms in relation to law enforcement.&lt;SEP&gt;The Fundamental Rights Impact Assessment is an evaluation required prior to the deployment of high-risk AI systems, focusing on their potential impacts on individual rights.&lt;SEP&gt;Fundamental Rights Impact Assessment is an evaluation to determine potential effects an AI system may have on fundamental rights.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f40cde20fc8948de8e853c9a34187f56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-358eb1d0b0f35e665a7b23702159cfd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-880ccb1f68ffcae0925e238408590ede&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81b13333cc1be55a8f31fdada74da057&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b4a84f46448cc3a4a1755da273e920e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019184</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="General-Purpose AI Model">
  <data key="d0">General-Purpose AI Model</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The General-Purpose AI Model is an artificial intelligence system specifically designed to perform a diverse array of tasks across multiple applications. It is characterized by its flexibility and the potential to be integrated into various other systems, enabling it to address a wide range of functions regardless of its market representation.

This model is classified based on its capabilities and the systemic risks associated with its use, which are important considerations in developing regulatory frameworks surrounding AI technology. A General-Purpose AI Model must adhere to specific obligations regarding risk management and compliance, particularly when it is intended for placement in the market, such as the Union market regulations. 

In essence, the General-Purpose AI Model serves as a multi-functional tool in the AI landscape but also brings with it certain responsibilities and regulatory requirements due to the systemic risks it may pose. Consequently, all implementations and applications of this model are subject to scrutiny and must comply with established safety and ethical standards to mitigate associated risks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6f379f07f844b3112cd145a56e02874b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6651a485fa4747217fdc9be856c3bf9d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f137cf6069f0720a443c5b5abd0fe3ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d97d0e266280dff1c105fac7dc08fc5d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bb17f83caa294ef6efb4f278d7d59fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-546a0f6bb154d36417ac57e86137b45d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8ea3c173c0c1e99c19f3957adaea81b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13766dce116c63c31fc5d746b27279fc</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019185</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Judicial Authority">
  <data key="d0">Judicial Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">A judicial authority is a legal body that can grant authorization for the use of biometric identification systems for law enforcement purposes.&lt;SEP&gt;A Judicial Authority adjudicates legal matters and grants authorizations related to law enforcement activities.&lt;SEP&gt;Judicial authority refers to entities that possess the power to administer justice, such as courts or judges, often using AI systems for legal processes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f40cde20fc8948de8e853c9a34187f56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e64e0ad4efda4fc9f3a84823cb301955&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b4a84f46448cc3a4a1755da273e920e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e99d990c855f3b544868eeee8a6b049b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a13415ed2c222ba72d78fdab855a6ca</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019185</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) 2019/1020">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) 2019/1020</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) 2019/1020 is a comprehensive legislative framework enacted to strengthen market surveillance and ensure compliance of products within the European Union. This regulation enhances the enforcement of Union market rules, ensuring that only compliant products are allowed to reach the market. It builds upon and amends previous regulations, thereby establishing more robust structures for oversight.

The regulation provides detailed guidelines and procedures for market surveillance activities, including the responsibilities assigned to market surveillance authorities to uphold product safety and compliance. It emphasizes the importance of conformity assessment procedures for various products, ensuring that they meet established EU standards and requirements.

Additionally, Regulation (EU) 2019/1020 has specific implications for the oversight of artificial intelligence (AI) systems and models. It stipulates reporting obligations and outlines obligations related to the market surveillance of AI technologies, thereby integrating these modern innovations into the existing regulatory framework.

In essence, Regulation (EU) 2019/1020 serves to consolidate and enhance the mechanisms for product compliance and market oversight in the European Union, addressing both traditional products and emerging technologies like AI systems. It reflects the EU's commitment to maintaining high standards of product safety and consumer protection across the market.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-80a99ad850f0546ea9da41c8d764b154&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5af0747da2a9f2783a1bde010a13814&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80e46c2caec4056bbc2d3b305e3ed190&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-088a4c3c3c775d33baa63868a127c869&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a54b012266e9b9c7302fce6d400f583&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e318b5cf27cebec499fc2e251461775a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc7122206f7a3097526258a05d85baef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74667d89df5ee6111b7743e86ee4744f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f40b01fb5e1dbaa442b55c31285ecb50&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22207e9a20c55a3749a58440b8aab4fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b1941526d498e207caabd2fb04f938f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019185</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
