<node id="Real-Time Remote Biometric Identification Systems">
  <data key="d0">Real-Time Remote Biometric Identification Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Real-time remote biometric identification systems are used in law enforcement to confirm an individual's identity in publicly accessible spaces, subject to authorization and specific conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;Real-time remote biometric identification systems are technologies that identify individuals based on their biometric data and operate immediately, raising concerns regarding privacy and discrimination.&lt;SEP&gt;Real-time remote biometric identification systems are technologies used in public spaces for law enforcement purposes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3642f938e14bfed60a5d5b5fdc383e38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab5bd61fedb2857e3db189c5f7bb8f94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b4a84f46448cc3a4a1755da273e920e</data>
