<node id="EU Database">
  <data key="d0">EU Database</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The EU Database is a proposed centralized repository designed to facilitate transparency and regulatory compliance for high-risk artificial intelligence (AI) systems within the European Union. This database aims to ensure that providers and deployers of such systems meet established registration requirements and adhere to relevant protocols across various sectors.

Functionally, the EU Database serves multiple roles, including the registration of high-risk AI systems and the management of associated regulatory obligations. It supports the tracking of compliance with Union data protection laws and addresses the needs of law enforcement by ensuring that registered systems align with established regulations. 

Moreover, the EU Database stores crucial information related to the testing and compliance status of AI systems, contributing to a comprehensive understanding of their regulatory standing within the EU framework. By capturing specific details pertinent to compliance requirements, the EU Database plays a vital role in maintaining oversight and accountability in the deployment of high-risk AI technologies across the region.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f40cde20fc8948de8e853c9a34187f56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a54b012266e9b9c7302fce6d400f583&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38cdce9b64b40ba40d6acb529d375787&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a13415ed2c222ba72d78fdab855a6ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b14c58587932db3a6dafb07fe1b8b673&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73e4afb71ddc31ffc854d861300d4eb6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fe225f6b6c5b43aceb1fd1109bf8e4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5da5d9be8aadcb05915f4a8f8f5aa33</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019190</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
