</node>
<node id="Article 82">
  <data key="d0">Article 82</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 82 addresses compliant AI systems that present risks to health, safety, or public interest protection.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-38cdce9b64b40ba40d6acb529d375787</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019196</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Sets">
  <data key="d0">Data Sets</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Data sets are collections of data used for training, validation, and testing AI systems, which must be relevant, representative, and free of errors for effective performance.&lt;SEP&gt;Data Sets are collections of data used for training AI systems, encompassing their provenance, scope, and main characteristics.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd94ba8542b0c8ff4b050fc6027f5237&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-561d345a761ead6d6e1bfabd0f89e09c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019196</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Small and Microenterprises">
  <data key="d0">Small and Microenterprises</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Small and microenterprises are businesses characterized by a limited number of employees and revenue, which may provide simplified technical documentation for compliance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd94ba8542b0c8ff4b050fc6027f5237</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019196</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bias Detection and Correction">
  <data key="d0">Bias Detection and Correction</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Bias detection and correction refers to techniques aimed at identifying and mitigating bias in AI systems, especially those classified as high-risk.&lt;SEP&gt;Bias Detection and Correction refers to the processes and measures implemented to identify and mitigate biases in AI systems, ensuring fairness and compliance with regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd94ba8542b0c8ff4b050fc6027f5237&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8b33cb346ddcf954cb3e193a006d6add</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019196</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Alternative Dispute Resolution">
  <data key="d0">Alternative Dispute Resolution</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Alternative dispute resolution refers to methods used to resolve conflicts outside of traditional judicial proceedings, which may involve AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e99d990c855f3b544868eeee8a6b049b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019196</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) 2018/1725">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) 2018/1725</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) 2018/1725 is a legislative framework that focuses on the protection of personal data handled by Union institutions and agencies within the European Union. This regulation outlines specific rules governing the processing of personal data, ensuring that any such data management adheres to established privacy standards and safeguards the rights of individuals.

The regulation applies to personal data processed by various EU institutions and bodies, emphasizing the importance of privacy in all administrative matters within the EU. It also establishes supplementary data protection measures tailored for certain data processing activities, thereby reinforcing the protection of individuals' personal information. 

Furthermore, Regulation (EU) 2018/1725 plays a significant role in the broader context of data protection, particularly in its implications for emerging technologies such as artificial intelligence. By doing so, it ensures that the processing of personal data within these contexts is aligned with the fundamental principles of privacy and data protection, thus further contributing to the regulatory landscape governing personal data in the EU.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9238afdc9781d2e524a5550b3c165bed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd94ba8542b0c8ff4b050fc6027f5237&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8b33cb346ddcf954cb3e193a006d6add&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc7122206f7a3097526258a05d85baef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7aba082da5b9f8ab2defc1a7a725bef0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74667d89df5ee6111b7743e86ee4744f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5da5d9be8aadcb05915f4a8f8f5aa33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d055d5f99b33b0d67edb91e844c4185</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019196</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) 2024/900">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) 2024/900</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) 2024/900 is a legal framework aimed at governing the use of AI systems, particularly related to electoral processes and voting rights.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e99d990c855f3b544868eeee8a6b049b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019197</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 39 of the Charter">
  <data key="d0">Article 39 of the Charter</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 39 of the Charter protects the right to vote within the European Union, emphasizing the importance of maintaining democracy and the rule of law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e99d990c855f3b544868eeee8a6b049b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019197</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI System">
  <data key="d0">AI System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The AI System is defined as a technological entity designed to simulate human intelligence by performing tasks typically requiring human cognition. These systems are distinguished from traditional software by their ability to learn and reason, enabling them to infer outputs that can significantly impact environments.

AI Systems encompass a range of artificial intelligence technologies applicable across military, civilian, and law enforcement domains. They include various tools, services, and components aimed at model training, testing, and integration, operating based on a collection of algorithms. Specifically, an AI System consists of AI models that guide its functionalities and can be classified into categories based on risk levels, including high-risk classifications according to specific regulatory criteria.

These systems are structured to operate autonomously, producing outcomes based on the inputs received, which can influence individuals and groups in terms of risk and safety. Compliance with essential quality and safety requirements is crucial, and as part of a conformity assessment procedure, AI Systems undergo evaluation to ensure adherence to regulatory standards regarding their training, documentation, and overall assessment before market placement. Thus, AI Systems represent an evolving intersection of technology and regulatory compliance that addresses both innovation and societal impact.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9238afdc9781d2e524a5550b3c165bed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e87d6d03ced0c44c2805ed7127eb0258&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea757da73e875c6fedacdd166bb91c2e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-474ee56c196aef9638f343ef09589bca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20cc9868fcea5ce578101b36c79a42ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93ef23a1d24ffc516addd681974bac32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b14c58587932db3a6dafb07fe1b8b673&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d08b2a930ede07e77c7cc4f29016fc57&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-741b1675a971d075b2d3571148530b89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81b13333cc1be55a8f31fdada74da057&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22dcb6c71a1828d1166aad9d5a7cac19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-061f3c307dd55152ffbb5bdfae17ea90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51c94d77f328c85a261162f4664235f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-561d345a761ead6d6e1bfabd0f89e09c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019197</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EC) No 810/2009">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EC) No 810/2009</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EC) No 810/2009 is a legal guideline established by the European Parliament concerning visa management and related procedures.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EC) No 810/2009 is a legal act from the European Parliament and Council establishing a Community Code on Visas, governing visa policies within the EU.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e99d990c855f3b544868eeee8a6b049b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e47ed52d4514f1818e6c0687c1aa57e4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019197</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Directive 2013/32">
  <data key="d0">Directive 2013/32</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Directive 2013/32 is an EU directive related to processes regarding the treatment of applicants for international protection.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e99d990c855f3b544868eeee8a6b049b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019197</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CE Marking">
  <data key="d0">CE Marking</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">CE marking is an indication that high-risk AI systems conform to relevant regulations, allowing them to be marketed and used within the internal market.&lt;SEP&gt;CE marking indicates that an AI system complies with regulatory requirements and applicable legislation.&lt;SEP&gt;CE marking indicates that the high-risk AI system meets EU safety, health, and environmental protection requirements and is required for regulatory compliance.&lt;SEP&gt;The CE marking signifies that a product, including high-risk AI systems, complies with EU safety standards and regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The CE Marking indicates a product's conformity with EU safety standards, especially for high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;The CE Marking indicates compliance with European standards and regulations but can be affixed incorrectly or not at all.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e318b5cf27cebec499fc2e251461775a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d17f49a76bb2cf6b427b715f614df19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c3976a157910b9837b3b68c158c5b6b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b14c58587932db3a6dafb07fe1b8b673&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fe225f6b6c5b43aceb1fd1109bf8e4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e14a05a776d89b0f172b0c5789b0936</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019197</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Registration in the EU Database">
  <data key="d0">Registration in the EU Database</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The registration in the EU database is a compliance measure mandated by EU regulations that must be carried out properly.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e318b5cf27cebec499fc2e251461775a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019197</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Authorised Representative">
  <data key="d0">Authorised Representative</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An authorised representative is a person in the Union accepted to perform obligations on behalf of a provider of an AI system.&lt;SEP&gt;The authorised representative is appointed by the provider to carry out certain regulatory compliance tasks regarding the high-risk AI system.&lt;SEP&gt;The authorised representative is appointed by providers established in third countries to act on their behalf within the Union market.&lt;SEP&gt;The Authorised Representative is an entity appointed by the provider to act on their behalf regarding compliance with regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;An authorised representative is a designated individual responsible for ensuring compliance with specified regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e318b5cf27cebec499fc2e251461775a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51749b7ff68c3ff9e52c0d29dfb02772&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d17f49a76bb2cf6b427b715f614df19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13766dce116c63c31fc5d746b27279fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51c94d77f328c85a261162f4664235f6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019197</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Union AI Testing Support Structures">
  <data key="d0">Union AI Testing Support Structures</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Union AI Testing Support Structures are systems established to support the Member States in the enforcement of AI regulations and testing.&lt;SEP&gt;Union AI testing support structures are designated entities that provide technical support and advice related to AI compliance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e318b5cf27cebec499fc2e251461775a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df0cf5bee4370453cb38606bad89b764</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019197</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Directive (EU) 2019/1937">
  <data key="d0">Directive (EU) 2019/1937</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Directive (EU) 2019/1937 addresses the reporting of infringements and the protection of whistleblowers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e318b5cf27cebec499fc2e251461775a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019197</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Logging Capabilities">
  <data key="d0">Logging Capabilities</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Logging capabilities are features of high-risk AI systems that allow for the automatic recording of relevant events for traceability and compliance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cb73a01a1d9b0ba7ee87eb6d896fbea4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019197</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scientific Panel">
  <data key="d0">Scientific Panel</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Scientific Panel is a group of experts that the AI Office may consult to ensure high standards in the drawing up of codes of practice.&lt;SEP&gt;The Scientific Panel is intended to integrate scientific community insights into the implementation of the Regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;The Scientific Panel consists of independent experts focused on providing technical expertise in AI and ensuring regulatory adherence.&lt;SEP&gt;The scientific panel supports monitoring activities related to AI systems and may alert authorities about potential risks associated with AI models.&lt;SEP&gt;The Scientific Panel consists of experts who provide impartial advice on AI models and support enforcement activities as per regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Scientific Panel provides alerts regarding systemic risks related to general-purpose AI models and investigates compliance.&lt;SEP&gt;The Scientific Panel is established under Article 68 and provides expert evaluations for the Commission.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6651a485fa4747217fdc9be856c3bf9d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f137cf6069f0720a443c5b5abd0fe3ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed27aea701ddc7f366ea5adbe8a4b8e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15ddf6f50e7dd1750489a4999454bcdf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df0cf5bee4370453cb38606bad89b764&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b1941526d498e207caabd2fb04f938f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfd6bb7a9801a10b9d2b6a706f0d919d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019198</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Qualified Alert">
  <data key="d0">Qualified Alert</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Qualified Alert is a formal notice by the Scientific Panel indicating potential systemic risks posed by a general-purpose AI model.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6651a485fa4747217fdc9be856c3bf9d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019198</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Provider of General-Purpose AI Model">
  <data key="d0">Provider of General-Purpose AI Model</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Provider of General-Purpose AI Model refers to any entity that develops or supplies general-purpose AI models, responsible for compliance with regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6651a485fa4747217fdc9be856c3bf9d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019198</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Law Enforcement Authorities">
  <data key="d0">Law Enforcement Authorities</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Law enforcement authorities are governmental bodies responsible for the enforcement of laws and ensuring public safety, often involving AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Law enforcement authorities are agencies responsible for the enforcement of laws, the prevention of crime, and the prosecution of offenders.&lt;SEP&gt;Law Enforcement Authorities are responsible for the investigation and prevention of criminal offenses and the safeguarding of public security.&lt;SEP&gt;Law enforcement authorities are tasked with maintaining public order and safety, often utilizing AI systems to support their operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e47ed52d4514f1818e6c0687c1aa57e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d44ed9cdcce8d29cd4cf7a4556478e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eced97c6a138205573883808dbd74066&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5772ed895bc8308d060b1975c2dd69d0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019198</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="UN Convention Relating to the Status of Refugees">
  <data key="d0">UN Convention Relating to the Status of Refugees</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The UN Convention relating to the Status of Refugees is an international treaty aimed at protecting asylum seekers and refugees.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e47ed52d4514f1818e6c0687c1aa57e4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019198</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Financial Intelligence Units">
  <data key="d0">Financial Intelligence Units</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Financial intelligence units are agencies responsible for analyzing information related to anti-money laundering and financial tasks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e47ed52d4514f1818e6c0687c1aa57e4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019198</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI Tools">
  <data key="d0">AI Tools</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">AI tools refer to various applications of artificial intelligence technologies, particularly in law enforcement and public authorities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e47ed52d4514f1818e6c0687c1aa57e4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019198</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vulnerable Persons">
  <data key="d0">Vulnerable Persons</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Vulnerable persons are individuals who may face risks or discrimination and whose rights must be protected, especially in contexts of migration and border control.&lt;SEP&gt;Vulnerable persons are groups who may be disproportionately affected by AI systems, necessitating special considerations regarding accessibility and equality.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e47ed52d4514f1818e6c0687c1aa57e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b75f7d42df244a78773a748afb4f421f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019199</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Human Oversight">
  <data key="d0">Human Oversight</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Human oversight involves monitoring AI systems to ensure they comply with ethical standards and regulations, playing a critical role in risk management.&lt;SEP&gt;Human oversight of high-risk AI systems aims to ensure that there are adequate measures to monitor and interpret the system's outputs effectively.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7c2fbe724dee488ea4e437995307241f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-234952a50b5a02b1afedbe8d8e1c076b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019199</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Risk Mitigation Measures">
  <data key="d0">Risk Mitigation Measures</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Risk mitigation measures are strategies implemented to minimize foreseeable misuse and enhance the safety of AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-234952a50b5a02b1afedbe8d8e1c076b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019199</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European Union Law">
  <data key="d0">European Union Law</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">European Union law sets regulatory standards applicable to the development and use of high-risk AI systems, emphasizing human rights and privacy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-234952a50b5a02b1afedbe8d8e1c076b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019199</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European Digital Innovation Hubs">
  <data key="d0">European Digital Innovation Hubs</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">European Digital Innovation Hubs are entities that support organizations in their digital transformation efforts, including AI development.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Digital Innovation Hubs are initiatives that support technological innovation and facilitate compliance with the Regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;European Digital Innovation Hubs are initiatives aimed at supporting digital transformation for SMEs and promoting innovation across the EU.&lt;SEP&gt;European Digital Innovation Hubs are facilities that support digital innovation and technological advancements across Europe.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-234952a50b5a02b1afedbe8d8e1c076b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d5a14698f71544a90fc06f98323f315&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15ddf6f50e7dd1750489a4999454bcdf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e0d95f75393cb87bb510dfcf3ba0ef5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019199</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vulnerable Groups">
  <data key="d0">Vulnerable Groups</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Vulnerable groups refer to populations that may be disproportionately affected by biases in AI systems, including racial or ethnic groups.&lt;SEP&gt;Vulnerable groups include individuals who may be particularly at risk due to factors such as age or disability in interactions with AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Vulnerable groups refer to segments of the population that may require special consideration in testing and data processing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;Vulnerable groups are individuals who may be at higher risk during testing due to their age or disability.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-234952a50b5a02b1afedbe8d8e1c076b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73e4afb71ddc31ffc854d861300d4eb6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5da5d9be8aadcb05915f4a8f8f5aa33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caf8819d467d1204dd768c10cacdbf06</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019199</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Compliance Services">
  <data key="d0">Compliance Services</data>
  <data key="d1">service</data>
  <data key="d2">Compliance services include third-party verification and support to ensure adherence to data governance and management requirements for AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-234952a50b5a02b1afedbe8d8e1c076b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019199</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="APIs">
  <data key="d0">APIs</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">APIs (Application Programming Interfaces) are technical means through which access to the general-purpose AI model may be requested.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f137cf6069f0720a443c5b5abd0fe3ea</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019199</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 90(1)">
  <data key="d0">Article 90(1)</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 90(1) refers to the basis on which the Commission may designate general-purpose AI models as having systemic risks.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 90(1) outlines the legal provisions concerning the evaluation and access of general-purpose AI models.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f137cf6069f0720a443c5b5abd0fe3ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bb17f83caa294ef6efb4f278d7d59fd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019199</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 101">
  <data key="d0">Article 101</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 101 describes the penalties for failing to provide requested access to the general-purpose AI model.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f137cf6069f0720a443c5b5abd0fe3ea</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019199</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Technical Documentation">
  <data key="d0">Technical Documentation</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Technical Documentation refers to a comprehensive set of records that provide essential information regarding high-risk artificial intelligence (AI) systems. This documentation is crucial for assessing compliance with regulatory standards and facilitating post-market monitoring. It must contain detailed information relevant to the operation and management of these AI systems, which is necessary for compliance verification by competent authorities.

The technical documentation encompasses various elements, including all necessary information to evaluate the AI system's adherence to compliance requirements. It outlines the compliance requirements themselves, detailing the information needed for proper assessment. This includes records that demonstrate the compliance of high-risk AI systems with applicable regulations, as well as documentation that describes the functionalities, components, and operational guidelines of the AI systems.

Furthermore, technical documentation must be adequately prepared and made available to relevant authorities to ensure transparency and regulatory oversight. It serves as a fundamental resource for assessing the system's reliability and safety, outlining detailed instructions and guidelines for others in the process of integration and use of the AI model. Overall, technical documentation plays a pivotal role in the responsible management and oversight of high-risk AI systems, ensuring that they meet established standards and are compliant with necessary regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd94ba8542b0c8ff4b050fc6027f5237&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e318b5cf27cebec499fc2e251461775a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb73a01a1d9b0ba7ee87eb6d896fbea4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-234952a50b5a02b1afedbe8d8e1c076b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8b33cb346ddcf954cb3e193a006d6add&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51749b7ff68c3ff9e52c0d29dfb02772&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d17f49a76bb2cf6b427b715f614df19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c3976a157910b9837b3b68c158c5b6b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e64e0ad4efda4fc9f3a84823cb301955&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d08b2a930ede07e77c7cc4f29016fc57&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-741b1675a971d075b2d3571148530b89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8ea3c173c0c1e99c19f3957adaea81b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019200</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 94">
  <data key="d0">Article 94</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 94 provides procedural rights for economic operators related to the general-purpose AI model.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f137cf6069f0720a443c5b5abd0fe3ea</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019200</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 95">
  <data key="d0">Article 95</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 95 concerns codes of conduct for voluntary application of specific requirements to AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f137cf6069f0720a443c5b5abd0fe3ea</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019200</data>
