</node>
<node id="General-Purpose AI Model Providers">
  <data key="d0">General-Purpose AI Model Providers</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">General-Purpose AI Model Providers are the companies or entities responsible for supplying general-purpose AI models and are subject to regulatory measures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f137cf6069f0720a443c5b5abd0fe3ea</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019200</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="National Law">
  <data key="d0">National Law</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">National law refers to laws established by individual countries that may consider certain requirements for high-risk AI systems as disproportionate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e20d35aae57ccfd5ec58ef7772f98c17</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019200</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Organizational Measures">
  <data key="d0">Organizational Measures</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Organizational measures refer to protocols and policies implemented to mitigate risks associated with high-risk AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e20d35aae57ccfd5ec58ef7772f98c17</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019200</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="EU Declaration of Conformity">
  <data key="d0">EU Declaration of Conformity</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The EU Declaration of Conformity is a crucial document required for high-risk AI systems, affirming their compliance with specific regulatory requirements set by the European Union. It serves as an official statement that certifies a product's adherence to necessary standards and regulations, ensuring that it meets the established EU compliance criteria.

This documentation must be meticulously prepared to demonstrate alignment with EU legislation and is particularly significant in the context of high-risk AI systems. In accordance with Article 47, the declaration confirms that the AI system fulfills the specified regulatory obligations. It is important to note that this declaration must be retained for a period of 10 years, highlighting its role in regulatory accountability.

By serving as a certification that products meet EU standards, the EU Declaration of Conformity plays an essential part in promoting safety and compliance within the marketplace. As such, it is not merely a formality but a vital component of the relationship between manufacturers, regulatory bodies, and the assurance of consumer protection within the EU.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e318b5cf27cebec499fc2e251461775a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e20d35aae57ccfd5ec58ef7772f98c17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51749b7ff68c3ff9e52c0d29dfb02772&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d17f49a76bb2cf6b427b715f614df19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c3976a157910b9837b3b68c158c5b6b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-561d345a761ead6d6e1bfabd0f89e09c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf7d18a6020405fb3429834a129e7cd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d2a58a86edb7bec623750da3d232aa2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fe225f6b6c5b43aceb1fd1109bf8e4f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019200</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 48">
  <data key="d0">Article 48</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 48 outlines the requirements for affixing the CE marking to high-risk AI systems to indicate conformity with regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e20d35aae57ccfd5ec58ef7772f98c17</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019200</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Union Data Protection Law">
  <data key="d0">Union Data Protection Law</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Union data protection law includes regulations ensuring the right to privacy and the protection of personal data, applicable to AI system lifecycle management.&lt;SEP&gt;Union Data Protection Law refers to regulations governing the handling of personal data within the European Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8b33cb346ddcf954cb3e193a006d6add&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e0d95f75393cb87bb510dfcf3ba0ef5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019200</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Transparency Measures">
  <data key="d0">Transparency Measures</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Transparency measures refer to requirements for providing clear and comprehensive information about high-risk AI systems to ensure accountability.&lt;SEP&gt;Transparency measures are guidelines that impose documentation and information sharing obligations on AI model providers to enhance accountability.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8b33cb346ddcf954cb3e193a006d6add&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf9439294cd1ddefbd5a696360ace9e7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019200</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Minimisation">
  <data key="d0">Data Minimisation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Data minimisation is a principle aimed at reducing the amount of personal data collected and processed to the necessary minimum required for the intended purpose.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8b33cb346ddcf954cb3e193a006d6add</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019201</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Protection by Design and by Default">
  <data key="d0">Data Protection by Design and by Default</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Data protection by design and by default is a framework ensuring that data protection measures are integrated into the development and operation of AI systems from the outset.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8b33cb346ddcf954cb3e193a006d6add</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019201</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Anonymisation">
  <data key="d0">Anonymisation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Anonymisation is a technique used to remove personal identifiers from data, making it impossible to link the data back to an individual.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8b33cb346ddcf954cb3e193a006d6add</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019201</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Encryption">
  <data key="d0">Encryption</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Encryption is a method of encoding data to prevent unauthorized access and ensure the confidentiality of personal information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8b33cb346ddcf954cb3e193a006d6add</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019201</data>
