<node id="Human Oversight Measures">
  <data key="d0">Human Oversight Measures</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Human oversight measures are necessary strategies identified by AI system providers to ensure proper monitoring and intervention by natural persons throughout the system's lifecycle.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-46bc64e87ac07d3576c10a8dd9d66d9e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019201</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 23">
  <data key="d0">Article 23</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 23 describes the obligations of importers as per the established regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 23 establishes obligations that importers must adhere to in order to comply with EU laws and regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7f5283f6c8ea50d5bcac79684f773610&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b45385ec456bd2744fcc58cd02368fc0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 51">
  <data key="d0">Article 51</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 51 defines classification rules for identifying general-purpose AI models with systemic risks.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 51 relates to additional requirements necessary for the enforcement and compliance of delegated powers in EU legislation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7f5283f6c8ea50d5bcac79684f773610&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bb17f83caa294ef6efb4f278d7d59fd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 52">
  <data key="d0">Article 52</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 52 addresses specific obligations and operational procedures concerning delegated acts within the European Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7f5283f6c8ea50d5bcac79684f773610</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 53">
  <data key="d0">Article 53</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 53 outlines the obligations for providers of general-purpose AI models, including documentation and compliance requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 53 outlines specific obligations for providers of General-Purpose AI Models prior to their market introduction.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 53 outlines obligations that must be adhered to by general-purpose AI model providers.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 53 establishes further rules on the delegation of power and associated compliance measures in EU law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7f5283f6c8ea50d5bcac79684f773610&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-546a0f6bb154d36417ac57e86137b45d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13766dce116c63c31fc5d746b27279fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ba035757525dfa257fa2b97fdbd40b2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Union Financial Services Law">
  <data key="d0">Union Financial Services Law</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Union financial services law consists of rules and requirements applicable to financial institutions regarding governance and risk management.&lt;SEP&gt;Union financial services law encompasses regulations governing financial institutions within the European Union.&lt;SEP&gt;Union financial services law comprises regulations governing financial institutions' operations and compliance measures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-51749b7ff68c3ff9e52c0d29dfb02772&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a13415ed2c222ba72d78fdab855a6ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f40b01fb5e1dbaa442b55c31285ecb50</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Providers">
  <data key="d0">Providers</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Providers are entities that supply high-risk AI systems and are responsible for ensuring compliance with relevant regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Providers are entities that supply AI systems to deployers and play a role in the incident reporting procedures outlined in the regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Providers are organizations or individuals responsible for designing and deploying AI systems that must adhere to specified transparency obligations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-51749b7ff68c3ff9e52c0d29dfb02772&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a13415ed2c222ba72d78fdab855a6ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d043d4edae3c59146709349b2875a92&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5da5d9be8aadcb05915f4a8f8f5aa33</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Corrective Actions">
  <data key="d0">Corrective Actions</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Corrective actions refer to the measures providers must take when a high-risk AI system is found to be non-compliant with regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-51749b7ff68c3ff9e52c0d29dfb02772</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Competent Authority">
  <data key="d0">Competent Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">A competent authority is an official body that may request information and documentation from providers to demonstrate system conformity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-51749b7ff68c3ff9e52c0d29dfb02772</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Automatically Generated Logs">
  <data key="d0">Automatically Generated Logs</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Automatically generated logs are records produced by high-risk AI systems to track their operation and performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-51749b7ff68c3ff9e52c0d29dfb02772</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cybersecurity">
  <data key="d0">Cybersecurity</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Cybersecurity is critical for protecting AI systems from malicious attacks aiming to alter their behavior and misuse.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cfdd4a90d27a0fa7cfe5caacb375335c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ENISA">
  <data key="d0">ENISA</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">ENISA is the European Union Agency for Cybersecurity, providing expertise and support in cybersecurity policy and practices.&lt;SEP&gt;ENISA is the European Union Agency for Cybersecurity, responsible for cybersecurity policy and cooperation under Regulation (EU) 2019/881.&lt;SEP&gt;ENISA, the European Union Agency for Cybersecurity, supports the enforcement of cybersecurity aspects related to AI regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;ENISA is a cybersecurity organization and a permanent member of the Advisory Forum.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cfdd4a90d27a0fa7cfe5caacb375335c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-70bf47b2a9599482bedc275e3e2257a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df0cf5bee4370453cb38606bad89b764&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5a5973b039f9a9af3e3e9d93b392c66</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ICT Infrastructure">
  <data key="d0">ICT Infrastructure</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">ICT infrastructure refers to the underlying information and communication technology systems that support the operation of digital elements, including AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cfdd4a90d27a0fa7cfe5caacb375335c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Digital Elements">
  <data key="d0">Digital Elements</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Digital elements refer to products or systems that operate digitally and are subject to specific cybersecurity regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cfdd4a90d27a0fa7cfe5caacb375335c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Technical Solutions">
  <data key="d0">Technical Solutions</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Technical solutions are measures designed to prevent or minimize harmful behavior in high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Technical solutions are methodologies implemented to ensure transparency and traceability of AI outputs, including techniques such as watermarks and metadata identification.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cfdd4a90d27a0fa7cfe5caacb375335c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73e4afb71ddc31ffc854d861300d4eb6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019203</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) 2019/881">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) 2019/881</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) 2019/881 is a legislative document by the European Parliament that sets cybersecurity policy and requirements for digital products.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2019/881 establishes provisions for cybersecurity policy and tasks related to AI systems in the European Union.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2019/881 relates to cybersecurity requirements for AI systems and includes provisions for certificates of conformity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cfdd4a90d27a0fa7cfe5caacb375335c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-70bf47b2a9599482bedc275e3e2257a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfb1222254442ec5ae96316c08a386f0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019203</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 34">
  <data key="d0">Article 34</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 34 outlines the operational obligations of notified bodies concerning high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 34 defines additional obligations applicable to notified bodies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b45385ec456bd2744fcc58cd02368fc0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78ea54ae6ffd2850256fb7ad037b8474</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019203</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Importer">
  <data key="d0">Importer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">An importer is a person or body in the Union that places an AI system on the market under the name of an entity from a third country.&lt;SEP&gt;The importer is the entity responsible for bringing the high-risk AI system to the market and ensuring its compliance with regulations before market placement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d17f49a76bb2cf6b427b715f614df19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51c94d77f328c85a261162f4664235f6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019203</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Rights of Persons with Disabilities">
  <data key="d0">Rights of Persons with Disabilities</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Rights of Persons with Disabilities emphasizes legal obligations for the protection and promotion of equality for individuals with disabilities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-70bf47b2a9599482bedc275e3e2257a5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019203</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Directive (EU) 2016/2102">
  <data key="d0">Directive (EU) 2016/2102</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Directive (EU) 2016/2102 mandates accessibility requirements for public sector bodies in the European Union.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive (EU) 2016/2102 establishes rules for the accessibility of websites and mobile applications of public sector bodies within the EU.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-70bf47b2a9599482bedc275e3e2257a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea757da73e875c6fedacdd166bb91c2e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019203</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Directive (EU) 2019/882">
  <data key="d0">Directive (EU) 2019/882</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Directive (EU) 2019/882 is a legislation by the European Parliament regarding accessibility requirements for products and services.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive (EU) 2019/882 focuses on harmonizing rules for the accessibility of products and services in the European market.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive (EU) 2019/882 outlines requirements related to AI systems and aims to ensure their safe deployment and transparency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-70bf47b2a9599482bedc275e3e2257a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73e4afb71ddc31ffc854d861300d4eb6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2378b7a291e44d534884f6b6e7eeb2a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019203</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Natural or Legal Person">
  <data key="d0">Natural or Legal Person</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Natural or Legal Person refers to individuals or organizations that can be responsible for the placement of high-risk AI systems on the market.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-70bf47b2a9599482bedc275e3e2257a5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019203</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Union Institution">
  <data key="d0">Union Institution</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Union institutions include bodies, offices, or agencies within the European Union that must comply with regulations regarding AI practices and data protection.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-382f1c7a3c02bab4bf3bee2d03cc7e1f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019204</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="EUR 1 500 000">
  <data key="d0">EUR 1 500 000</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">EUR 1,500,000 represents the maximum administrative fines for non-compliance with Article 5 related to AI practices.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-382f1c7a3c02bab4bf3bee2d03cc7e1f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019204</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="EUR 750 000">
  <data key="d0">EUR 750 000</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">EUR 750,000 represents the maximum administrative fines applicable for non-compliance with AI system requirements outside Article 5.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-382f1c7a3c02bab4bf3bee2d03cc7e1f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019204</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="EUR 15 000 000">
  <data key="d0">EUR 15 000 000</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">EUR 15,000,000 indicates the upper limit for fines that can be imposed by the Commission on providers of general-purpose AI models for violations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-382f1c7a3c02bab4bf3bee2d03cc7e1f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019204</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Distributors">
  <data key="d0">Distributors</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Distributors are entities that contribute to the development of AI systems by distributing products to customers.&lt;SEP&gt;Distributors are entities responsible for making high-risk AI systems available in the market and ensuring compliance with regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Distributors are entities that distribute AI systems and are involved in the notification processes related to incidents or risks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3976a157910b9837b3b68c158c5b6b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea757da73e875c6fedacdd166bb91c2e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a13415ed2c222ba72d78fdab855a6ca</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019204</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Importers">
  <data key="d0">Importers</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Importers are entities that contribute to the development of AI systems by bringing products into a specific market.&lt;SEP&gt;Importers are parties that bring high-risk AI systems into the market and must ensure they meet all necessary requirements and documentation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3976a157910b9837b3b68c158c5b6b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea757da73e875c6fedacdd166bb91c2e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019204</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Operators">
  <data key="d0">Operators</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Operators are entities that manage AI systems, either within the Union or in third countries, and are covered by the Regulation's rules.&lt;SEP&gt;Operators are individuals or entities that can perform multiple roles, such as acting as both distributors and importers in the AI system development process.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ea757da73e875c6fedacdd166bb91c2e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3725d0d03194d1c923cc1275d5433c2a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019204</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Components">
  <data key="d0">Components</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Components refer to the individual parts or elements that make up an AI system, which may include software modules, hardware, or sub-systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ea757da73e875c6fedacdd166bb91c2e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019204</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Court of Justice of the European Union">
  <data key="d0">Court of Justice of the European Union</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Court of Justice of the European Union reviews decisions made by the Commission under this Regulation and has jurisdiction over penalties.&lt;SEP&gt;The Court of Justice of the European Union has unlimited jurisdiction to review decisions related to fines fixed by the Commission.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37fb1095f63f925386014701386e5a4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ad4d08daad55de411fe1304fd990b8e3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019205</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EC) No 300/2008">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EC) No 300/2008</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EC) No 300/2008 establishes common rules in the field of civil aviation security, impacting the regulations on AI systems used in aviation.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EC) No 300/2008 is a legal document that includes provisions about technical specifications and procedures for security equipment.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EC) No 300/2008 is one of the regulations that is amended by Regulation (EU) 2024/1689.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EC) No 300/2008 relates to common rules in the field of civil aviation security and is referenced in Regulation (EU) 2024/1689.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EC) No 300/2008 outlines rules for civil aviation security and repeals an earlier Regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37fb1095f63f925386014701386e5a4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7078a625612fc9b62bb1e1986ffe1b7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0bb1522a7ffbcc317a23b095e16b092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0cbd1a5d65f0da33dfc2d2c52c0fa26f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ab4686c3d64e748fcf2e50ddb488920</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019205</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) 2024/1689">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) 2024/1689</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) 2024/1689 is a legislative act by the European Parliament and the Council of the European Union concerning rules on artificial intelligence.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2024/1689 sets harmonized rules on artificial intelligence and amends various existing regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2024/1689 establishes harmonized rules on artificial intelligence and amends several existing regulations and directives.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2024/1689 lays down harmonized rules on artificial intelligence, amending several existing regulations and directives.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2024/1689 lays down harmonised rules on artificial intelligence and amends various previous regulations and directives.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37fb1095f63f925386014701386e5a4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7078a625612fc9b62bb1e1986ffe1b7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0bb1522a7ffbcc317a23b095e16b092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b084b4b20e358aaf88a17e35cc6da65d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b64b4983aba9917221464e74b0d86865</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019205</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) No 167/2013">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) No 167/2013</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) No 167/2013 addresses the approval and market surveillance of agricultural and forestry vehicles, relating to high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) No 167/2013 is a legal document that is amended concerning safety components of artificial intelligence systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) No 167/2013 is one of the regulations amended by Regulation (EU) 2024/1689.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) No 167/2013 pertains to the type approval of agricultural and forestry vehicles, and its relevance is noted in the context of the Artificial Intelligence Act.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37fb1095f63f925386014701386e5a4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7078a625612fc9b62bb1e1986ffe1b7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0bb1522a7ffbcc317a23b095e16b092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ab4686c3d64e748fcf2e50ddb488920</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019205</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) No 168/2013">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) No 168/2013</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) No 168/2013 concerns the approval and market surveillance of two- or three-wheel vehicles and quadricycles, relevant to AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) No 168/2013 includes amendments related to artificial intelligence systems' safety components.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) No 168/2013 is another regulation that faces amendments from Regulation (EU) 2024/1689.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) No 168/2013 covers the approval and market surveillance of two- or three-wheel vehicles, referenced for amendments regarding AI.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) No 168/2013 is a legislative act regulating the approval and market surveillance of two- or three-wheel vehicles and quadricycles.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37fb1095f63f925386014701386e5a4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7078a625612fc9b62bb1e1986ffe1b7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0bb1522a7ffbcc317a23b095e16b092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0cbd1a5d65f0da33dfc2d2c52c0fa26f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ab4686c3d64e748fcf2e50ddb488920</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019205</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Artificial Intelligence Act">
  <data key="d0">Artificial Intelligence Act</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The Artificial Intelligence Act, referred to in the regulations, sets forth harmonized rules regarding artificial intelligence.&lt;SEP&gt;The Artificial Intelligence Act is a legislative framework aimed at regulating AI systems and ensuring compliance within the EU.&lt;SEP&gt;The Artificial Intelligence Act is a legislative proposal intended to regulate AI systems within the EU to ensure safety and compliance with established standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37fb1095f63f925386014701386e5a4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7078a625612fc9b62bb1e1986ffe1b7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b084b4b20e358aaf88a17e35cc6da65d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019205</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Remote Biometric Identification">
  <data key="d0">Remote Biometric Identification</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Remote biometric identification refers to the technology that identifies individuals from a distance, potentially leading to biased results and discriminatory effects based on various attributes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d05ea92d6d58b07fd1569406080813a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019205</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High-Risk Classification">
  <data key="d0">High-Risk Classification</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">High-risk classification indicates a categorization for systems that pose significant risks, particularly those that affect persons' rights and safety.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d05ea92d6d58b07fd1569406080813a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019205</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Education">
  <data key="d0">Education</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Education refers to the structured process through which individuals gain knowledge, skills, and competencies, which AI systems may impact significantly.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d05ea92d6d58b07fd1569406080813a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019205</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employment">
  <data key="d0">Employment</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Employment involves work-related contractual relationships, influencing workers' rights, promotion, and decision-making processes.&lt;SEP&gt;Employment refers to the condition of having a paid position in a job, which AI systems analyze for recruitment and management purposes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d05ea92d6d58b07fd1569406080813a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d44ed9cdcce8d29cd4cf7a4556478e3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019205</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Discriminatory Effects">
  <data key="d0">Discriminatory Effects</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Discriminatory effects refer to adverse impacts on individuals based on their age, ethnicity, sex, or disabilities, often as a result of biased systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d05ea92d6d58b07fd1569406080813a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019205</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Directive (EU) 2022/2557">
  <data key="d0">Directive (EU) 2022/2557</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Directive (EU) 2022/2557 outlines regulations regarding critical infrastructure and its role in protecting public safety.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive (EU) 2022/2557 outlines regulations for critical entities and repeals previous directives, affecting the use of biometric identification systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive (EU) 2022/2557 outlines requirements for high-risk AI systems used in the management and operation of critical infrastructure.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d05ea92d6d58b07fd1569406080813a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab5bd61fedb2857e3db189c5f7bb8f94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b4a84f46448cc3a4a1755da273e920e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019206</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="New Provider">
  <data key="d0">New Provider</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A new provider refers to any subsequent entity that assumes responsibility for a high-risk AI system after its initial deployment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-474ee56c196aef9638f343ef09589bca</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019206</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Product Manufacturer">
  <data key="d0">Product Manufacturer</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">A product manufacturer is an entity responsible for creating products that may include high-risk AI systems as components.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-474ee56c196aef9638f343ef09589bca</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019206</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deployers">
  <data key="d0">Deployers</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Deployers are individuals or organizations responsible for using high-risk AI systems, tasked with understanding and informing affected natural persons regarding the system's use.&lt;SEP&gt;Deployers are individuals or entities responsible for using high-risk AI systems under specific guidelines.&lt;SEP&gt;Deployers refer to entities that utilize high-risk AI systems and are responsible for compliance with associated regulations and obligations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-474ee56c196aef9638f343ef09589bca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a13415ed2c222ba72d78fdab855a6ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-358eb1d0b0f35e665a7b23702159cfd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20cc9868fcea5ce578101b36c79a42ff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019206</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Third Parties">
  <data key="d0">Third Parties</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Third parties are entities that make tools, services, and processes accessible to the public and are often involved in the AI value chain.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-20cc9868fcea5ce578101b36c79a42ff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019206</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Directive 2002/14/EC">
  <data key="d0">Directive 2002/14/EC</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Directive 2002/14/EC is a European legal document establishing workers' rights to information and consultation regarding employment issues, including AI system deployment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-20cc9868fcea5ce578101b36c79a42ff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019206</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI Value Chain">
  <data key="d0">AI Value Chain</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The AI Value Chain encompasses all actors involved in the development, deployment, and use of AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;The AI value chain refers to the series of processes and relationships involved in the development, deployment, and integration of AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;The AI value chain refers to the series of processes and stakeholders involved in the development and deployment of AI models.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-20cc9868fcea5ce578101b36c79a42ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed27aea701ddc7f366ea5adbe8a4b8e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97987bc5b95dc5a6f6ebc189b5a394a1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019206</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Obligations">
  <data key="d0">Obligations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Obligations refer to the responsibilities and requirements that need to be fulfilled by providers and deployers of high-risk AI systems according to regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Obligations refer to the responsibilities regarding the detection and labeling of artificially generated or manipulated content as outlined by the Commission.&lt;SEP&gt;Obligations are specific duties and responsibilities that AI providers must adhere to under the regulations specified in Articles 53 and 55.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-20cc9868fcea5ce578101b36c79a42ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bb17f83caa294ef6efb4f278d7d59fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ba035757525dfa257fa2b97fdbd40b2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019206</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Technical Access">
  <data key="d0">Technical Access</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Technical access denotes the necessary permissions and abilities required to engage with AI system components as part of compliance and support.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-20cc9868fcea5ce578101b36c79a42ff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019206</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Directive 2014/90/EU">
  <data key="d0">Directive 2014/90/EU</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Directive 2014/90/EU outlines regulations on marine equipment, crucial for ensuring safety in naval applications of AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive 2014/90/EU establishes requirements for maritime equipment and is subject to amendments through legislative changes regarding AI.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive 2014/90/EU is one of the legal documents affected by Regulation (EU) 2024/1689 amendments.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive 2014/90/EU addresses marine equipment standards and repeals Council Directive 96/98/EC.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7078a625612fc9b62bb1e1986ffe1b7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0bb1522a7ffbcc317a23b095e16b092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0cbd1a5d65f0da33dfc2d2c52c0fa26f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ab4686c3d64e748fcf2e50ddb488920</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019207</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Directive (EU) 2016/797">
  <data key="d0">Directive (EU) 2016/797</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Directive (EU) 2016/797 focuses on interoperability in the rail system within the European Union, affecting AI technologies in transport.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive (EU) 2016/797 relates to railway interoperability and its amendments address the integration of AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive (EU) 2016/797 is a directive that is also impacted by Regulation (EU) 2024/1689.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7078a625612fc9b62bb1e1986ffe1b7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0bb1522a7ffbcc317a23b095e16b092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ab4686c3d64e748fcf2e50ddb488920</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019207</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) 2018/858">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) 2018/858</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) 2018/858 pertains to the approval and market surveillance of motor vehicles and their systems, where AI is utilized.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2018/858 sets rules for the type approval of motor vehicles and includes stipulations for AI systems as safety components.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2018/858 is amended by Regulation (EU) 2024/1689.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2018/858 focuses on the approval and market surveillance of motor vehicles and repeals Directive 2007/46/EC.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7078a625612fc9b62bb1e1986ffe1b7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0bb1522a7ffbcc317a23b095e16b092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0cbd1a5d65f0da33dfc2d2c52c0fa26f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ab4686c3d64e748fcf2e50ddb488920</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019207</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Directive 2016/797">
  <data key="d0">Directive 2016/797</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Directive 2016/797 focuses on the interoperability of the rail system; its relationship with AI regulations is highlighted in the text.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7078a625612fc9b62bb1e1986ffe1b7b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019207</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Financial Institutions">
  <data key="d0">Financial Institutions</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Financial institutions are organizations subject to internal governance requirements and obligations under Union financial services law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5a13415ed2c222ba72d78fdab855a6ca</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019207</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Workers' Representatives">
  <data key="d0">Workers' Representatives</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Workers' representatives are individuals or groups that advocate for the rights and interests of workers concerning the use of AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5a13415ed2c222ba72d78fdab855a6ca</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019207</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Notified Body">
  <data key="d0">Notified Body</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Notified Body is a conformity assessment body recognized under specific regulations and applicable legislation. It is an organization designated to evaluate the conformity of certain products before they can be legally placed on the market, ensuring that these products meet the required standards for safety and performance.

Established under national law in a Member State, the Notified Body carries out conformity assessments which may involve several processes, including reviewing the quality management systems of manufacturers and ensuring compliance with necessary regulations. In addition to this, a Notified Body examines technical documentation for products, particularly high-risk AI systems, and assesses whether they meet the relevant regulatory requirements.

The Notified Body also plays a crucial role in monitoring compliance of high-risk AI systems with legal requirements, assessing any changes and notifying providers as necessary. Furthermore, they have the authority to issue assessment certificates, confirming that certain products meet the stipulated standards. It is important to note that the designation of a Notified Body can be subjected to restrictions or withdrawals under circumstances stipulated in applicable legislation, which underscores the regulatory oversight in the function of these bodies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d17f49a76bb2cf6b427b715f614df19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d997baeb2a2ac2118ac1e3e19dfcf16&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6507d56efb6357f20f57227d44b681ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0714fdb65a0577bc4493dcb81d0a915&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60ded1802882124212402df3d80de903&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d08b2a930ede07e77c7cc4f29016fc57&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-741b1675a971d075b2d3571148530b89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d2a58a86edb7bec623750da3d232aa2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e14a05a776d89b0f172b0c5789b0936</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019207</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Banking Entities">
  <data key="d0">Banking Entities</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Banking entities are regulated organizations that may deploy high-risk AI systems in compliance with public service obligations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-358eb1d0b0f35e665a7b23702159cfd5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019207</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Insurance Entities">
  <data key="d0">Insurance Entities</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Insurance entities are businesses that may deploy high-risk AI systems under public service frameworks to assess risks and provide services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-358eb1d0b0f35e665a7b23702159cfd5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019207</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Post-Remote Biometric Identification Systems">
  <data key="d0">Post-Remote Biometric Identification Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Post-remote biometric identification systems are technologies that analyze biometric data from a distance for identification purposes, requiring strict regulations due to their intrusive nature.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-358eb1d0b0f35e665a7b23702159cfd5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019207</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Directive (EU) 2020/1828">
  <data key="d0">Directive (EU) 2020/1828</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Directive (EU) 2020/1828 focuses on representative actions for the protection of collective consumer interests.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive (EU) 2020/1828 is among the directives amended by Regulation (EU) 2024/1689.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e0bb1522a7ffbcc317a23b095e16b092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b084b4b20e358aaf88a17e35cc6da65d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
