<node id="Systemic Risks">
  <data key="d0">Systemic Risks</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Systemic risks relate to potential negative effects associated with general-purpose AI models, including threats to public safety, democratic processes, and the dissemination of harmful content.&lt;SEP&gt;Systemic risks refer to potential hazards associated with the capabilities and impacts of general-purpose AI models on society and the market.&lt;SEP&gt;Systemic risks refer to potential issues that can arise from the development and use of general-purpose AI models, which could lead to serious incidents.&lt;SEP&gt;Systemic Risks in the context refer to potential issues arising from the design and use of online services that providers must assess and mitigate.&lt;SEP&gt;Systemic Risks refer to potential threats posed by the development or use of General-Purpose AI Models that can impact the Union or its citizens.&lt;SEP&gt;Systemic risks refer to potential threats posed by AI systems that may impact the broader system at Union level.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0a8f57272764fbaa96a8c14389c0661d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d97d0e266280dff1c105fac7dc08fc5d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed27aea701ddc7f366ea5adbe8a4b8e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-837ff2237a4d4f4c44aa67702b89ec06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13766dce116c63c31fc5d746b27279fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ba035757525dfa257fa2b97fdbd40b2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019211</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Small and Medium Enterprises (SMEs)">
  <data key="d0">Small and Medium Enterprises (SMEs)</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Small and Medium Enterprises (SMEs) are businesses that may need simplified compliance paths regarding AI model regulations, balancing costs and usability.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0a8f57272764fbaa96a8c14389c0661d</data>
