<node id="Harmonised Standards">
  <data key="d0">Harmonised Standards</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Harmonised Standards are standards that conform to the requirements established by European regulations, including those concerning compliance.&lt;SEP&gt;Harmonised standards are technical specifications recognized and used to demonstrate the conformity of high-risk AI systems or general-purpose AI models.&lt;SEP&gt;Harmonised standards are established criteria that AI systems must meet to ensure compliance with regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Harmonised standards refer to established criteria to ensure compliance with specific regulatory requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Harmonised Standards are the agreed-upon criteria or guidelines applied to ensure AI systems meet regulatory requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0714fdb65a0577bc4493dcb81d0a915&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-926dc457d536779e13715d0b813c320d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-837ff2237a4d4f4c44aa67702b89ec06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfb1222254442ec5ae96316c08a386f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-561d345a761ead6d6e1bfabd0f89e09c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019212</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Civil Society Organisations">
  <data key="d0">Civil Society Organisations</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Civil society organisations may be consulted by the AI Office to ensure diverse perspectives are included in the development of codes of practice.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed27aea701ddc7f366ea5adbe8a4b8e8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) 2022/2065">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) 2022/2065</data>
  <data key="d1">regulation</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) 2022/2065 pertains to the liability of providers of intermediary services in the realm of digital services.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2022/2065 provides a risk-management framework for AI systems and models embedded in large online platforms.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2022/2065 sets out obligations for providers of large online platforms and search engines regarding systemic risks associated with their services.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2022/2065 establishes obligations for AI systems, including the labeling of artificially generated content to protect public interest and democracy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed27aea701ddc7f366ea5adbe8a4b8e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-837ff2237a4d4f4c44aa67702b89ec06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a169417b09f70fa2792a3c9ce82a678d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74667d89df5ee6111b7743e86ee4744f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Risk-Management Policies">
  <data key="d0">Risk-Management Policies</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Risk-management policies are guidelines established to manage systemic risks associated with general-purpose AI models.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed27aea701ddc7f366ea5adbe8a4b8e8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="International Approaches">
  <data key="d0">International Approaches</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">International approaches involve diverse methods and strategies adopted globally to regulate and manage AI technologies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed27aea701ddc7f366ea5adbe8a4b8e8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Educational and Vocational Training Institutions">
  <data key="d0">Educational and Vocational Training Institutions</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Educational and vocational training institutions provide learning environments for natural persons at different levels of education.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d44ed9cdcce8d29cd4cf7a4556478e3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Self-Employment">
  <data key="d0">Self-Employment</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Self-employment refers to individuals working for themselves rather than being employed by others, often evaluated by AI systems for eligibility and support.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d44ed9cdcce8d29cd4cf7a4556478e3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Creditworthiness">
  <data key="d0">Creditworthiness</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Creditworthiness is an evaluation of the ability of a natural person to repay debts, often assessed by AI systems for financial services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d44ed9cdcce8d29cd4cf7a4556478e3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Emergency First Response Services">
  <data key="d0">Emergency First Response Services</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Emergency first response services include police, firefighters, and medical aid, which utilize AI systems for dispatch and triage.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d44ed9cdcce8d29cd4cf7a4556478e3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Section 5">
  <data key="d0">Section 5</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Section 5 outlines standards, conformity assessments, and certifications related to high-risk AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-926dc457d536779e13715d0b813c320d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chapter V">
  <data key="d0">Chapter V</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Chapter V includes sections that impose obligations on AI systems within the regulatory framework.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-926dc457d536779e13715d0b813c320d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Standardisation Requests">
  <data key="d0">Standardisation Requests</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Standardisation requests are issued by the Commission to elicit the development of standards for AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-926dc457d536779e13715d0b813c320d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Common Specifications">
  <data key="d0">Common Specifications</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Common specifications are implementing acts that establish requirements for AI system regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Common specifications are technical criteria developed to ensure high-risk AI systems meet necessary compliance requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-926dc457d536779e13715d0b813c320d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfb1222254442ec5ae96316c08a386f0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Online Search Engines">
  <data key="d0">Online Search Engines</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Online Search Engines are platforms that use AI systems to perform searches and integrate results, falling under the obligations of Regulation (EU) 2022/2065.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-837ff2237a4d4f4c44aa67702b89ec06</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Very Large Online Platforms">
  <data key="d0">Very Large Online Platforms</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Very Large Online Platforms are digital services with substantial user bases, subject to specific obligations under Regulation (EU) 2022/2065 regarding risk assessment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-837ff2237a4d4f4c44aa67702b89ec06</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mitigating Measures">
  <data key="d0">Mitigating Measures</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Mitigating Measures are actions that providers must take to address and alleviate identified systemic risks as outlined in Regulation (EU) 2022/2065.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-837ff2237a4d4f4c44aa67702b89ec06</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European Standardisation">
  <data key="d0">European Standardisation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">European Standardisation refers to the process of developing common standards to ensure compliance with regulations such as Regulation (EU) 2022/2065.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-837ff2237a4d4f4c44aa67702b89ec06</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
