</node>
<node id="Microenterprises">
  <data key="d0">Microenterprises</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Microenterprises refer to very small operators that have specific obligations under the Regulation yet face fewer administrative burdens.&lt;SEP&gt;Microenterprises are small businesses with specific guidelines issued by the Commission for compliance with regulations pertaining to AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-15ddf6f50e7dd1750489a4999454bcdf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e4463f7eaf425919a6a8182d693643c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019219</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Advisory Forum">
  <data key="d0">Advisory Forum</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Advisory Forum contributes stakeholder input to the implementation of the Regulation at both Union and national levels.&lt;SEP&gt;The Advisory Forum is established to provide advice and technical expertise to the Board and the Commission, ensuring diverse stakeholder representation.&lt;SEP&gt;The Advisory Forum is established to provide technical expertise and to advise the Board and the Commission in relation to AI regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-15ddf6f50e7dd1750489a4999454bcdf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df0cf5bee4370453cb38606bad89b764&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5a5973b039f9a9af3e3e9d93b392c66</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019219</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Quality Management System Elements">
  <data key="d0">Quality Management System Elements</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Quality Management System Elements are components that microenterprises are required to fulfill under the simplified framework as part of the Regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-15ddf6f50e7dd1750489a4999454bcdf</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019219</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="System Architecture">
  <data key="d0">System Architecture</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">System architecture describes the arrangement and interaction of software components within a general-purpose AI model.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e8ea3c173c0c1e99c19f3957adaea81b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019219</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Integration">
  <data key="d0">Integration</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Integration is the process of incorporating a general-purpose AI model into various AI systems, encompassing tasks and input-output modalities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e8ea3c173c0c1e99c19f3957adaea81b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019219</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Model Parameters">
  <data key="d0">Model Parameters</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Model parameters outline the architecture and specifications that influence the behavior of the AI model.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e8ea3c173c0c1e99c19f3957adaea81b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019219</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Set Quality">
  <data key="d0">Data Set Quality</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Data set quality refers to the metrics that assess the size and accuracy of data used for training an AI model.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e8ea3c173c0c1e99c19f3957adaea81b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019219</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Training Computation">
  <data key="d0">Training Computation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Training computation details the resources, such as floating point operations and estimated costs, required to train an AI model.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e8ea3c173c0c1e99c19f3957adaea81b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019219</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Input and Output Modalities">
  <data key="d0">Input and Output Modalities</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Input and output modalities specify the forms of data that a general-purpose AI model can process and generate, including text, images, and other types.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e8ea3c173c0c1e99c19f3957adaea81b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019219</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Registered Business Users">
  <data key="d0">Registered Business Users</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Registered business users are entities that utilize the general-purpose AI model, impacting its reach and significance in the market.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e8ea3c173c0c1e99c19f3957adaea81b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019219</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Registered End-Users">
  <data key="d0">Registered End-Users</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Registered end-users are individuals or organizations that directly engage with the general-purpose AI model for specific tasks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e8ea3c173c0c1e99c19f3957adaea81b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019219</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Adversarial Testing">
  <data key="d0">Adversarial Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Adversarial testing refers to the measures implemented to evaluate the robustness of a system, including techniques like red teaming against the general-purpose AI model.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e8ea3c173c0c1e99c19f3957adaea81b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019219</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Model Adaptations">
  <data key="d0">Model Adaptations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Model adaptations involve changes made to the AI model, including alignment and fine-tuning to improve performance and applicability.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e8ea3c173c0c1e99c19f3957adaea81b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019219</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
