<node id="Ethics Guidelines for Trustworthy AI">
  <data key="d0">Ethics Guidelines for Trustworthy AI</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Ethics guidelines for trustworthy AI comprise a set of ethical principles that guide the development and use of AI to ensure trustworthiness and accountability.&lt;SEP&gt;The Ethics Guidelines for Trustworthy AI set the framework for ethical and trustworthy AI systems within the Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-061f3c307dd55152ffbb5bdfae17ea90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4996cfa66f0668d565cd83bbe46dd21a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019220</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI HLEG">
  <data key="d0">AI HLEG</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The AI HLEG (High-Level Expert Group on Artificial Intelligence) is an independent group appointed by the Commission to develop ethical guidelines for AI.&lt;SEP&gt;The AI HLEG is a group that provides guidelines for the development and use of AI systems emphasizing human agency and oversight.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-061f3c307dd55152ffbb5bdfae17ea90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f8eb19a191801e8405a7745849c61a0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019220</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Risk-Based Approach">
  <data key="d0">Risk-Based Approach</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The risk-based approach is a method outlined in the Regulation to tailor binding rules for AI systems based on the intensity and scope of potential risks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-061f3c307dd55152ffbb5bdfae17ea90</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019220</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
