  <data key="d5">1773019222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) 2019/1937">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) 2019/1937</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) 2019/1937 is a directive of the European Parliament and the Council aimed at protecting individuals reporting breaches of Union law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6a7c04a6e62adc17c47006b55b3e8bce</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 290 TFEU">
  <data key="d0">Article 290 TFEU</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 290 TFEU pertains to the delegation of powers to the Commission to adopt certain acts, particularly regarding regulatory frameworks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6a7c04a6e62adc17c47006b55b3e8bce</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="human centric and trustworthy AI">
  <data key="d0">human centric and trustworthy AI</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Human-centric and trustworthy AI refers to artificial intelligence systems designed with consideration for human rights, safety, and ethical standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6a7c04a6e62adc17c47006b55b3e8bce</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="2 August 2029">
  <data key="d0">2 August 2029</data>
  <data key="d1">date</data>
  <data key="d2">2 August 2029 is a deadline set for the Commission to evaluate and review the Regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6a7c04a6e62adc17c47006b55b3e8bce</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="2 August 2028">
  <data key="d0">2 August 2028</data>
  <data key="d1">date</data>
  <data key="d2">2 August 2028 is a deadline for the Commission to report on the need to amend the list of high-risk areas.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6a7c04a6e62adc17c47006b55b3e8bce</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 49(5)">
  <data key="d0">Article 49(5)</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 49(5) outlines requirements for testing of high-risk AI systems in real-world conditions within Union law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-caf8819d467d1204dd768c10cacdbf06</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Prospective Provider">
  <data key="d0">Prospective Provider</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">A prospective provider is an entity that intends to conduct testing of high-risk AI systems but has not yet done so.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-caf8819d467d1204dd768c10cacdbf06</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Legal Representative">
  <data key="d0">Legal Representative</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A legal representative is an individual appointed by a provider or prospective provider to act on their behalf within the Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-caf8819d467d1204dd768c10cacdbf06</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Parliament">
  <data key="d0">Parliament</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Parliament is a governing body that has laid down rules and general principles concerning control mechanisms of the Commission's implementing powers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3d055d5f99b33b0d67edb91e844c4185</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Implementation Regulation">
  <data key="d0">Implementation Regulation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Implementation Regulation governs the mechanisms and requirements for the oversight and use of AI technologies in the European Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3d055d5f99b33b0d67edb91e844c4185</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 5 TEU">
  <data key="d0">Article 5 TEU</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 5 of the Treaty on European Union outlines the principles of subsidiarity and proportionality relevant to EU legislation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3d055d5f99b33b0d67edb91e844c4185</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019223</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI Models">
  <data key="d0">AI Models</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">AI Models are systems created using artificial intelligence technology, which are subject to the same regulations as AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;AI models are algorithms that power artificial intelligence systems, including general-purpose AI models mentioned in the Regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;AI Models refer to general-purpose artificial intelligence systems that require classification and risk assessment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-55fa705f95ec5acec79f8b691041b65c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-413f3509ccce7d84f0a2044eb12be69f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfd6bb7a9801a10b9d2b6a706f0d919d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019223</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI">
  <data key="d0">AI</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">AI, or artificial intelligence, encompasses technologies that can perform tasks that typically require human intelligence, which is regulated by the European Artificial Intelligence Board.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77f7e4da7918161a180fb26c5a1704ff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019223</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Risk">
  <data key="d0">Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Risk represents the combination of the probability of harm occurring and the severity of that harm associated with AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-51c94d77f328c85a261162f4664235f6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019223</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Distributor">
  <data key="d0">Distributor</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A distributor is a person in the supply chain making an AI system available on the Union market, distinct from provider or importer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-51c94d77f328c85a261162f4664235f6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019223</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Operator">
  <data key="d0">Operator</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An operator encompasses various roles including provider, importer, or distributor involved in AI system management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-51c94d77f328c85a261162f4664235f6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019223</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Placing on the Market">
  <data key="d0">Placing on the Market</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Placing on the market refers to the initial availability of an AI system or a general-purpose AI model in the Union market.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-51c94d77f328c85a261162f4664235f6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019223</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Putting into Service">
  <data key="d0">Putting into Service</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Putting into service signifies the supply of an AI system for first use directed towards the deployer in the Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-51c94d77f328c85a261162f4664235f6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019223</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Legal Person">
  <data key="d0">Legal Person</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A legal person refers to an entity, such as a corporation or organization, that has legal rights and obligations like a natural person, particularly in the domain of deploying AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-51c94d77f328c85a261162f4664235f6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019223</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 74(11)">
  <data key="d0">Article 74(11)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 74(11) refers to a specific provision within the Regulation focused on market surveillance authorities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-413f3509ccce7d84f0a2044eb12be69f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773019223</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
