<edge source="Commission" target="European Parliament">
  <data key="d7">8.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation known as the Commission of the European Parliament plays a crucial role in the legislative framework of the European Union. This relationship is characterized by collaboration and information exchange between both entities to ensure effective governance and legislation.

The Commission and the European Parliament work together to evaluate data protection measures, ensuring that they align with established regulations. As part of the regulatory preparation process, the Commission is responsible for transmitting relevant documents to the European Parliament, which facilitates informed discussions and decisions regarding legislation.

Additionally, the European Parliament is actively involved in the creation and enactment of legislation, frequently collaborating with the Commission to shape laws within the EU framework. The Commission notifies the European Parliament about various significant activities, including the adoption of delegated acts and regulatory decisions. This communication is vital for ensuring that Parliament is kept informed and can respond appropriately to developments in regulation.

Furthermore, the Commission takes into account findings and recommendations from the European Parliament when drafting legislative proposals, demonstrating a responsive governance model. The involvement of the European Parliament in the consultation process is essential, as it plays a key role in shaping final legislation and holds the Commission accountable for its actions. The obligation for the Commission to evaluate and report on specific regulations further illustrates the ongoing interaction between these entities in fulfilling their legislative responsibilities.

In summary, the relationship between the Commission and the European Parliament is integral to the legislative process in the European Union, characterized by active collaboration, notification of developments, and the integration of parliamentary insights into legislative proposals.</data>
  <data key="d9">collaboration,consultation,decision-making,document sharing,governance,legislative collaboration,legislative evaluation,legislative process,notification,reporting</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-2cbf3f86a25d11cd5d991d79db9a221a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f087b1b4f7f6e16afe33b8014a5f30c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58a23170492ef728683ec4aa9e03ccb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e302930e155db8d2b9e787df655d5751&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b39c0bb45bd2a8849aa7e9bcb8c9d4a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f5283f6c8ea50d5bcac79684f773610&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5f6ef3b354bb0dbf8af7b2c108fd236&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6a7c04a6e62adc17c47006b55b3e8bce</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1773019318</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
