<edge source="Commission" target="Member States">
  <data key="d7">16.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation between the Commission and the Member States encompasses a framework of oversight, collaboration, and compliance particularly regarding data protection and artificial intelligence (AI) regulations. The Commission is responsible for ensuring that Member States adhere to data protection regulations, and it engages with them to promote compliance through various measures, including certification mechanisms. This includes the requirement for Member States to notify the Commission of changes and provisions in their laws pertaining to data protection, as well as the rules concerning law enforcement and AI systems.

The Commission also plays a critical role in guiding Member States in the implementation of AI regulations and ensuring that these regulations comply with ethical standards and local needs. Member States are tasked with informing the Commission about their regulatory frameworks for AI, including measures surrounding penalties and enforcement. This collaborative relationship facilitates ongoing communication, allowing the Member States to update the Commission regarding the list of notified bodies and any changes to their status.

Furthermore, the Commission encourages Member States to work under its supervision in matters of conformity assessments and to actively participate in consultations about these processes. The establishment of regulatory sandboxes for AI is another area where Member States collaborate with the Commission to meet compliance requirements. Throughout these interactions, the Commission and Member States strive to ensure that data protection regulations and AI-related measures are effectively implemented and constantly updated to address emerging challenges and necessities.

In summary, the relationship between the Commission and the Member States is characterized by mutual cooperation aimed at maintaining regulatory compliance in data protection and AI systems, promoting ethical standards, and facilitating information exchange to uphold the integrity of the regulatory framework.</data>
  <data key="d9">collaboration,communication,compliance,consultation,cooperation,enforcement,ethical guidelines,governance,implementation,implementation support,information sharing,legal provisions,notification,oversight,regulation collaboration,regulatory authority,regulatory compliance,regulatory framework,regulatory oversight,responsibilities</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-fe63429efbb90ae6ec22b62b5d79e7b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d44a5f83cf273e81899482e995be2a98&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fb6a4af737980e04056c2522ea213fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3642f938e14bfed60a5d5b5fdc383e38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-088a4c3c3c775d33baa63868a127c869&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b75f7d42df244a78773a748afb4f421f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f5283f6c8ea50d5bcac79684f773610&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5f6ef3b354bb0dbf8af7b2c108fd236&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d997baeb2a2ac2118ac1e3e19dfcf16&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6507d56efb6357f20f57227d44b681ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b14c58587932db3a6dafb07fe1b8b673&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf7d18a6020405fb3429834a129e7cd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f743aee05d8e1afc03000436802a1ad2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-413f3509ccce7d84f0a2044eb12be69f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfd6bb7a9801a10b9d2b6a706f0d919d</data>
