<edge source="Member State" target="Supervisory Authority">
  <data key="d7">7.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Each Member State has its own Supervisory Authority to enforce data protection regulations locally.&lt;SEP&gt;The Supervisory Authority operates within the regulatory framework established by a Member State.&lt;SEP&gt;Supervisory Authority is established by a Member State to ensure compliance with data protection regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Each Member State is responsible for establishing its own Supervisory Authority to ensure compliance with regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Supervisory Authority has oversight and legal authority within each Member State to enforce data protection regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The supervisory authority oversees compliance with data protection regulations among Member States.&lt;SEP&gt;The Supervisory Authority operates within the jurisdiction of the specific Member State it represents.</data>
  <data key="d9">data protection,enforcement,establishment,jurisdiction,legal authority,oversight,public authority,regulatory compliance,regulatory framework,regulatory oversight</data>
