<edge source="Union" target="Member States">
  <data key="d7">6.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Member States are responsible for implementing data protection regulations within the framework of the Union.&lt;SEP&gt;The Union establishes a regulatory framework that Member States must adhere to regarding data protection.&lt;SEP&gt;Member States operate within the jurisdiction of the Union and must adhere to its regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Member states are governed by the regulations and legal frameworks established by the Union.&lt;SEP&gt;Member States operate within the framework established by the Union while retaining specific competencies, especially regarding national security.&lt;SEP&gt;The Union provides regulatory frameworks that guide Member States in the governance of AI system usage and protections for workers.</data>
  <data key="d9">collective agreement,compliance,governance,government structure,implementation,jurisdiction,legal authority,membership,regulation,regulatory framework</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-499a505625518b0e48c48965f5a70336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9403aaca1e6e92e51844c1b1175b373b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e47ed52d4514f1818e6c0687c1aa57e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00803764d58d840979922e38d1dc555c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55fa705f95ec5acec79f8b691041b65c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51c94d77f328c85a261162f4664235f6</data>
