<edge source="Supervisory Authority" target="Controller">
  <data key="d7">12.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relationship between the Controller and the Supervisory Authority involves critical oversight regarding compliance with personal data processing regulations. The Controller is obligated to cooperate with the Supervisory Authority to adhere to these regulatory requirements, ensuring that all activities meet the established standards for data protection.

In situations where a personal data breach occurs, the Controller must notify the Supervisory Authority promptly. Additionally, prior consultation with the authority is required when engaging in operations deemed to be high-risk concerning personal data processing. This proactive approach ensures that any potential risks are managed in accordance with guidelines set out by the Supervisory Authority.

The Supervisory Authority plays a key role in enforcing regulations that the Controller must follow. They are responsible for monitoring the activities of the Controller, guaranteeing adherence to applicable data protection legislation. This includes oversight of compliance and the authority to mandate corrective actions in response to data breaches or non-compliance with legal standards.

The Controller has specific obligations, including informing Data Subjects of their right to lodge a complaint with the Supervisory Authority if their requests regarding personal data are neglected. This transparency is essential for maintaining trust and accountability in data management practices.

Overall, the Supervisory Authority ensures that Controllers comply with data protection laws and regulations, which are critical for safeguarding personal data. The collaborative relationship between the Controller and the Supervisory Authority is vital for upholding data protection principles and addressing any compliance issues that arise in the handling of personal data.</data>
  <data key="d9">accountability,complaint process,compliance,compliance oversight,compliance verification,consultation,cooperation,enforcement,oversight,regulation,regulatory compliance,regulatory oversight,responsibility</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-ca204399e5b95988e550678c5f4db7ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47177763646868a685685b7567bea40f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89bcf919dc1ff2d224ffc9b6e042a2c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ce3387b9f0e9256cf8b0a10e0726f37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3626adc7cf865bec83f6479c1e08cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e144d059e01c4df4d2fdb9406d31751d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7aa4d903bc5ead1fdb896356fd92fbd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8252fb4b704db3adac7bfb7714d3b70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df28c0bb060b598df163cc06bf49d0e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f71c70521bc1935b4a077373428f4b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c22927198decad5ee173ab2f05d62983</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1773019001</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Supervisory Authority" target="Processor">
  <data key="d7">3.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The Processor is subject to oversight by the Supervisory Authority to ensure adherence to regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Processor is also required to consult with the Supervisory Authority regarding processing matters.&lt;SEP&gt;The supervisory authority monitors and ensures processors comply with data protection obligations.</data>
  <data key="d9">compliance,consultation,oversight,regulatory compliance,regulatory oversight,responsibility</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-ca204399e5b95988e550678c5f4db7ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ce3387b9f0e9256cf8b0a10e0726f37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f71c70521bc1935b4a077373428f4b1</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1773019001</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Supervisory Authority" target="Data Subject">
  <data key="d7">4.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The supervisory authority is responsible for communicating the progress of complaints to the data subjects.&lt;SEP&gt;Data subjects have the right to lodge complaints with a supervisory authority regarding potential infringements of their rights.&lt;SEP&gt;The Supervisory Authority oversees the rights and protections of the Data Subject concerning their personal data.&lt;SEP&gt;Data Subjects have the right to lodge complaints with a supervisory authority regarding the processing of their personal data.</data>
  <data key="d9">communication,complaint mechanism,complaint process,oversight,personal data,rights protection</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-8bb97fdc90c81e778311b34e1a2883b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-36a1ea945634c046899535f1e8f39a77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af9d06fe383d38e16d29be00a265867e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af27fd67de6b968672bf93dbf11392ac</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
