  <data key="d8">The supervisory authority has the responsibility to oversee compliance and may revoke a certification if conditions are not met.&lt;SEP&gt;The certification body is required to provide reasons to the supervisory authority for granting or withdrawing certifications.&lt;SEP&gt;The Supervisory Authority oversees the Certification Body's actions regarding the issuance and withdrawal of certifications.</data>
  <data key="d9">compliance,enforcement,oversight,regulatory oversight</data>
