<edge source="Supervisory Authority" target="Board">
  <data key="d7">7.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The Board is empowered to adopt decisions and issue opinions involving supervisory authorities during disputes.&lt;SEP&gt;The supervisory authority operates under the directives of the Board, which governs its decision-making process.&lt;SEP&gt;The supervisory authority transmits requirements and criteria to the Board as part of regulatory oversight.&lt;SEP&gt;The Board issues opinions regarding measures related to the supervisory authority's decisions in Member States.&lt;SEP&gt;The Board oversees the decisions and objections raised by the supervisory authority concerning draft regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Supervisory Authority must inform the Board of any decisions made regarding data subjects and complaints.&lt;SEP&gt;The Supervisory Authority forwards opinions or decisions from the Board to the court when necessary.</data>
  <data key="d9">authority,compliance measures,decision oversight,decision process,decision-making,information transmission,opinion issuance,oversight,regulation,regulatory framework,reporting</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-c9552394e758f858742ece06fe166111&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da5e0cbe02b415c14c47d962922ae943&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51e09a8c8db52827f80f9874a8d4e4de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f087b1b4f7f6e16afe33b8014a5f30c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af9d06fe383d38e16d29be00a265867e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af27fd67de6b968672bf93dbf11392ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4fb6b788c6bc23206d8cd996c5a6a6b</data>
