<edge source="Controller" target="Processor">
  <data key="d7">15.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation between the Controller and the Processor is vital in the context of data protection and privacy. The Controller is responsible for establishing the purposes and means of personal data processing and retains overall responsibility for compliance with applicable regulations. This role involves making crucial decisions regarding data processing activities and ensuring that all actions adhere to legal standards.

The Processor, on the other hand, operates under the authority of the Controller, carrying out the actual processing of personal data as per the Controller's instructions. Its responsibilities include managing specific data processing tasks while ensuring compliance with legal obligations set forth. The Processor acts on behalf of the Controller, following defined guidelines and contractual agreements that clarify their roles and responsibilities in handling the data.

The relationship between the Controller and Processor is characterized by collaboration aimed at ensuring adherence to data protection regulations. The Controller may engage the Processor through a contractual agreement that outlines the obligations each party must fulfill. For instance, the Processor is required to notify the Controller of any personal data breaches that may occur, adhering to established protocols designed to protect sensitive information.

Ultimately, while the Processor effectively manages data processing tasks, the Controller maintains the primary accountability for determining how personal data should be processed and ensuring that all processing activities comply with relevant data protection laws. This dynamic underscores the importance of their cooperation to achieve compliance and safeguard personal data.</data>
  <data key="d9">authority,collaboration,compliance,compliance assistance,contractual relationship,data handling,data management,data processing,delegation,liability,operational responsibility,organizational role,processing relationship,relationship,responsibilities,responsibility,roles</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-1fc0f10aaf2165d757efc7d75a7d7d18&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47177763646868a685685b7567bea40f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bb97fdc90c81e778311b34e1a2883b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1552a23fe0792f0f86048881370b455d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ce3387b9f0e9256cf8b0a10e0726f37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7071cdf0dedffd1eaf46713ebddb9b1e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66ded376bcd1c12c425bce88cfd552a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0ab083807b5f91410241f4f574d25b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f087b1b4f7f6e16afe33b8014a5f30c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bbf8c83dfe1a6df2d3a3d01645abe8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db7bcd6a42a9c26ced1d71444d109dff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-499a505625518b0e48c48965f5a70336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8907f0fe9fc1b981b8c734b5cbf9008&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e5e9be572ec001588771fa74ce45258</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1773019008</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Controller" target="Data Subject">
  <data key="d7">20.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation between the Controller and the Data Subject is fundamental in the context of data protection and privacy laws. The Controller is defined as the entity that determines the purposes and means of processing personal data and is tasked with acquiring explicit consent from the Data Subject before any data processing occurs. This responsibility requires the Controller not only to respect the Data Subject's rights but also to actively uphold and protect those rights throughout the data processing lifecycle.

The Controller is obligated to respond promptly to any requests made by the Data Subject concerning their personal data. This includes a duty to inform the Data Subject about their rights under data protection regulations and disclose any actions taken regarding their requests. The Controller must demonstrate that the Data Subject has consented to the processing of their data, and they are responsible for ensuring that the consent meets legal standards. Furthermore, the Controller must provide comprehensive information to the Data Subject about the processing activities involving their personal data.

Moreover, the Data Subject is the individual whose personal data is being processed, and they hold specific rights under relevant data protection laws, including the right to restrict processing and to seek judicial remedies against any infringements concerning their data rights. The Controller must adhere to these rights, ensuring that the Data Subject is fully informed about the data processing operations and their implications.

In summary, the Controller bears the primary responsibility for managing the personal data of the Data Subject, ensuring compliance with applicable regulations, maintaining transparency in data processing practices, and safeguarding the rights of the Data Subject throughout the entire process.</data>
  <data key="d9">compliance,consent,consent acquisition,consent requirement,data processing,data processing authority,data protection,data rights,information,processing authority,responsibilities,responsibility,rights,rights and responsibilities,rights notification,rights protection</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-8bb97fdc90c81e778311b34e1a2883b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b303412f58783d3e4bc19dbad4e2a43c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd97dcdb68144953a81ad8ba7d8f52b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0ab083807b5f91410241f4f574d25b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bfe3c72af8b2bd319fe191920f25097&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f087b1b4f7f6e16afe33b8014a5f30c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b661d0b109eaf570a61ae0d0ca8020b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbc89674e06d04462cc498a8c1da1d44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62b277bc6fa564a434a6c338a48eea46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca37d7dbc74be645fc1de3e6e772a586&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2016931a6e14615018d3d7f8304b6a1e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e144d059e01c4df4d2fdb9406d31751d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9355b1cd3c48988b8332485ef99af2c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7aa4d903bc5ead1fdb896356fd92fbd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8252fb4b704db3adac7bfb7714d3b70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d92eec8ceb3813d55e2b578c5604f24&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae28521738df7feadad1be4821afc294&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c09ea8bbba955df15eafbe1da5facb38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b3266fc2be81fd61dcffc1afc41700b</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
