<edge source="Member State Law" target="Union Law">
  <data key="d7">7.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Member State Law must comply with Union Law regarding the conditions and regulations for processing personal data.&lt;SEP&gt;Union Law provides guidelines that Member State Law must align with regarding the processing of personal data.&lt;SEP&gt;Member State Law operates within the framework established by Union law, ensuring compliance with data protection principles.&lt;SEP&gt;Union Law and Member State Law work together to enforce regulations regarding data protection and processing.&lt;SEP&gt;Union Law governs and influences the legal obligations imposed by individual Member State laws.&lt;SEP&gt;Union law and Member State law provide the regulatory framework that governs the processing of personal data and ensures compliance for controllers and processors.&lt;SEP&gt;Union Law provides overarching guidance that Member State Law must align with regarding data subject rights.</data>
  <data key="d9">data processing,data protection,legal compliance,legal framework,legislative measures,national regulation,regulation compliance,regulatory framework</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-3ce3387b9f0e9256cf8b0a10e0726f37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b303412f58783d3e4bc19dbad4e2a43c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0ab083807b5f91410241f4f574d25b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8ea5b2826564cb4f4f5c8c193fab368&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc7a45c7f8eea9ab9297b5839c19c2a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62b277bc6fa564a434a6c338a48eea46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fa893844a2197c46302e74437f2bbef</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1773019011</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
